aS'<p>As a law firm in Savannah, The Conner Law Group has worked with the surviving families of individuals who died because of negligence on the part of product manufacturers or service providers.&#160;The causes of <strong>wrongful death</strong> can include the following:</p><ul><li>Motor vehicle accidents: Operators and manufacturers of autos, motorcycles, ATVs, go-karts, boats, powered mopeds and scooters, dune buggies, and personal watercraft</li><li>Workplace accidents: Construction site mishaps, road work collisions, explosions, electrocutions, falls, falling objects, defective machinery and improper training</li><li>Nursing home abuse and neglect: Improper restraints (chemical and physical), bed sores, malnutrition, dehydrations, injurious pressure and infections (such as gangrene)</li><li>Medical malpractice: Birth trauma, anesthesia error, ER negligence, failure to diagnose, surgical errors, <a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/08/30/AR2010083003946.html?hpid=sec-health">unnecessary treatment and misdiagnosis</a></li><li>Pharmacy mistakes: Medication errors such as improper dosages, incorrect medications and other prescription filling errors</li><li>Un-secure and unsafe premises: Non-functioning video and alarm security systems, malfunctioning locks, poorly trained security personnel, toxic substances on-site, carbon monoxide at toxic levels, slip-fall hazards, and faulty athletic and amusement facilities</li></ul><p>Finding an attorney, preparing an effective case</p><p>Of course, every scenario is different, as is the negligence of those who are responsible.&#160; No two cases are alike.&#160; But when someone dies in an accident as a result of the actions of others, whether in Savannah or elsewhere, <strong>wrongful death</strong> claims necessarily should be filed.&#160; That accident removed the love, companionship and financial contribution the deceased played in your family.&#160; You are legally entitled to compensation.</p><p>When you begin your search and call law firms that handle wrongful death claims, you should always inquire about the case experience of the attorney or attorneys who may represent you in Savannah courts.&#160;Your <a title="Savannah Wrongful Death Attorney" href="http://www.mikeconner.com/">Savannah wrongful death attorney</a>&#160;accepts your case on contingency only, meaning an attorney earns no fees until a successful settlement.</p><p>Contact us</p><p>Whether seeking to recover damages from injuries due to a devastating accident, a negligently manufactured product, or abuse at the hands of a caregiver, the Conner Law Group and Mike Conner, Esq. want to help you achieve your best legal outcomes.&#160; Contact us online or call 912-644-5743 in Savannah or 912-427-9870 in Jesup for more information.</p>The Conner Law Group<br />7 East Congress Street<br />Suite 702(B)<br />Savannah, Georgia 31402<!--more--><p>At the&#160;Savannah, <a title="Georgia Personal Injury Law Firm" href="http://www.mikeconner.com/attorneys/david-conner/">Georgia personal injury law firm</a>, David Michael Conner&#160;of The Conner Law Group, P.C.&#160;aid families and individuals who become victims of a negligent act that results in personal injury or worse, death.</p>'
