aS'<p class="MsoNormal">\r\nA caring and compassionate <a href="http://www.estey-bomberger.com/practice-areas/wrongful-death/">California wrongful death lawyer</a> can help families of fatal accident victims or victims of criminal acts make sense of the legal and financial aspects of a loss. Having to deal with the unexpected death of a parent, spouse, child, grandparent or domestic partner can be emotionally traumatizing and physically taxing. During such difficult times, turn to a law firm who understands the pain and grief that follows a loss and is sensitive to the legal and emotional needs of grieving clients. </p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Courtroom Experience Counts</b></p>If you have suffered the loss of a loved one because of another person or entity&#8217;s negligent actions, seek the counsel of a skilled California wrongful death lawyer. When selecting a personal injury lawyer, look for a lawyer who has experience inside and outside the courtroom handling complex wrongful death cases. Many personal injury lawyers do not have trial experience and will often settle without going to trial, which can result in a low settlement. California wrongful death lawyers who have established themselves as aggressive trial lawyers have an advantage when negotiating with insurance companies and defense counsels. Trial experience can produce much higher settlement outcomes.<p /><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Types of California Wrongful Death Claim Damages</b></p>There is no amount of money that can replace the life you have lost. The primary goal in recovering monetary compensation is to make sure you and your family is taken care of in the absence of your loved one. Compensation recovery can ensure funeral and burial expenses are reimbursed, final medical bills are paid and compensation for your loved one&#8217;s lost earnings are provided for. You may also be compensated for non-economic damages, such as loss of companion, loss of love, loss of support, loss of parental guidance (if applicable), and pain and suffering. In cases of extreme gross negligence, the court may award punitive damages. Punitive damages are intended to punish the at-fault party in an effort to prevent further misconduct.<p /><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Speak to a California Wrongful Death Attorney Today</b></p><p class="MsoNormal">If you would like to see justice served on your loved one&#8217;s behalf, do not wait any longer to contact a trusted California wrongful death attorney. You do not want to risk your legal rights and you do want to settle for less than what your case may be worth. Most California personal injury attorneys can tell you what your case may be worth during the initial consultation. Contact an attorney to begin the process of filing a <a href="http://www.estey-bomberger.com/practice-areas/wrongful-death/what-is-a-wrongful-death-claim/">wrongful death claim</a>.&#160;</p><!--more-->Contact an attorney with a record of success in wrongful death cases today. Almost all personal injury attorneys offer free consultations.&#160;'
