aS'As reported by KSBW News, SALINAS, Calif. -- A known Salinas gang member was found guilty Thursday of assault with a deadly weapon on a peace officer. <p />A jury found Raymond Campos, 30, guilty of trying to run over sheriff\'s deputy Jesse Pinon on April 10, 2009, at an apartment complex on Natividad Road. <p />Prosecutors said that Pinon and Salinas police officer Jeff Alford saw Campos conduct drug sales at the apartment complex. When the officers went to arrest Campos, he got into a car, backed up and hit Pinon. <p />Pinon was pulled under the car and had one wheel drive over his collarbone, just missing his head, officials said. <p /><p>Campos, who prosecutors said was a member of the Norteno gang, was also found guilty of possession of methamphetamine for sale.</p><p>If you or a loved on has been accused of assault with a deadly weapon or any crime, You may need a <a title="Salinas Criminal Attorney" href="http://www.biegellawoffice.com/contact/">Salinas Criminal Attorney</a>.&#160; Contact the <a href="http://www.biegellawoffice.com/criminal-law/">Monterey County Criminal Defense Attorneys</a> at The Biegel Law Firm for immediate help.&#160; (877) 223-8982.</p><!--more-->A known Salinas gang member was found guilty Thursday of assault with a deadly weapon on a peace officer.'
