aS'<br /><p>For surviving family members of someone killed in an accident, the many perplexing legal and financial challenges are often overwhelming. Fortunately, wrongful death laws are written to provide justice in Louisiana and other states, and lawyers who work on behalf of survivors are skilled at achieving the best outcomes for those families. </p><p>Wrongful death attorneys in particular are experienced at job-related deaths that often occur in heavy industries: deep-water ports and shipping, agriculture, natural resources, and chemicals (including oil, gas, timber, water, salt, rubber, plastic, concrete, and sulfur). Even the large tourism industry can be the cause of wrongful death, such as when an employee is killed in an airline, hotel, or restaurant accident, or when a breach of security occurs. The <a href="http://www.bls.gov/iag/" target="&#95;blank">U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics</a> tracks fatal accidents on the job by industry . </p><p>Before contacting a wrongful death lawyer, family members should understand the following factors:</p><ul><li><b>Wrongful death definition.</b> This is when negligence or a willful act lead to the injury and death of an individual. It can include failure to train individuals in the proper handling of dangerous materials, failure to provide necessary safety equipment, or failure to provide a safe environment. If inadequate security allowed an intruder to commit a crime, the owner and manager of the property in question may be held liable.</li><li><b>Statute of limitations.</b> Louisiana wrongful death law requires that a personal injury lawsuit (which includes wrongful death) be filed within one year of the incident. Some exceptions are possible, but this clearly shows the need to act quickly.</li><li><b>Compensation.</b> Family members can sue for the loss of present and future wages, expenses related to emergency healthcare, funeral expenses, loss of consortium (for a surviving spouse), and mental anguish.</li></ul><p>The nature of every wrongful death case, however, is that no two incidents are the same. The parties responsible for the death may try to argue that a portion of (or all) fault for the accident lay with the victim, which effectively would limit the size of the settlement. This is why experienced <a href="http://www.markslear.com/aop/louisiana-wrongful-death/">Baton Rouge wrongful death attorneys</a> play an important role in achieving fair and just compensation. </p><p>Marks and Lear PLC<br />301 St. Charles St.<br />Baton Rouge, Louisiana 70802<br />(225) 383-5678</p><!--more-->For surviving family members of someone killed in an accident, the many perplexing legal and financial challenges are often overwhelming. Fortunately, wrongful death laws are written to provide justice.'
