aS'<p>In Clearwater, insurance fraud takes place as often as anywhere else. For example, if you are in a car accident, you might be approached by a fraudulent car accident attorney who is partnered with a cooperating doctor. They may try to use your injuries to pocket insurance money. Choosing recognized and reputable professionals-a respected doctor and professionally recognized lawyer-is an important and effective means of fending off such operations.</p><p>If you were in an auto accident in Clearwater, how would you choose your doctors? How would you select an <a href="http://www.careyandleisure.com/" target="&#95;blank">Clearwater personal injury attorney</a>? Medical professionals might be a function of the hospital where you receive emergency treatment, or are referred by your family physician. But a lawyer should be selected on the basis of experience in that area of law and recognition by peers (attorney awards, such as being named among SuperLawyers or Martindale Hubbell peer review ratings).</p><p><strong>Warning signs to watch out for</strong></p><p>To avoid fraudulent operations, look for these warning signs:</p><ul><li>When either the doctor or lawyer encourages excessive diagnostic and therapeutic expenses, saying that the insurance company will cover everything.</li><li>When the attorney or doctor suggests that you, the patient, can make money by getting extra care.</li><li>When the lawyer gets involved in setting up various diagnostic procedures with multiple healthcare providers (neurologists, orthopedic doctors, chiropractors, and physical therapists).</li><li>When you are steered to a single treatment facility where multiple professionals see you on the same day. </li><li>When several diagnostic tests are recommended with very little explanation or discussion and no sharing of the results after tests are completed.</li><li>When much of the focus is on the spine or a nerve injury where you have no symptoms (for example, when they investigate for soft-tissue injuries or a restriction of joint movement, or overly emphasize a bulging disc, which, for many people, is not necessarily a medical problem).</li><li>When the <a href="http://www.healthcare.gov/law/infocus/providers/index.html" target="&#95;blank">healthcare provider</a> asks for no deductibles or co-payments, or when invoices for medical services are sent to the attorney instead of the patient.</li></ul><p>These are referred to as personal injury mills, intended to line the pockets of lawyers and doctors. But they can also lead to long-term problems for the patient. If the scam is uncovered, the patient might be found equally guilty of fraud, which would affect his or her future prospects for getting hired, getting insurance, or being able to collect on legitimate claims.</p><p><strong>Safeguarding your rights and interests in Clearwater, Florida</strong><br />If you or a loved one has been injured by the negligent act of a person, company, or dog, do not delay in contacting <a href="http://www.careyandleisure.com/tampa-accident-injuries/" target="&#95;blank">Tampa accident attorney</a> in Florida, either online or by phone: 727-799-3900.&#160; We set up a free initial consultation to discuss your case.&#160; If we are able to take your case, we work on a contingent fee basis&#8212;we only get paid for our services if you win a monetary award.<br /><br />Carey &amp; Leisure<br />622 Bypass Drive Suite 100<br />Clearwater, FL 33764-5002<br />(727) 799-3900</p><!--more-->If you were in an auto accident in Clearwater, how would you choose your doctors? How would you select an Clearwater personal injury attorney? Medical professionals might be a function of the hospital where you receive emergency treatment, or are referred by your family physician.'
