aS'<p class="MsoNormal">\r\nInthe days following your Elk Grove car accident, an insurance company adjuster may approach you with a settlement offer. No matter how friendly the insurance adjuster may seem, beware of any initial settlement offers. In an effort to close the claim quickly and cheaply, insurance companies often pressure car accident victims into accepting a low settlement. Most initial insurance company settlement offers are below the true value of damages. Some victims may not realize their claim is worth far more than what the insurance company is offering them. Once a settlement offer has been accepted, victims will be denied the opportunity to pursue legal action in the future. </p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">If you are being pressured into accepting a settlement by an insurance adjuster, do not hesitate to speak to a reputable <a href="http://www.elkgrovecaraccidents.com/">Elk Grove car accident lawyer</a>. Based on the circumstances surrounding your case, a skilled lawyer will be able to determine the true value of damages and whether or not an insurance company&#8217;s initial settlements offer is acceptable.</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b>Types of Elk Grove Car Accident Damages</b></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Compensatory and punitive damages are comprised of economic and non-economic losses a victim has suffered as a result of another person&#8217;s negligent or reckless actions. The most common types of damages awarded in a personal injury or wrongful death claim, compensatory damages may include lost wages, hospital bills, medical care expenses, emotional distress, deceased&#8217;s anticipated earnings, loss of companionship, disfigurement, loss of quality of life, loss of parental guidance (if applicable), loss of love and physical pain. In cases where a defendant&#8217;s actions were particularly offensive, a judge may award punitive damages. The intention of punitive damages is to punish the defendant and discourage other wrongdoers from engaging in similar conduct.</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b>Choose an Experienced Trial Attorney</b></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Many personal injury attorneys lack trial experience and therefore, will not present a client&#8217;s case to a judge and jury. Refusing to take a case to court can jeopardize a victim&#8217;s settlement outcome. Many victims are forced to settle for less than what they need and deserve. When choosing an attorney, look for an Elk Grove car accident attorney who will not hesitate to take your case to court if settlement negotiations are stalled.</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b>Contact an Elk Grove Car Accident Attorney Immediately</b></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Waiting to contact an Elk Grove car accident attorney could prevent you from securing a fair and just personal injury or wrongful death claim settlement. A competent attorney can ensure you do not miss filing deadlines. If you are concerned about litigation costs, do not let that stop you from contacting an attorney. Most <a href="http://www.esteyandbomberger.com/">northern California personal injury lawyers</a> do not get paid until you do.&#160;</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p /><!--more-->In the days following your Elk Grove car accident, an insurance company\r\nadjuster may approach you with a settlement offer. No matter how friendly the\r\ninsurance adjuster may seem, beware of any initial settlement offers.&#160;'
