aS'<p>With the calendar reading April and the weather finally getting nicer, traffic is picking up on the roads of eastern Long Island. And with the increased traffic on our highways, drivers can expect to find greater surveillance by the police. <p /></p><p>As I drove eastbound yesterday morning (April 1<sup>st</sup>) around 11:00 a.m. from the Southampton Town Justice Court in Hampton Bays to my office in Southampton, I passed a motorist pulled over by a patrol car just after I had crossed the Shinnecock Canal on Sunrise Highway (Route 27).&#160; I had not driven a half-mile more when I came upon another motorist pulled over by a patrol car on County Road 39A.&#160; Seeing two drivers stopped by the police so close to one another was a great reminder that Sunrise Highway and County Road 39A in Southampton are two of the most heavily policed roads on eastern Long Island and that drivers need to be constantly aware of their speed while traveling on these roadways. <p /></p><p>We can help drivers avoid points on their license and increased insurance premiums if a driver receives a speeding&#160;ticket or other traffic ticket in Southampton NY or other area of Suffolk County. Drivers can contact our office and receive a consultation at no charge. Effective legal representation can have dramatic results on the outcome of a traffic law case.&#160;<p /></p><!--more-->Driving on Sunrise Highway and County Road 39A in Southampton NY.'
