aS'It may be difficult to reconcile the idea of pregnancy hormones \r\nhealing brain injuries, but researchers at Duke University believe they \r\nmay have stumbled upon just such a fact in testing for TBI.&#160; The hormone\r\n progesterone, normally associated with pregnancy, is actually produced \r\nby both men and women and has been shown to reduce inflammation in an \r\nacute brain injury if given by IV for five days within eight hours of \r\nthe injury.&#160; The hormone can penetrate the blood-brain barrier, \r\ndecreasing swelling and slowing down brain cell death.\r\n<p>At least two million people suffer <a title="Traumatic Brain Injury" href="http://www.scarlettlawgroup.com/practice-areas/traumatic-brain-injury">traumatic brain injuries</a>\r\n each year.&#160; Currently, there is no definitive treatment or therapy for \r\nacute brain injuries, although many different methods are used to \r\ncontrol swelling and pressure.&#160; Patients in comas are often subjected to\r\n clinical trials to which their families gladly agree simply because \r\nmedical science offers little hope for a cure.</p>\r\n<p>The goal for this trial is to enroll at least 1,100 TBI patients.&#160; More than 150 hospitals in 21 countries are taking part.</p>\r\n<p><b>What Is TBI?</b></p>\r\n<p><a title="traumatic brain injury" href="http://www.scarlettlawgroup.com/videos/traumatic-brain-injury">Traumatic brain injury</a>\r\n occurs when some type of external force causes an injury to the brain.&#160;\r\n Most TBIs result from accidents such as car crashes or contact during \r\nsports, although some result from slip-and-fall and other accidents.&#160; \r\nMild TBIs usually heal themselves, but many seemingly simply brain \r\ninjuries result in long-term complications.&#160; It is also impossible to \r\npredict exactly how a particular type of blow to the head will affect an\r\n individual.</p>\r\n<p>Those who cause accidents that result in a traumatic brain injury may\r\n be held accountable by the victim or his or her family through the \r\nfiling of a personal injury lawsuit.&#160; A lawsuit that involves a TBI may \r\ninclude requests for damages such as payment of medical bills and lost \r\nwages.&#160; However, a serious TBI may also result in long-term disability, \r\nthe inability to hold a job, and suffering on the part of the family.</p>\r\n<p>An attorney who handles TBI cases often looks at the totality of loss\r\n in order to help the victim determine how much compensation to seek.&#160; \r\nBecause traumatic brain injury cases are so complicated, a personal <a title="San Francisco Injury Lawyer" href="http://www.scarlettlawgroup.com/contact">injury attorney</a> may be able to help the victim or the <a title="family members" href="http://www.scarlettlawgroup.com/practice-areas/traumatic-brain-injury/families-care-givers">family members</a> sort out the confusing aspects of the case and focus on physical and mental recovery.</p>'
