aS'<p class="MsoNormal">\r\nAccording to the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration, impaired driving is often a symptom of a much larger problem &#8211; alcohol abuse. Alcohol abuse can come in many forms. Some people drink excessively regularly (all day, every day), some people drink excessively on one occasion (binge drinking) and some individuals drink excessively over an extended period of time (&#8220;benders&#8221;). Binge drinking (consuming approximately four or more drinks in a two hour period of time) has become one of the most common forms of alcohol abuse in America. Although binge drinking is commonly associated with the younger generation, the Center for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) reports that 70 percent of binge drinking episodes involve adults age 26 or older. The CDC also reports that binge drinkers are 14 percent more likely to report alcohol-impaired driving than people who don&#8217;t binge drink. </p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Bakersfield DUI Accident Statistics</b></p><p class="MsoNormal">Alcohol-related car accidents tragically kill thousands of Americans every year. In California, more than 1,145 people were tragically killed in alcohol-related car crashes in 2009, reports the California Highway Patrol (CHP). In Bakersfield, 12 people were killed and 163 were injured in alcohol-related car accidents in 2009. Keep in mind; an alcohol-related car crash is defined as an accident in which one driver involved had a blood alcohol concentration level of .01 or higher. The legal limit in California is .08.</p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Seeking Justice in the Civil Court System</b></p><p class="MsoNormal">Can a DUI accident victim obtain justice for an accident-related injury or death? Victims who were injured or who lost a loved one in a drunk driving accident caused by the negligent actions of another person may be able to seek justice in the civil court system. Before a victim speaks to an insurance agent, it is imperative he or she talks to a skilled <a href="http://bakersfield-injury-lawyers.com/drunk-driving-accident.html">Bakersfield DUI accident victim attorney</a>. A reputable attorney can give a victim or a victims&#8217; family a clear plan for obtaining justice.</p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Obtaining Financial Compensation</b></p><p class="MsoNormal">The severe physical and emotional consequences associated with a Bakersfield drunk driving accident can never be undone no matter what form of justice a victim obtains, however, by taking legal action, a victim can ensure that those responsible for a tragic crash are held accountable. Filing a claim will also allow a victim to get help for the severe financial burdens associated with a DUI accident injury or loss. In a personal injury or wrongful death claim, financial compensation may be obtained for medical bills, lost earnings, shortened life expectancy, funeral costs, loss of care, loss of support, disability, and pain and suffering.</p><p class="MsoNormal">Please contact a knowledgeable <a href="http://bakersfield-injury-lawyers.com/car-accident.html">Bakersfield car accident lawyer</a> now to learn what types of damages you may be awarded in a DUI accident lawsuit. If you wait to contact a lawyer, you may be denied a claim filing.&#160;</p>'
