aS'<p>Last week&#160; there was speculation that the Huntington Beach Police Department would post the faces of all persons arrested for DUI in Huntington Beach on the cities facebook site.&#160; obviously, this created a huge stir and some controversey among those in the legal community and&#160;one <a href="http://www.lawyerinlongbeach.com/Huntington-Beach-DUI-Attorney.html">Huntington Beach DUI Attorney</a> , &quot;What a bold move&quot; said many police officers in surrounding communities.&#160; The announcement, it is believed, &#160;was intended to deter those who may have been tempted to drink and drive in the city of Huntington Beach.</p><p>In the end the city capitulated, many believe due to the threats of lawsuits for invasion of privacy and possible defamation.&#160; According to one <a href="http://www.lawyerinlongbeach.com/">Long Beach DUI Attorney</a> it would have been the first in the state to enact such drastic practices in an effort to stem the tide of DUI arrests.</p><p>The bottom line is that drunk driving is a serious and dangerous act and some think drastic measures must be taken to slow down the Huntington Beach DUI caseload that has burgeoned over the last ten years to become the highest in the state of california.&#160; Whether or not such practices would curtail the conduct of those caught for drunk driving remains to be tested.</p><p>Although it was originally reported that the Police department was contemplating the action, according to a high ranking official within the Huntington Beach Police Dept., &#160;turns out there was never an announcement by the Huntington Beach Police Department that all DUI drivers faces would be posted on Facebook.&#160; In fact, it was never considered.<br /><br />The suggestion to do so was by one city councilmember and that idea was rejected by the rest of the city council.&#160;&#160;&#160; The entire discussion is available to watch off the City of Huntington Beach website under City Council Agenda for January 18, 2011 - &quot;video&quot;<br /></p><!--more--><p>Last week&#160; there was speculation that the Huntington Beach Police Department would post the faces of all persons arrested for DUI in Huntington Beach on the cities facebook site.&#160; obviously, this created a huge stir and some controversey among those in the legal community and&#160;one <a href="http://www.lawyerinlongbeach.com/Huntington-Beach-DUI-Attorney.html">Huntington Beach DUI Attorney</a> , &quot;What a bold move&quot; said many police officers in surrounding communities.&#160'
