aS'Being in a car accident can be a truly devastating experience,  regardless of how serious your crash may have been.\r\n<p>And when it comes to  accident injuries, among the most common are related to the neck and  back. After all, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whiplash&#95;%28medicine%29" target="&#95;blank">whiplash</a>\r\n is a condition that many accident victims  suffer and is typically \r\ncaused upon striking another vehicle or  stationary object at any speed;\r\n this collision causes the vehicle to  stop abruptly, forcing the driver\r\n and other passengers to lunge forward  due to the velocity. For those \r\nwho are wearing seat belts, and back and  neck can be seriously injured.\r\n Of course, whiplash from a seat belt is  better than the alternative, \r\nbut it can still be quite painful.</p>\r\n<p>So if you have suffered a <a href="http://www.getmejustice.com/">neck injury following a car crash</a>,\r\n regardless  of whether the symptoms of the whiplash surfaced hours or \r\neven days  after the accident, the fact remains that you should seek \r\nmedical  attention immediately. After all, the pain can get worse over \r\ntime and,  if untreated, you may have an underlying injury that could \r\nseriously  impede your everyday life. Of course, seeking medical \r\nattention for such  injuries can be expensive, especially with the high \r\ncost of hospital  visits these days. This is especially true if you do \r\nnot have adequate  insurance coverage.</p>\r\n<p>In these situations, the best thing that you can do is to file an  \r\ninsurance claim. This way, you can reach a settlement with your  \r\ninsurance company to cover the costs of your medical bills, vehicle  \r\ndamage, and other related expenses from your crash. Of course, you  \r\nshould not expect to receive a fair settlement on your first attempt at \r\n filing a claim, as many insurance companies these days will shell out \r\nas  little money as possible. Instead, you should take the matter to \r\ncourt  if your original settlement is unfair and your insurance company \r\nis  unwilling to work with you.</p>\r\n<p>When going to court, you should also take the time to hire a neck \r\ninjury  attorney. This way, you will have a professional on your side \r\nwho has  experience with cases like yours and will give you the best \r\nchance for  success.</p>\r\n<p>The <a href="http://www.getmejustice.com/injury-lawyers">Personal injury attorneys</a>\r\n of Shapiro Goldman Babboni &amp; Walsh have represented people who have\r\n  been injured by another\'s negligence and those who\'s insurance \r\ncompanies  are attempting to get out of providing fair compensation for \r\nserious  injuries. Our Lawyers have helped those who have suffered a \r\nvariety of  injuries including neck and spine injury, back injuries, \r\nbrain and head  injuries and all forms of auto accident related \r\ninjuries. Office  locations around southwest Florida include Sarasota, \r\nBradenton, St.  Petersburg, Venice, Port Charlotte, Lakeland, Ft. Myers,\r\n Arcadia and  Punta Gorda.</p><!--more-->Being in a car accident can be a truly devastating experience,  regardless of how serious your crash may have been.\r\n\r\n\r\nAnd when it comes to  accident injuries, among the most common are related to the neck and  back'
