aS'<br /><p><strong>Auto accidents</strong><br />Not all accidents result from driver negligence. In fact, a number of accidents occur because of defective automobiles or defective automobile parts. The government has recalled millions of vehicles because of design flaws that put people at risk.</p><p><strong>Recalls in 2012</strong><br /><a href="http://www.washingtoncaraccidentsandinjuries.com/auto-accidents/" target="&#95;blank">Tacoma auto accident lawyers</a> can pursue a lawsuit to recover damages on behalf of motorists and passengers who suffer serious injuries because their vehicle or vehicle parts were subject to recall. Manufacturers are strictly liable if their products are unreasonably dangerous.&#160;&#160; </p><p>To give an idea of the extent of recalls that can occur,&#160;<a href="http://www.nbcnews.com/business/toyota-hold-worlds-biggest-car-recall-16-years-1C6374378" target="&#95;blank">NBC News</a> reported that Toyota recalled 2.5 million vehicles sold in the United States in 2012 because of fire risk. The cars subject to recall were Toyota and Scion brands, with a total worldwide recall of 7.43 million. This is the largest recall since Ford Motor Company recalled 7.9 million vehicles in 1996. Stuck accelerators also caused recalls for Toyota in recent years. NBC stated that Toyota had more recalls than any other auto manufacturer in the United States in 2010 and nearly claimed the same ranking for 2011. It appears Toyota will rank top again for recalls in 2012. However, 2011 was Honda&#8217;s year for the most recalls. Honda rose to the top of the 2011 list when it recalled 1.7 million vehicles. However, Toyota and Honda do not stand alone when it comes to recalls. Chevrolet and Ferrari also had recalls, just not as extensively as the other manufacturers. </p><p><strong>Protecting your rights</strong><br /><a href="http://www.washingtoncaraccidentsandinjuries.com/" target="&#95;blank">Mark A. Hammer &amp; Associates</a> has fought for clients and protected their rights in auto accident cases for the past three decades. We handle cases throughout<br />Puget Sound and Western Washington. Our firm has the wherewithal to investigate cases, discover the underlying causes of accidents and hold manufacturers accountable when unsafe vehicles lead to accidents. Find out how we can help.</p><p><strong>Mark A. Hammer &amp; Associates</strong><br />748 Market St.<br />Suite 300<br />Tacoma, WA 98402</p><!--more-->Not all accidents result from driver negligence. In fact, a number of accidents occur because of defective automobiles or defective automobile parts. The government has recalled millions of vehicles because of design flaws that put people at risk. Toyota and Honda ranked highest for recalls since 2010, and Toyota appears to top the list again in 2012. Experienced auto accident lawyers can help you hold manufacturers accountable and recover compensation for injuries.'
