aS'<p>Torrance, California, is located in densely populated Southern California, an area notorious for traffic with its share of accidents.  Rear-end collisions are common, resulting in many injuries including &#8220;whiplash&#8221;.  Whiplash results when the head and neck are whipped harshly forward and backward.  The resulting extreme motion can cause strains and tears in the ligaments and muscles of the neck, as well as stretching and strain to the spinal cord.  </p><p>Of course, spinal cord health is vital to the body it is the highway along which communication travels between the brain and the body.  And your <a href="http://www.ehlinelaw.com/" title="personal injury attorney">personal injury attorney</a> knows that musculoskeletal injuries are no less traumatic and can be quite painful and difficult to resolve.\r\nThe most important factor to healing whiplash is immediate treatment.  Evaluating the severity of whiplash and beginning treatment within mere hours of the accident is necessary in putting a halt to inflammation and other processes that will further damage the neck and spine area.  </p><p>Unfortunately, most people falsely believe that an ambulance staff is equipped to make decisions about spine and neck health; they are not.  Even some emergency rooms may be understaffed.  Proper evaluation and treatment really should begin as soon as possible with permanent staff or a specialist.  Unfortunately, most people believe that the seemingly minor aches and pains they feel after an accident indicate only minor injuries. </p><p> Just as the ambulance staff is intended to transport patients to a true medical facility, the victim should not try to guess what type of injuries he or she has rather than let a doctor decide.  This type of mistake can have life-long consequences as whiplash that is untreated or left too long can result in a long-term set of symptoms classified as &#8220;whiplash associated disorder&#8221;. </p><p> These symptoms can include depression, limited range of motion, and even effects on workplace and home life.  Add that to the usual symptoms of whiplash which can include headaches, dizziness, shoulder and arm pain, and insomnia.  Even waiting for insurance to make medical arrangements can be a waste of precious time that would best be spent evaluating and treating.\r\n</p><p>If you or your loved one is the victim of an automobile collision due to the negligence of another driver, it is important that you call an attorney convenient to your Torrance location immediately after the accident.  The sooner you call, the more quickly your qualified <a href="http://www.ehlinelaw.com/pages/4193/torrance-accident-injury-lawyer.htm">Torrance personal injury attorney</a> can facilitate medical treatment and begin the recompense process. Call Ehline Law Firm PC and learn more 21250 Hawthorne Blvd., Suite 500 Torrance, CA 90503<br />USA Phone: +1.424.233.0709.</p><!--more-->The most important factor to healing whiplash is immediate treatment.  \r\nEvaluating the severity of whiplash and beginning treatment within mere \r\nhours of the accident is necessary in putting a halt to inflammation and\r\n other processes that will further damage the neck and spine area.'
