aS'Parking structure accidents can be deadly; these are accidents that happen every year and is proven in the people that have been injured or killed, with the most recent being a 76 year old woman in West Los Angeles that was fatally injured when her Volkswagen SUV plunged from the fourth story of a parking structure April 26, 2011. \r\n<ul><li>October 8, 2010 an 83 year old man who crashed through a concrete barrier on the parking garage of his condominium building and amazingly survived the vehicles plunge to the pavement below. The man according to emergency personnel had head trauma and possible back injuries.</li>\r\n<li>April 16, 2010 in Huston Texas a 62 year old man was killed when the Toyota Sienna he was driving plunged from the upper floor of a parking garage.  He was pronounced dead after paramedics attempted chest compressions from the 20 foot fall from the second floor of the parking structure. The man according to reports was trying to park when his minivan went through the safety cables. </li>\r\n<li>January 23, 2011 a vehicle plunged from the fourth floor of the Golden Nugget parking structure in Las Vegas killing two people. Police believe the elderly man that was driving hit the gas instead of the break crashing through the concrete slab that killed him and his wife. The building inspector stated that the safety panel had blown out where it is embedded into the concrete and the concrete bolts and slabs are only meant to withstand approximately 6,000 pounds. </li>\r\n<li>Another of these tragic accidents was when a 15 year old Milwaukee teen was killed. This accident did not involve a vehicle the teen, a friend and his mother were walking near the building when a 30 foot wide piece of concrete facade fell from the parking structure. The other teen and his mother were seriously injured. </li></ul>\r\nThese are just some of the parking structure accidents that caused serious injuries or death and while partially the drivers fault in some cases the fact that the concrete slabs and bolts can only withhold approximately 6,000 pounds of pressure, the driver that accidently hits the gas instead of the breaks is going to be seriously injured or killed. \r\nAfter a parking garage accident in Los Angeles the injured victim or the family of a victim that was killed should speak with a parking structure injury attorney. These types of accidents the death or injuries can be cause by lack of proper maintenance or even manufacturing. \r\n<strong><p><strong xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"></strong>About the Author</p></strong>Michael Ehline of Ehline Law Firm PC, is a highly experienced personal injury lawyer and nationally recognized <a href="http://www.ehlinelaw.com/pages/100091/parking-structure-personal-injury-lawyers.htm">parking structure injury attorney</a>.  If you were injured and suffered a wrongful death, car accident brain injury, or motorcycle accident friction burn injury, contact him at 633 West Fifth Street, 28th Floor, Los Angeles, CA 90071; 213.596.9642; 50 Francisco Street #460, San Francisco, CA 94133 (415) 684-7688.<!--more-->After a parking garage accident in Los Angeles the injured victim or the\r\n family of a victim that was killed should speak with a parking \r\nstructure injury attorney.'
