aS'<p>Our <a href="http://www.merandalawfirm.com/" target="&#95;blank">Columbus drunk driving lawyers</a> at The Meranda Law Firm provide legal advice and representation primarily in the areas of DUI, traffic violations, criminal defense, family law, and personal injury. Much of our practice involves defending clients in DUI cases.</p><p>A <a href="http://www.merandalawfirm.com/Firm%20Info/Firm%20Profile.aspx" target="&#95;blank">Columbus DUI law firm</a> defending against drunk driving offenses must have a great deal of chemical testing technical and procedural understanding to effectively defend a DUI case. Faulty chemical tests are commonplace. Taking a blood test at the time of the incident can often help to discredit a wrongly administered chemical test. Testing officers, who fail to observe the alleged DUI for belching, smoking, vomiting, or eating within a certain time before administering the test, end up with erroneous test results. Testing equipment must be calibrated and operated by a tester who follows correct procedure. A Columbus attorney experienced in drunk driving can bring various challenges against chemical testing as part of a DUI defense.</p><p>Other areas that skilled Columbus attorneys investigate include the DUI stop&#8212;to discover whether probable cause existed, and field sobriety tests, that can often be challenged. Depending on the circumstances of the case, negotiating a plea or arguing for reduced charges may be other options to consider.</p><p>This article was provided by:<br />The Meranda Law firm<br /><a href="http://www.merandalawfirm.com/Firm%20Info/Practice%20Areas.aspx" target="&#95;blank">Columbus drunk driving defense</a><br />http://www.merandalawfirm.com/</p><!--more-->Our <a href="http://www.merandalawfirm.com/" target="&#95;blank">Columbus drunk driving lawyers</a> at The Meranda Law Firm provide legal advice and representation primarily in the areas of DUI, traffic violations, criminal defense, family law, and personal injury. A <a href="http://www.merandalawfirm.com/Firm%20Info/Firm%20Profile.aspx" target="&#95;blank">Columbus DUI law firm</a> defending against drunk driving offenses must have a great deal of chemical testing completed to prove their case.'
