aS'\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">When\r\nanything in a family structure changes, it can impact a child of any age. Any\r\nfamily that experiences change outside of the traditional, two-parent\r\nbiological family has been studied to present potential risk to children. </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Remarriage\r\npresents a very dramatic change in a child&#8217;s life. They are suddenly a part of\r\nwhat may feel like two completely separate families, along with having a new &#8220;parent&#8221;\r\nin their life that is around them a lot of the time, in most cases. </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">These\r\nnew changes can cause a child to feel confused and frightened, and may often\r\nfeel uncomfortable asking questions about what is happening now that there are\r\nthese new people and new routines in their daily life. </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Many\r\nchanges can come with divorce and remarriage for a child, including moving to a\r\ndifferent home, changing schools, losing contact with some of their family members,\r\nsharing a room with new siblings, and adjusting to the new rules and\r\nenvironment of a new family structure. </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">As a\r\nresult of these changes, the child may feel unloved or unwanted, especially if\r\nthere are stepsiblings in the picture. They have lost some of their family\r\nroutines and traditions, and they may experience extreme feelings of loss and\r\nwanting things to be back the way they were before. They risk feeling like a\r\nstranger in their own home since so many things have suddenly changed.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThese feelings can increase into emotional and internal issues that are much\r\nworse if not address when they first begin. If the child is being neglected and\r\nthe parents are not effectively communicating these changes and how the child\r\nfeels about them, there are many things that could result from these emotions,\r\nincluding a loss of self-esteem, anxiety, poor performance at school, continual\r\nfeelings of confusion, displaced anger, and more. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nDivorce isn&#8217;t easy for anyone, especially the children involved. Child custody can\r\nalso be a great issue that arises, especially when one of the parents gets\r\nremarried. Meet with a Tucson divorce lawyer today to discuss how your legal\r\nrights to your children can be protected after a divorce.</p>\r\n\r\n'
