aS'<p class="MsoBodyText">Clients often ask how the Social Security Administration\r\ndecides if he or she is disabled.&#160; The\r\nreality is that this process can be very subjective, and depends on who reviews\r\nyour application.&#160; However, determining\r\nwhether a person is disabled is based on a five-step process:</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst">1.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Are\r\nyou currently working?</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle">2.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Is\r\nyour condition severe?</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle">3.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Is\r\nyour condition found on Social Security&#8217;s list of disabling conditions?</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle">4.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Can\r\nyou do the work you previously did?</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast">5.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Could\r\nyou do another type of work?</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">You can visit <a href="http://www.ssa.gov/dibplan/dqualify5.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.ssa.gov/dibplan/dqualify5.htm</a>\r\nfor additional information regarding social security disability\r\ndetermination. You may also visit <a href="http://www.socialsecuritydisabilityarkansas.com/" rel="nofollow">http://www.socialsecuritydisabilityarkansas.com/</a> for additional information about frequently asked questions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">For the Social Security Administration to properly\r\nassess your claim based on this five-step process, you need to make sure you\r\nfill out the paperwork properly and have adequate medical documentation.&#160; If you have any questions regarding your\r\nSocial Security Disability claim, contact the <a href="http://www.kieklaklawfirm.com/" rel="nofollow">Kieklak Law Firm</a> for help.&#160; </p><!--more-->The 5 Step Process of How the Social Security Administration Determines if You are Disabled'
