aS'<p class="MsoNormal">\r\nOne of the most destructive types of truck crashes is a runaway trailer accident. Runaway trailer accidents occur when a truck&#8217;s trailer becomes disconnected from the cab. A large trailer can weigh anywhere from 10,000 pounds empty to more than 30,000 pounds fully loaded with cargo. An unmanned trailer barreling down the road or highway can destroy anything in its path, including passenger vehicles, motorcyclists and bicyclists. Occupants of a passenger vehicle, a motorcycle\r\nrider or a cyclist can suffer catastrophic injuries in a runaway trailer accident. </p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Runaway Trailer Catastrophic Injuries</b></p><p class="MsoNormal">If a victim survives a potentially life-threatening catastrophic injury, the victim may never be able to return to their previous way of life. Catastrophic injury survivors often rely on caregivers to help them perform daily tasks, such as eating, dressing and bathing. Some catastrophic injury survivors suffer from severe secondary injuries, which require constant medical care. Other catastrophic injury victims suffer permanent neurological damage, organ dysfunction or paralysis. Examples of catastrophic injuries include:</p><p class="MsoNormal" /><ul><li>Spinal cord injuries &#8211; can result in incomplete or complete paralysis</li><li>Head injuries &#8211; may result in mild, moderate or severe brain damage</li><li>Burn injures &#8211; can result in first, second or third degrees burns</li><li>Bone fracture injuries &#8211; may result in permanent disfigurement&#160;</li><li>Internal organ injuries &#8211; can result in permanent organ dysfunction</li><li>Amputation injuries &#8211; may result in partial or complete loss of limb.</li></ul><p /><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Fighting for Your Future</b></p><p class="MsoNormal">Suffering a catastrophic injury in a truck collision often places enormous physical, emotional and financial stress on a victim. With the help of an understanding <a href="http://www.truck-accident-injury-attorneys.com/">California truck accident injury attorney</a>, victims can recover the highest amount of compensation possible. An established personal injury attorney will use every available resource to make sure victims&#8217; past, current and future needs are met. Helping clients achieve maximum compensation for medical expenses, care giving costs, lost income, diminished quality of life, physical pain and psychological distress should be your attorney&#8217;s priority.</p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Holding Negligent Parties Accountable</b></p><p class="MsoNormal">In addition to recovering monetary compensation, a <a href="http://www.truck-accident-injury-attorneys.com/types-of-truck-accidents/runaway-trailer-accidents/">California runaway trailer accident lawyer</a> can see that the parties responsible for the accident are held accountable. In commercial truck crashes, a truck driver, trucking company or auto part manufacturer may be liable for injury expenses. Let a skilled California personal injury lawyer explore all possible sources of compensation. Even if it means taking your case to court (if negotiations are stalled), an experienced lawyer should not hesitate to pursue compensation from all responsible parties.</p><!--more-->One of the most destructive types of truck crashes is a runaway trailer accident.\r\nRunaway trailer accidents occur when a truck&#8217;s trailer becomes disconnected\r\nfrom the cab. A large trailer can weigh anywhere from 10,000 pounds empty to\r\nmore than 30,000 pounds fully loaded with cargo.&#160;'
