aS'<p><br />There are four main offenses for driving under the influence (DUI) in California. However, aggravating circumstances &#8212; blood alcohol content (BAC) over.15, BAC test refusal, causing an accident, speeding, or having a child age 14 or younger in the car &#8212; can enhance sentencing.&#160; </p><p>Sentencing guidelines for DUI are:</p><strong>First Offense</strong><p class="Style1">*&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Fines: $390 to $1000</p><p class="Style1">*&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Jail: with probation, 48 hours to six months (with no probation, 96 hours to six months) </p><p class="Style1">*&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Program: three months or longer</p><p class="Style1">*&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; BAC refusal program:&#160; nine months or longer</p><p class="Style1">*&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; License suspension six months to 10 months</p><strong>Second Offense</strong><p class="Style1">*&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Fines: $390 to $1000</p><p class="Style1">*&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Jail: with or without probation, 96 hours to one year</p><p class="Style1">*&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Additional 96 hours for BAC refusal</p><p class="Style1">*&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Program: 18 or 30 months or longer</p><p class="Style1">*&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; License suspension two years from conviction date</p><p class="Style1">*&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Option of Ignition Interlock Device (IID)</p><strong>Third Offense</strong><p class="Style1">*&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Fines: $390 to $1000</p><p class="Style1">*&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Jail: with or without probation 120 days to one year</p><p class="Style1">*&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Additional 10 days in jail for BAC refusal</p><p class="Style1">*&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Program: 18 or 30 months or longer</p><p class="Style1">*&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; License revocation three years </p><p class="Style1">*&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Ignition Interlock Device (IID) </p><strong>Fourth Offense</strong><p class="Style1">*&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Fines: $390 to $1000</p><p class="Style1">*&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Jail: with or without probation, 180 days to one year or felony state prison</p><p class="Style1">*&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Additional 18 days imprisonment for BAC refusal</p><p class="Style1">*&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Program: 18 or 30 months or longer</p><p class="Style1">*&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; License revocation four years </p><p class="Style1">*&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Ignition Interlock Device (IID)</p><p>Under (Vehicle Code) <a href="http://www.dmv.ca.gov/pubs/vctop/d11/vc23103&#95;5.htm">VC 23103 pursuant to VC 23103.5</a>, a <a href="http://www.flthompson.com/practice-areas/dui-drunk-driving/" target="&#95;blank">Bakersfield DUI attorney</a> can plea bargain for a <i>wet reckless</i> charge, which reduces potential penalties.&#160; The defendant must plead <i>guilty </i>or <i>nolo contendere </i>(no contest) to consuming alcohol or taking drugs.&#160; Pleading wet reckless may still result in the Department of Motor Vehicles (DMV) license suspension and it counts as a prior.&#160; However, other benefits generally outweigh DUI conviction consequences.&#160; For example, a subsequent DUI arrest does not impose increased jail time (as above) because the maximum jail time for each wet reckless offense is 90 days.&#160; Probation periods are shorter.&#160; Fines are generally less, and there is no automatic license suspension penalty resulting from the criminal charge.&#160; </p><em><strong>Put a strong advocate on your side</strong></em><p>The Bakersfield, CA law office of Thompson Law can help protect your rights if charged with DUI.&#160; Our attorneys fight to achieve the best outcome possible. <a href="http://www.flthompson.com/contact-us/">Contact Thompson Law</a> for a free consultation.</p>'
