aS'<p class="MsoNormal">\r\nBoating is an activity enjoyed year round on the Sacramento Delta, which is an endless network of rivers traveling between Sacramento and San Francisco. For many boaters, a day planned water skiing, wakeboarding or fishing on one of Sacramento&#8217;s waterways can quickly end tragically. In 2009, boating accidents were responsible for the deaths of 736 Americans. Also in the same year,\r\nthousands of boaters suffered various types of preventable injuries in boating crashes nationwide. What causes a boating accident to occur? According to the United States Coast Guard, the top ten causes of U.S. boating accidents are:</p><p class="MsoNormal"><i>Operator inattention</i></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Boat operators distracted by other passengers, navigation systems, cell phones or stereos are the number one cause of boating collisions in the United States. </p><p class="MsoNormal"><i>Operator inexperience</i></p><p class="MsoNormal">Unfamiliarity with how to steer, stop or turn a boat in the ever-changing element of water can cause an operator to lose control of a vessel and crash. </p><p class="MsoNormal"><i>Excessive speeding</i></p><p class="MsoNormal">A boat operator can easily lose control of a vessel when excessively speeding, causing the vessel to flip or collide with another boat. Passengers can also be thrown from a vessel that is going too fast. </p><p class="MsoNormal"><i>Improper lookout</i></p><p class="MsoNormal">Operators who fail to keep their eyes &#8220;on the road&#8221; and keep a lookout for other vessels caused more than 330 boating accidents in 2009. </p><p class="MsoNormal"><i>Alcohol</i></p><p class="MsoNormal">The consumption of alcohol or drugs can affect an operator&#8217;s ability to think clearly, react quickly and stay focused. </p><p class="MsoNormal"><i>Machinery failure</i></p><p class="MsoNormal">An electrical system failure, faulty battery charger, fuel pump crack, rudder defect, steering arm malfunction or throttle defect can cause a Sacramento boating crash.</p><p class="MsoNormal"><i>Weather</i></p><p class="MsoNormal">Weather conditions, such as rain, fog or strong winds, contributed to more than 260 U.S. vessel accidents in 2009.&#160; </p><p class="MsoNormal"><i>Hazardous waters</i></p><p class="MsoNormal">Rocky or turbulent waters, oftentimes hidden under the surface of the water, can catch even an experienced boat operator off guard and quickly turn a fun day of recreational boating into a tragic one.</p><p class="MsoNormal"><i>Force of wave/wake</i></p><p class="MsoNormal">Boats traveling across the surface of a body of water produce a wake, which is a disruption in the flow of water. The size of the wake produced depends on the size of the boat. Large boats produce large wake. Small boats can be sunk if caught in the wake of a large boat. If powerful or large enough, waves can also overtake a boat. </p><p class="MsoNormal"><i>Rules of the road</i></p><p class="MsoNormal">Just as drivers must follow the rules of the road while operating a vehicle, operators must follow boating regulations and laws when operating a vessel. Boat\r\noperators who fail to obey laws and regulations can cause a devastating boat crash. </p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>When to Contact a Sacramento Boating Accident Lawyer</b></p><p class="MsoNormal">If you or a loved one has been seriously injured in an accident involving a vessel, the sooner you contact a skilled <a href="http://www.sacramento-personalinjurylawyers.com/boating-accident.html">Sacramento boating accident lawyer</a> the better your chances are of recovering maximum compensation. You may be entitled to compensation for health care costs, lost earnings, permanent scars, and pain and suffering. A <a href="http://www.sacramento-personalinjurylawyers.com/">Sacramento personal injury lawyer </a>with expertise in boating accidents cases can make sure you receive the compensation you need to move forward.</p><!--more-->Boating is an activity enjoyed year round on the Sacramento Delta, which\r\nis an endless network of rivers traveling between Sacramento and San Francisco.\r\nFor many boaters, a day planned water skiing, wakeboarding or fishing on one of\r\nSacramento&#8217;s waterways can quickly end tragically.&#160;'
