aS'<p>Anyone injured in a New Jersey car accident caused by the negligence of one or more other parties has the right to pursue compensation for all expenses related to injuries and other losses. However, identifying all negligent parties can be more complicated than you might expect. <a href="http://www.corradinoandpapa.com/practice-areas/nj-car-accident-lawyers/" target="&#95;blank">NJ car accident lawyers</a> often need to conduct detailed investigations to uncover everyone who shares responsibility for an accident.</p><p><strong>The driver may be just one of multiple liable parties</strong></p><p>Even a rear-end collision can be more complicated than it appears on the surface. Without a thorough investigation, victims may not realize how many parties may have played a role, such as the following:</p><ul><li>The manufacturer of faulty brakes that failed when the driver attempted to stop behind the car he or she hit</li><li>The repair shop that performed a poor repair job on the car that hit the other vehicle</li><li>The company that failed to properly repair a pot hole that caused a driver to lose control</li><li>The municipality that failed to provide warning signs of a known road hazard that caused the collision</li></ul><p>A good summary of personal injury law at <a href="http://research.lawyers.com/New-Jersey/Personal-Injury-in-New-Jersey.html" target="&#95;blank">Lawyers.com</a>&#160; describes some of the complexities of liability issues. Even with the contributory factors cited above, the driver who collided with your car may still share liability by neglecting to follow driving procedures that could have prevented or reduced the severity of the collision. The victim can share liability as well&#8212;and may not be able to collect damages if he or she is determined to be more at fault than are other parties.</p><p>These are all reasons why it is vital to avoid admitting fault or discussing an accident until you talk to an attorney with experience handling car accident claims.</p><p><strong>Experienced NJ car accident lawyers can make a difference to your case</strong></p><p>With almost six decades of experience, the New Jersey firm of Corradino &amp; Papa, LLC&#160; provides the skilled legal support needed when individuals suffer injury in NJ car accidents caused by the negligence of other parties. Our <a href="http://www.corradinoandpapa.com/practice-areas/car-accident-attorney/" target="&#95;blank">NJ car accident attorneys</a> are always available in emergency situations, and you pay no fee unless we recover damages. If you are in an accident, call us toll-free at 877-574-1200.</p><p>Corradino and Papa, LLC<br />935 Allwood Road, Suite 240, <br />Clifton, NJ 07012<br />877-574-1200</p><!--more-->Anyone injured in a New Jersey car accident caused by the negligence of one or more other parties has the right to pursue compensation for all expenses related to injuries and other losses. However, identifying all negligent parties can be more complicated than you might expect. NJ car accident lawyers often need to conduct detailed investigations to uncover everyone who shares responsibility for an accident.'
