aS'<p>-Blog posted but not reviewed or edited by LedgerLaw-</p><p dir="ltr">Hundreds of accidents happen every minute. Oftentimes these accidents happen due to simple negligence. If you have been a victim of such accident and your physical injury caused by the accident lead to lost wages, personal suffering, property damages and perhaps a change in your lifestyle, then it is time that you call in the big guns. A personal injury lawyer is a professional lawyer that can help you get the appropriate representation if you have been involved in accident wherein you are the victim. Personal injury lawyer are most common called upon during car accidents but they can also handle cases that involves your employer, you next door neighbor, your surgeon or just about anyone whove caused you personal or psychological injuries due to negligence. </p><b><p dir="ltr">What a lawyer can do for you?</p></b><p dir="ltr">When you are looking for a lawyer to handle your case, you need to first consider their background experience. Professionals have certification and licenses that proves their expertise but through experience they learn more and eventually become an expert. Filing a case against someone is a tough deal, but if you have a reputable lawyer by your side this is not going to be a problem at all. In fact, your chance of winning depends greatly on the person who represents you. </p><p dir="ltr">In cases of auto accidents, lawyers are up against the insurance company. Most insurance companies will have great lawyers too, that is why you need a representation that can help you get the most out of these insurance companies. A good personal injury lawyer can push them beyond their limit. You will not just get justifiable amount in terms of compensation but you will get the best out of it.</p><b><p dir="ltr">How much to pay?</p></b><p dir="ltr">There are different ways on how you can pay your lawyer. For lawyers, it is understandable that you cannot pay for their services right away. Of course they take into consideration some of the factors that hinder you from being able to pay like you had a personal injury and are not working due to physical pain. For these cases, a personal injury lawyer that charges you after winning the case will be more helpful. You will have an agreement that would be beneficial to both of you. The charges vary from 20% to 25% of the total compensation that you are claiming. If your lawyer lost the case, he or she will not be compensated, but if your case won, your lawyer is getting a percentage of the total amount compensated. This is called a contingency basis. This will be beneficial to you if you do not have money to spare for the case expenses. Lawyers that offer such also tend to work harder to win the case and to get more compensation to get higher commission.</p><p /><p>Law Offices of Ledger &amp; Associates<br />811 Wilshire Blvd<br />Suite 1000<br />Los Angeles, CA 90017<br />Office: 213-493-6588<br />Toll Free 800-300-0001<br />Website: <a href="http://www.ledgerlaw.com/">www.ledgerlaw.com</a></p>'
