aS'<p>As mentioned in the Denver Post:</p><p>Cunningham Fire Rescue will honor heroes \r\nin three recent emergencies, two near drownings and an auto accident, \r\nduring a ceremony Thursday night at the fire department\'s headquarters \r\nin Arapahoe County.</p> \r\n<p>The honorees include Katie Fogan, Layne Bradbury and Jessica Evans, \r\nwho collectively pulled a young girl from the Piney Creek Pool in \r\nCentennial and resuscitated her with CPR before emergency crews arrived \r\non June 17.</p> \r\n<p>The fire department will also honor Marcus Giavanni, who pulled a \r\nyoung boy from the Alton Park Pool in unincorporated Arapahoe County on \r\nJune 20.</p> \r\n<p>In the third case, Roger Berube and Patricia Ketchum, both of whom \r\nhave medical training, were the first to help a group of injured people \r\nin a two-car crash on June 22 at South Picadilly Street and South \r\nRiviera Way in Centennial.</p> \r\n<p>They continued to assist after medical emergency crews arrived, according to the fire department.</p><p>If you or a loved one has been injured in an accident, call the law firm of Bell &amp; Pollock, P.C., 303-795-5900 www.bellpollock.com&#160; <a href="http://www.bellpollock.com" title="Auto Accident Attorneys">Denver Auto Accident Lawyers</a></p><!--more-->Cunningham Fire Rescue honors heroes, Arapahoe County'
