aS'<p><strong>Questions to Ask Your Potential California Accident Attorney</strong></p><p /><p>If you are searching for an accident attorney, you have already survived the worst part of your ordeal &#8212; possibly an accident with a 20,000 to 80,000-pound truck.&#160; </p><p>Finding the right <a href="http://www.bostwickandjanoff.com/" target="&#95;blank">accident lawyer in san jose</a> to represent your case and fight for your rights to compensation for medical expenses, time off work, and pain and suffering is not as difficult as it might seem.&#160; </p><p>Start by asking the right questions. <br /><br />You want an accident attorney who knows the law</p><ul><li>What are my rights in this accident and how will you protect them?</li><li>What does California accident law say about liability and how does it apply in my case?</li><li>When do I have to decide if I want to file a lawsuit or not?</li></ul><p>You want an&#160;attorney who can explain liability</p><ul><li>Who is responsible for paying my medical bills, prescriptions, physical therapy and other expenses for my recovery?</li><li>How does lost time from work factor into my case?</li><li>Who will pay for my vehicle that may have been smashed by a tractor trailer?</li><li>I have to pay someone now to do my chores and shopping&#8212;who covers those expenses?</li></ul><p>You need an attorney to assess your case</p><ul><li>How do you determine if my case is worth taking?</li><li>What factors are working in my favor and what, if anything, is working against me?</li><li>I have heard of &#8220;pain and suffering&#8221;&#8212;what does it really mean, and does it apply in my case?</li><li>I was working when the accident occurred - how does that affect my case?</li></ul><p>An experienced attorney can tell you what to expect</p><ul><li>What is involved in filing a lawsuit against the driver who caused the accident?</li><li>What paperwork has to be filed and who files it?</li><li>What is your fee and are there additional costs I might have to pay?</li><li>What, if anything, should I be doing now to help my case?</li></ul><p>It is important and you deserve answers to all of these questions.&#160; If you have been injured in an accident in California, you may be entitled to compensation for medical expenses, lost wages, pain and suffering, and more.&#160; </p><p>Experienced <a href="http://www.bostwickandjanoff.com/attorneys/" target="&#95;blank">accident lawyers in San Jose</a>, <strong>Bostwick &amp; Janoff</strong>, who practice personal injury &amp; accident law can walk you through the legal issues and fight for the compensation you deserve.&#160; </p><p>Call <strong>408-286-2300</strong> to reach Bostwick &amp; Janoff today.</p><p /><!--more--><p>Finding the right <a href="http://www.bostwickandjanoff.com/" target="&#95;blank">accident lawyer in san jose</a> to represent your case and fight for your rights to compensation for medical expenses, time off work, and pain and suffering is not as difficult as it might seem...&#160; </p>'
