d ropes across trails: many times, bikers won&#8217;t see these ropes until they have caused accidents. </li><li>75% of motorcycle and bicycle accidents involve other vehicles. Most common are accidents in which the car or truck did not see the bike.</li><li>Rear-end collisions: caused by drivers of cars that did not see you.</li><li>Road debris: Loose pavement, oil slicks, uneven concrete or pot holes.</li><li>Car doors opening unexpectedly: people don&#8217;t always look closely enough.</li></ul><p>If you have been injured in a motorcycle, bicycle or scooter accident in the San Francisco, contact our team of <a href="http://www.sanfranciscomotorcycleaccidentlawyers.com/firm-profile/">motorcycle accident attorneys in San Francisco</a> today. We know the motorcycle accident laws and we know how to win your case.</p><p>Pave &amp; Bogaards</p><p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&source=s&#95;q&hl=en&geocode=&q=pave+%26+bogaards&vps=3&jsv=160h&sll=37.834734,-122.395763&sspn=0.085819,0.154495&ie=UTF8&latlng=37794836,-122403527,15478787514126269608&ei=8l8pSqy6Ko6wNv2&#95;hbMO&cd=2">601 Montgomery Street, Suite 1210<br />San Francisco, CA 94111</a>&#160; <br />Toll Free:&#160; 1-866-697-7652<br />Phone:&#160; 1-415-979-0480</p><!--more-->Pave &amp; Bogaards, <a href="http://www.sanfranciscomotorcycleaccidentlawyers.com/" target="&#95;blank">motorcycle accident attorneys in San Francisco</a>, discuss important facts concerning motorcycle, bicycle, and scooter accidents in California and know the motorcycle accident laws to win your case.'
