aS'<em><strong>Fighting for your rights against the IRS</strong></em><p>Compliance with tax laws is extremely important to the health and well-being of individuals and business. Tax controversies can result in state and federal tax issues, including:</p><p>?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Audits</p><p>?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Appeals</p><p>?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Collections</p><p>?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Criminal tax investigations</p><p>?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Civil and criminal tax litigation </p><p>Many tax disputes are resolved at the audit level, or at the Office of Appeals without the need for going to court. However, the process of resolving your tax issues is complicated. A <a href="http://www.taxjams.com/overview/" target="&#95;blank">Pennsylvania tax lawyer</a> who is skilled in negotiating with the Internal Revenue Service (IRS) and has handled cases that involve tax controversies can put you in the best position to protect yourself in any dispute with the IRS.</p><em><strong>Tools available to the IRS for unpaid taxes</strong></em><p>It is important to realize that the IRS has a number of tools that it can use against you to collect underpaid taxes. The IRS can do the following:</p><ul type="disc"><li>Levy a bank account</li><li>Garnish wages</li><li>Assert a tax lien against property</li></ul><p>Late fees, interest, and criminal penalties can result. You must challenge a lien within a strict time limit to remove it. Liens can affect your credit rating, and you should address them as quickly as possible. </p><em><strong>Tax issues can arise in many situations</strong></em><p>The Tax Code is constantly changing and is extremely complex. Lawyers who practice in the tax law area work hard to stay abreast of changes in not only the Internal Revenue Code, but in the way that the <a href="http://www.irs.ustreas.gov.com/" target="&#95;blank">IRS</a> interprets it. In certain situations, it may be appropriate to seek administrative determinations or revenue rulings about complex issues. </p><p>The many types of tax matters that can arise include, but are not limited to, the following:</p><ul type="disc"><li>Income taxes</li><li>Estate taxes</li><li>Gift taxes</li><li>State sales tax</li><li>Employment taxes</li><li>Tax evasion</li><li>Failure to file</li><li>Aiding and abetting in the filing of false returns</li><li>Non-payment of tax</li><li>Whistleblowers</li></ul><em><strong>For an experienced Pennsylvania tax attorney contact us</strong></em><p>If you become involved in any type of tax controversy, the experienced McCauley Law Offices, P.C. can help. Click here to contact us online or call 484-778-4055.</p><p>McCauley Law Offices, P.C.<br />510 Kennett Pike, P.O. Box 115<br />Chadds Ford, Pennsylvania 19317<br />Phone: (484) 778-4055</p><!--more-->When you become involved in any kind of tax dispute, it is in your interest to speak to a skilled tax lawyer. Liens can affect your credit rating, and you should address them as quickly as possible.'
