aS'When people get behind the wheels of vehicles and head out onto \r\npublic roads, they basically must face an ongoing series of decisions in\r\n terms of sharing the roads with others. All of these decisions must be \r\nmade correctly in order for danger to be avoided, and unfortunately this\r\n is not always what occurs. One of the most complicated decisions that \r\nmust be made by motorists on a regular basis involves when to yield to \r\nothers. Any mistakes made in these situations can instantly lead to \r\nCalifornia car accidents that lead to serious injuries and fatalities.\r\n<p>Below you will find a brief overview of the different types of \r\ndecisions that must be made by motorists with regards to yielding the \r\nright-of-way to other drivers. You will also find examples of what could\r\n result from mistakes being made in these situations. Anyone who has \r\nbeen harmed because of a driver failing to make the proper decision \r\nregarding when to yield should seek the help of <a href="http://www.mglawyers.com/index.php">experienced San Diego personal injury lawyers</a> as soon as possible.</p>\r\nDecisions Regarding When to Yield\r\n<p>Despite the many different types of decisions that must be made by \r\nmotorists with regards to when to yield the right-of-way, there are some\r\n situations that are more common than others. One common example would \r\ninvolve four-way stops at intersections. There is a certain order that \r\nmust be maintained, and if someone proceeds out of turn it can instantly\r\n lead to a crash.</p>\r\n<p>Another common example of making decisions regarding when to yield \r\ninvolves motorists attempting to merge onto a road. These situations are\r\n often more dangerous than those that occur at four-way stops because \r\nmotorists are moving at high rates of speed. As a result, people who \r\ncrash in these situations can be forced to endure enormous forces of \r\nimpact.</p>\r\nWhy Yielding Mistakes Are So Dangerous\r\n<p>When someone is supposed to yield the right-of-way to another driver \r\nand he or she fails to do so, it will often lead to a California car \r\naccident because there is little if any time to take corrective steps. \r\nIn addition, these crashes often lead to serious injuries and fatalities\r\n because the people involved in them are completely surprised with the \r\nmistake of the other driver and they are not prepared to deal with it. \r\nTherefore, many of the crashes that occur because of this mistake \r\ninvolve high rates of speed and force.</p>\r\nHow San Diego Personal Injury Lawyers Can Help\r\n<p>When someone is injured in a crash that was caused by a driver who \r\nfailed to yield the right-of-way properly, that person could face some \r\ndifficulty proving what happened, as these incidents usually occur in an\r\n instant and those involved may not have clear memories of how they were\r\n caused. Therefore, if you or someone you love has been injured in this \r\nmanner, you need to seek the help of <a href="http://www.mglawyers.com/index.php">San Diego personal injury lawyers</a> who have been fighting for the rights of clients for many years. Contact the <strong>Mitchell | Gileon Law Firm</strong> today to schedule a free initial consultation.</p><!--more-->When someone is injured in a crash that was caused by a driver who \r\nfailed to yield the right-of-way properly, that person could face some \r\ndifficulty proving what happened, as these incidents usually occur in an\r\n instant and those involved may not have clear memories of how they were\r\n caused. Therefore, if you or someone you love has been injured in this \r\nmanner, you need to seek the help of San Diego personal injury lawyers who have been fighting for the rights of clients for many years. '
