aS'We\'ve all tripped, slipped and fallen.  All of us have, every single one of us.  Some people slip in the shower and laugh it off.  Others fall off of a roof to their death.  Falls are the number one cause of injury-producing accidents every year, causing more than one million injuries.  Slips-and-falls are a serious hazard both physically and psychologically, which is why there are so many personal injury law firms that provide expert legal advice for individuals who have fallen due to the negligence of others.  \r\n\r\nHave you been injured in a fall?  Do you know if it was a negligent fall - if someone else\'s carelessness is responsible for your injury?  If you suspect that it was, it may be a good idea to contact a slip-and-fall personal injury attorney.  Actually, it is a good idea!  Now, as you prepare to call for a free consultation, go back through the event in your mind and think about a few things.  Most importantly, what kind of fall was it.  Here are some different slip-and-fall accidents:  \r\n\r\nA - trip-and-fall accident.  This is when pedestrians fall because of a foreign object.  For instance, if you fell in a super market because a can was in an aisle or there was some foreign liquid or substance on the walking surface that made you fall.  \r\n\r\nB - step-and-fall accidents.  This is when there is an actual inconsistency in the walking surface, like a hole or a bubble.  An example of this would be if you fell because a rug was torn or there was a hole in the sidewalk.  \r\n  \r\n  C - stump-and-fall accidents.  This is when someone falls because something was sticking out of the surface on which they were walking.  An example of this would be if you fell over a nail sticking out of a wooden floor.  \r\n\r\nAccidents like these always happen when we least expect them - when we are walking to our car, down a supermarket aisle, on an elevator or in a stair well.  Perhaps your landlord didn\'t adequately inform you that the front hall had just been waxed and you slipped and broke your hip?  Perhaps a gas station didn\'t clean up after an engine oil spill and you slipped and hit your head?  Perhaps your child or your spouse fell and was injured so severely their lives will never be the same?  Whatever the case may be there are literally thousands of ways for you to seriously injure yourself from a slip-and-fall accident. \r\n\r\nIf you or a loved one has been injured or died in a slip-and-fall accident and need help determining whether or not you have a case, you need to contact an experienced personal injury attorney as soon as possible to determine what legal options you may have.  For a free and detailed evaluation with a personal injury lawyer at Ledger &amp; Associates, please call 1-800-300-0001 or visit the firm\'s website for more information at <a href="http://www.ledgerlaw.com/">www.ledgerlaw.com</a>.<!--more-->We\'ve all tripped, slipped and fallen.  All of us have, every single one of us.  Some people slip in the shower and laugh it off.  Others fall off of a roof to their death.  If you or a loved one has been injured and another party was negligent, you need to read this article...'
