aS'<p>Thousands of automobile accidents occur in Florida every year.&#160; Many are preventable or involve preventable injuries.&#160;&#160; Because many drivers on the opposite side of the yellow line are texting; reading e-mails; impaired by drugs or alcohol or anger; or simply inattentive&#8212;we all need to be hyper-vigilant.&#160; In Florida, if we are not careful, we can be face a reduction of our injuries in a law suit against the at fault driver through comparative negligence.&#160; The failure to wear a seatbelt; a sudden stop; or not giving full attention to the roadway due to our own cell phones or conversations with passengers are all potential causes of comparative negligence.&#160; Please be careful out there&#8230;</p>'
