aS'<p><u>NYC malpractice law</u></p><p>During our half a century practicing malpractice litigation in NYC, the firm of Julien &amp; Schlesinger, P.C., has seen many cases unwittingly jeopardized by small mistakes that clients make.&#160; Ironically, these clients are the very ones who desperately need the compensation and peace of mind that a successful verdict provides.&#160; </p><p><u>Common mistakes</u> </p><p>Here is a list of the most common mistakes to avoid under <a href="http://www.nyc.gov/portal/site/nycgov/?front&#95;door=true" target="&#95;blank">NYC</a> medical malpractice law:</p><ul><li>Not seeking medical attention right away.&#160; By delaying the time in which you seek treatment for your injuries, it can make it difficult to determine if they, in fact, were the result of malpractice.&#160; If you recently underwent an operation or procedure and are experiencing even minor complications, be sure to keep a record of all follow-up treatments received.&#160; This can help create appropriate documentation that your practitioner disregarded the medical malpractice laws in NYC.</li><li>Not seeking legal guidance in a timely manner.&#160; When you suspect medical malpractice, you should seek legal counsel as soon as possible.&#160; The state&#8217;s statute of limitations applies for different illnesses and injuries, but, in general, the sooner you seek an attorney knowledgeable in NYC medical malpractice laws, the sooner you can begin the process of recovering losses for your suffering.</li><li>Assuming you do not have a case against the parties that wronged you.&#160; You may think you can only press a case against a physician or primary medical caregiver who treated you.&#160; This is not necessarily correct.&#160; Anyone involved in providing treatment that resulted in your suffering can be held liable, including nurses, nursing aides, lab technicians, pharmacists, hospitals, dialysis clinics, and other medical staff and facilities.&#160; Do not assume you do not have a case until you have spoken to a <a href="http://www.julienandschlesinger.com/aop/NYC-medical-malpractice/">nyc malpractice lawyer</a></li></ul><p><u>Contact us</u></p><p>Be sure you do not take actions that would undermine your NYC medical malpractice claim.&#160; Our firm has an outstanding 70-year history of practicing medical malpractice law in NYC.&#160; To discuss your malpractice litigation in NYC, contact Julien &amp; Schlesinger, P.C. at 1-866-915-3451.</p><p>Julien &amp; Schlesinger, P.C. - <a href="http://www.julienandschlesinger.com/firm-overview/">nyc medical malpractice law firms</a><br />One Whitehall Street, 17th Floor<br />New York, New York 10004<br />Phone: 1-866-915-3451</p><!--more--><p><a href="http://www.julienandschlesinger.com/aop/NYC-medical-malpractice/">nyc medical malpractice lawyer</a> - During our half a century practicing malpractice litigation in NYC, the firm of Julien &amp; Schlesinger, P.C., has seen many cases unwittingly jeopardized by small mistakes that clients make.&#160; Ironically, these clients are the very ones who desperately need the compensation and peace of mind that a successful verdict provides.&#160; </p>'
