aS'<p class="MsoNormal"> \r\nTruck accident experts agree that it is rarely one factor that contributes to a collision occurring, but rather a combination of factors. Events occurring hours, days or even months before the crash, such as truck driver training, road conditions, and truck design and maintenance can contribute to a San Francisco truck accident occurring. Some events occurring immediately before a crash, such as a driving maneuver or a truck driver&#8217;s inability to focus on the road, can also contribute to a devastating truck collision. A Federal Motor Carrier Safety Administration (FMCSA) 2007 report revealed the different causes of large truck crashes. Based on the FMCSA study, the top ten causes of commercial truck accidents were:</p><p class="MsoNormal" /><ul><li>In 29 percent of the crashes studied, brake problems were the most common cause of truck accidents.</li><li>Speeding, or traveling too fast for conditions, was the second most common cause of truck collisions (23 percent).</li><li>In 22 percent of commercial truck wrecks, unfamiliarity with the roadway was the cause.</li><li>Roadway problems, such as potholes, debris or construction zones, were responsible for 20 percent of truck crashes.</li><li>In 17 percent of collisions studied, over-the-counter drug use contributed to an accident occurring.</li><li>Fourteen percent of large truck accidents were caused by inadequate surveillance (e.g. checking blind spots and mirrors before making a turn or driving maneuver).</li><li>Driver fatigue was present in 13 percent of commercial truck wrecks.</li><li>Demanding work schedules and pressure from truck carriers contributed to ten percent of commercial truck crashes.</li><li>Truck drivers who made an illegal driving maneuver caused nine percent of accidents.</li><li>Driver inattention was a contributing factor in nine percent of truck collisions studied.</li></ul><p /><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Experience Counts</b></p><p class="MsoNormal">Large truck accident victims searching for a qualified <a href="http://www.sanfranciscopersonal-injurylawyers.com/">San Francisco personal injury lawyer</a> should consider the number of years an attorney has been practicing law, and whether the attorney has experience and success in truck accident litigation before hiring. A skilled <a href="http://www.sanfranciscopersonal-injurylawyers.com/truck-accident.html">San Francisco truck accident attorney</a> can secure clients up to four times more monetary compensation than if a client was to handle a case on their own or hire an inexperienced lawyer.</p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Don&#8217;t Wait to Contact a San Francisco Truck Accident Lawyer</b></p><p class="MsoNormal">The sooner you contact a reputable lawyer, the sooner you may be able to recover funds for medical expenses, lost wages, lost benefits, diminished quality of life, permanent scars, disability, care giving services, and pain and suffering.\r\nThe majority of attorneys will take your call for free and in private.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&#160;</p><!--more-->Truck accident experts agree that it is rarely one factor that\r\ncontributes to a collision occurring, but rather a combination of factors. Events\r\noccurring hours, days or even months before the crash, such as truck driver\r\ntraining, road conditions, and truck design and maintenance can contribute to a\r\nSan Francisco truck accident occurring.&#160;'
