aS'<p>Making a claim against a party who has injured you in a <a title="Denver car accident attorney" href="http://www.dlslawfirm.com">Denver car accident</a>, slip-and-fall incident, motorcycle accident or other accident can be intimidating. But it needn&#8217;t be, and here&#8217;s why.</p><p>It&#8217;s natural for people to hesitate about filing a claim, because you may think other people will look disapprovingly at you like it&#8217;s somehow a bad thing to bring a claim against them, or even sue them if need be. The insurance industry has done a good job of creating the false idea that people file&#160;claims and lawsuits because they&#8217;re hoping to get a big settlement. They toss around the phrase &#8220;frivolous lawsuit&#8221; so much that people often think any claim is a frivolous action by a greedy person.</p><p>But <a title="Contact Dianne Sawaya" href="http://www.dlslawfirm.com/contact-us">if you&#8217;ve truly been hurt by someone else&#8217;s negligence</a>, you should be fairly compensated for your medical bills, for your lost income and for your pain and suffering. I tell my clients this a lot: Almost no one gets involved in an &#8220;on purpose;&#8221; they get involved in an &#8220;accident.&#8221; That&#8217;s what insurance is for &#8211; to pay for the damages resulting from a Colorado personal injury accident.</p><p>People pay premiums so if they&#8217;re involved in an accident, the insurance company will compensate the injured party. It&#8217;s a business transaction &#8211; premium for protection. If you file a claim, or even a lawsuit, you&#8217;re filing an action that an insurance company is responsible for making good on. You should no more be intimidated or hesitant to file a personal injury claim than you should be to file a claim on your health insurance or your homeowners insurance.</p><p>If you&#8217;ve been hurt in an accident, give me a call at (303) 758-4777 or email me at <a href="mailto:DLS@dlslawfirm.com">DLS@dlslawfirm.com</a>. Let&#8217;s talk about your case. There&#8217;s no obligation. At The Law Offices of Dianne Sawaya, we&#8217;re happy to talk with you. If we think you have a case, we&#8217;ll tell you so. If we don&#8217;t think you have a case, we&#8217;ll tell you that too. We can help get you and your family the financial compensation you deserve for the injuries you&#8217;ve suffered.</p><p>And remember &#8211; if we take your case, we don&#8217;t get paid unless you get paid.</p><!--more-->Making a claim against a party who has injured you in a Denver car accident, slip-and-fall incident, motorcycle accident or other accident can be intimidating. But it needn&#8217;t be, and here&#8217;s why.'
