ns, please contact one of our attorneys.  Information provided by our attorneys should only be considered legal advice after a formal attorney-client relationship has been established with our law firm and you and confirmed in writing by one of our attorneys.</em><!--more-->Last week, the U.S. Department of Homeland Security issued a new I-9 employment eligibility verification form. Employers are required to complete the I-9 form to confirm the identity and employment authorization of each new employee who is hired. Although employers should begin using the new I-9 form right away, older versions of the form (dated 02/02/09 and 08/07/09 in the lower left corner of the form) will be accepted until May 7, 2013. After May 7, 2013, only the new form will be accepted.'
