aS'<p>Our&#160;<a title="Michigan no-fault insurance attorneys" href="http://www.buckfirelaw.com/practice&#95;areas/michigan-no-fault-insurance-lawyer-detroit-auto-nofault-attorney.cfm" target="&#95;blank">Michigan&#160;no-fault insurance attorneys</a>&#160;recently settled a case with Allstate Insurance for $55,000.00.&#160; The lawsuit sought payment of unpaid attendant care services and household services to our client who was injured in a Detroit car accident.&#160;Allstate Insurance wrongfully refused to pay her benefits.</p><p>Our client suffered serious injuries, including&#160;a right acetabular fracture requiring surgery, a subsequent separation of the hardware fixing the original acetabular fracture, and an ultimate removal of a portion of the right hip and inability to walk or function normally. Multiple hip surgeries and hip replacements that have failed as her body has rejected the hardware.</p><p>As a result of these serious injuries, she required attendant care services and replacement service benefits.&#160; Medicaid paid many of her insurance benefits and Allstate insurance was required to reimburse the government, but failed to do so.&#160; Additionally, our client could not handle many of her activities of daily living and needed assistance for others.&#160; Allstate refused to pay those benefits.&#160; We filed suit for her in the Federal Court in Detroit, Michigan.&#160; The case settled before trial.</p>Victims of Michigan car accidents do have legal rights. If you or a family member have suffered injuries in an auto accident and are denied the Michigan No-Fault Insurance benefits you are entitled to contact our office now to speak to an experienced <a title="Michigan personal injury lawyer" href="http://www.buckfirelaw.com/" target="&#95;blank">Michigan personal injury lawyer</a>. Call now at (800) 606-1717!'
