aS'<p MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt" class="MsoNormal">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; In the February 13, 2012 edition of <a href="http://www.gpo.gov/fdsys/pkg/FR-2012-02-13/pdf/2012-3226.pdf">The Federal Register</a>, the Social Security Administration published new visual impairment listings for public consideration and comment.&#160; Before final changes can be made to existing regulations, the SSA must publish proposed revisions and take into account public comments.&#160; Comments must be received no later than April 13, 2012.&#160; <p /></p><p MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt" class="MsoNormal">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; While there aren&#8217;t any major changes to the <a href="http://www.tampaworkerscomp.com/social-security-determine-disability.html">current listings</a>, the SSA believes it can ensure more timely adjudication of claims by making text changes to clarify and simplify current rules and by updating additional acceptable testing for evaluating a person&#8217;s visual field loss.<p /></p><p MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt" class="MsoNormal">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; This will be the first update since 2006.&#160; According to the SSA, the proposal reflects the programs experience and adjudicator questions and comments received since 2006.&#160; On a date to be announced, the SSA intends to publish revisions to update the criteria for evaluating hearing disorders and speech and language disorders.<p /></p>'
