aS'<div class="detailSpacer articleDetailContent"><p>According to an experienced brain injury lawyer, at a few seconds rate, someone obtains a head injury due to various reasons. A large number suffer from such injuries annually, and sometimes suffer permanent disabilities because of it.</p>\r\n<p>Because of this, the leading causes of brain injury were gathered in order to set precaution.As reported by the CDC or the Center for Disease Control and Prevention, head injuries are the major cause of mortality in adults and in children. They have also found that these account to 44% of total injury related deaths in the country. And so, the following are, respectively, believed to be the five leading causes of traumatic brain injuries: Car accidents, Bicycle Accidents, Falls, Sports and Acts of Violence or Assault. &#160;If you are in accident that resulting in a brain injury contact a Traumatic Brain Injury Attorney immediately.</p>\r\n<p>The brain has a very dynamic in our body, and is also responsible for the normal functioning of many of our body systems. Therefore, if injury affects our brain, it may largely change our life as well. Injury in the brain may result to damage in our storage of information, homeostatic processes, and the accumulation and retribution of data. It may also result to unconscious emotional and social problems.</p>\r\n<p><b>Types of Head injuries</b><br />These injuries are highly avoidable, and most of the time does not yield permanent brain damage. However, amnesia, or forgetting what happened before, during, and right after the accident, sophisticated care should be given to someone who has possible head injury. Symptoms may show off days after the accident and may have worsened in time. These injuries may include bruises, lacerations, tenderness, abrasions, and other forms of damages that may be very detrimental.</p>\r\n<p><br /><b>The most common types of head injuries are:</b><br />? Loss of consciousness: shortly after the accident is one of the sure indicators of brain injury <br />? Concussion: jarring of the brain that may also result to loss of consciousness, but is less serious than a contusion.<br />? Brain contusion: it is a bruise or hematoma in the brain that may result to inflammation<br />? Skull fracture: the skull, or parts of it are broken which leaves the brain unprotected.<br />? Hematoma: bleeding or clot formation in the brain that is also indicative of a contusion<br /></p><p><b>Prevention of Such Injuries</b></p><p>In order to keep yourself safe from these injuries, it is very important to follow safety precautions at all time. These precautions are common, but are seen very effective not only to prevent brain injuries, as well as other injuries you can obtain through these accidents.</p>\r\n<p>Wearing of seat belts, helmets and other safety equipments when riding cars, bicycles and motorcycles has been a long time safety precaution. For pedestrians, especially at night, it is best to well bright colored clothing or other elements that would make you more visible at night. Children and infants should always be seated in the back seat, never in the front. Listening to music through head or earphones while walking down the streets is discouraged as it can ruin your concentration. It is also best to examine both sides of the street before crossing as to be certain that it is already safe to cross.</p>\r\n<p>To prevent falls, especially to the elderly, we encourage that you hold side rails or ask for assistance when going up or down the stairs. Avoiding slippery or wet floors is also a must. Clear passageways or walk ways with elements that may cause tripping or falling. Knowing potential side effects of medication may also ensure safety. Never leave infants or children unattended, especially when they are placed on high places or unsafe environments. Having a clear vision may also avoid such accidents.</p>\r\n<p>When engaging in sports it is always best to be equipped with safety gears, and if abuse or assault is suspected or just happened, it is best to call the proper authorities right away.</p>\r\n<p>To speak with a brain injury lawyer call 800-300-0001. Website: <a href="http://www.ledgerlaw.com/">LedgerLaw</a>.</p></div><!--more-->When engaging in sports it is always best to be equipped with safety gears, and if abuse or assault is suspected or just happened, it is best to call the proper authorities right away.To speak with a&#160;brain injury lawyer&#160;call 800-300-0001.'
