aS'<p>Auto accidents are the most common of personal injury lawsuits in the United States. <a href="http://www.nhtsa.gov/" target="&#95;blank">The National Highway Traffic Safety Administration</a> estimates that 50 million people are injured in traffic accidents each year. Most of us never give auto accidents much thought-until we are personally involved in one. But it is good to be informed in case you ever do have a serious car accident. One area it is important to focus on is whiplash, and the types of symptoms that may indicate its presence.</p><p><strong>Whiplash</strong>&#160;<br />The most common injury people suffer in a car accident is whiplash. Whiplash is a serious injury involving the neck or back. It is a collection of symptoms, usually caused by abrupt motion of the head forward or backward. It can include neck and back strains, stiffness and pain, as well as soft-tissue injuries to muscles, ligaments, and tissues. </p><p>Rear-end collisions are usually associated with a whiplash injury. Whiplash often does not appear immediately and the damage caused by it can be temporary or permanent. Most importantly, whiplash can be insidious. It may take a long time to manifest as an injury, and years to resolve. Besides neck and back pain, whiplash can also cause:</p><ul><li>Headache</li><li>Dizziness</li><li>Nervousness</li><li>Depression</li><li>Numbness in arm or hand</li><li>Nausea</li><li>Anxiety</li><li>Ringing in the ears</li><li>Blurred vision</li><li>Sleep disturbance</li></ul><p>After a car accident, seek immediate medical review of your situation. Then, contact a <a href="http://www.cranefloresllp.com/ventura-personal-injury-lawyers/" target="&#95;blank">Ventura personal injury attorney</a> about the possibility of bringing a lawsuit for the damages you incur. A firm that practices on a daily basis in the area of personal injury law knows how to fight to obtain the maximum fair compensation that you deserve.</p><p><strong>Contact our firm today</strong></p><p>If you suffered any type of injury in a car accident, do not hesitate to call us and speak to an <a href="http://www.cranefloresllp.com/" target="&#95;blank">Oxnard personal&#160;injury attorney</a> at our firm anytime day or night. Contact Crane Flores, LLP today for a free consultation. Call (866) 988-4529, 24-hours, toll free. Our attorneys are conveniently located in three offices in Santa Barbara, Oxnard, and Los Angeles. We are available to assist clients in Los Angeles, Ventura County, and Santa Barbara County, including Oxnard, Ventura, Thousand Oaks, Santa Barbara, Santa Maria, and Carpinteria. We can resolve your legal problems.</p><p>Crane Flores, LLP<br />11601 Wilshire Boulevard, Suite 500<br />Los Angeles, CA 90025<br />(310) 235-1461</p><!--more-->Auto accidents are the most common of personal injury lawsuits in the United States. The National Highway Traffic Safety Administration estimates that 50 million people are injured in traffic accidents each year. Most of us never give auto accidents much thought-until we are personally involved in one. But it is good to be informed in case you ever do have a serious car accident. One area it is important to focus on is whiplash, and the types of symptoms that may indicate its presence.'
