aS'<p>People are always bothered with the thought that the person who caused the accident is not immediately paying for their medical treatment.&#160;&#160; Truthfully, the negligent party&#8217;s insurance carrier is going to want to do their homework to determine liability.</p><p>By using your own medical insurance to pay for the care you are taking advantage of your health insurance carrier&#8217;s contracted rates with the medical providers.&#160; Ultimately, the negligent party will pay for your care as most health insurance carriers will want reimbursement for the costs they incurred in your treatment.</p><p>If you have been injured in an accident and need representation from an <a href="http://www.jacksonwhitelaw.com/az-personal-injury/">Arizona personal injury attorney</a>, please call me at (480) 648-8928.</p>'
