aS'<br /><p>White crosses and roadside shrines dot highway areas across the United States where people died because of traffic accidents. Dangers vary depending on the streets and roadways. However, when accidents result from someone&#8217;s negligence causing injury or death, an accident lawyer can help victims recover compensation for damages. </p><p><b>Dateline study reveals road dangers</b></p><p><a href="http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/7844269/ns/dateline&#95;nbc/t/dangerous-roads/" target="&#95;blank">Dateline NBC television</a> studied America\'s most dangerous roads by searching, reviewing, and evaluating information contained in federal accident databases about fatal accidents. They scrutinized highways county by county and found that fatal crashes often involve speeding motorists and drunk driving.</p><p>Traffic congestion and high speeds add to the dangers of drunk driving on interstate freeways, which put the interstates at the top of Dateline\'s dangerous highways list. Dateline&#8217;s analysis of Illinois revealed that Cook County\'s section of I-94 was the most dangerous for drunken driving encounters. While I-94 did not rank top of the list nationwide, it ranked significantly high.</p><p>While much of Route 66 no longer exists, dangerous curves and steep inclines made it one of Illinois\' most precarious highways, which at one point earned the nickname of Bloody 66. Route 66 extended from Chicago to Los Angeles. However, during the 1960s and 70s, the national highway system constructed Interstate 55 to replace the Route 66 stretch between Chicago and St. Louis.</p><p>The Dateline report also revealed that some roadways are particularly dangerous for pedestrians. Yet, fences, re-synchronized traffic lights, and signs alerting motorists about pedestrian traffic can significantly diminish deaths of those on foot. While a concern, pedestrian deaths represent only 10 percent of traffic fatalities. Many more people die as motorists in traffic accidents. </p><p><b>For trusted legal representation</b></p><p>For more than 50 years, our attorneys at Friend, Levinson &amp; Turner LTD have helped clients obtain the compensation they deserve for accidents that cause injuries and wrongful deaths. Our <a href="http://www.fltinjurylawfirm.com/">Chicago car accident attorneys</a> also assist clients with real estate, worker comp, and personal injury cases. Our law firm is conveniently located at 33 N. LaSalle St., Suite 3200, Chicago, IL 60602. Clients can call toll free at 888-512-3025, locally at 312-346-8465. </p><!--more-->White crosses and roadside shrines dot highway areas across the United States where people died because of traffic accidents.&#160; Dangers vary depending on the streets and roadways.&#160; However, when accidents result from someone&#8217;s negligence causing injury or death, Chicago car accident lawyers can help victims recover compensation for damages. '
