aS'<p>Los Angeles is home to some of the most dangerous roadways in the country. Each year, traffic congestion and driver negligence contribute to thousands of accidents, making a car accident lawsuit in Los Angeles a very common occurrence. Highways in and around the Los Angeles metro area were the subject of a recent national study. </p><p>According to the Scripps Howard News Service, California highways represent fifty percent of a list of the most dangerous roads nationwide. The list, based on a survey of 562,712 total fatal automobile accidents between 1994 and 2008, describes several California roads in detail: </p><p /><ul><li>Most dangerous national highway: I-15, San Bernardino County. During the study period, a total of 834 automobile accidents occurred, and these crashes caused 1,069 deaths. I-15 was the only highway found to be involved in more than 1,000 fatalities. </li><p /><li>Second most dangerous national highway: I-10 in Riverside County, totaling 440 accidents and 515 fatalities. </li><p /><li>Third most dangerous national highway: I-5 in Los Angeles County, accounting for 434 auto accidents and 494 deaths during the period that the study covers. </li><p /><li>The sixth most dangerous national highway: I-5 in San Diego County, accounting for 348 accidents that contributed to 382 deaths. </li><p /><li>Eighth most dangerous national highway: I-10 in Los Angeles, with 299 accidents and 327 deaths.</li></ul><p>Factors contributing to the danger of these roads include road design, construction, repair, and reorganization, in addition to instances of reckless and careless driving. </p><p>If you suffer an accident on any road in California, discuss your case with an experienced <a title="Automobile Accident Attorney in Los Angeles" href="http://www.mansellandmansell.com/ourexpertise/auto-accident/find-car-accident-attorney-la-california/" target="&#95;blank">automobile accident attorney in Los Angeles</a>. Mansell &amp; Mansell, A.P.C., has assisted victims of Los Angeles auto accidents for the past twenty years, obtaining tens of millions of dollars in compensation on their behalf. Talk to our attorneys today to see how our firm can help win your case. </p><p><b>Contact our auto accident attorneys in Los Angeles</b> </p><p>Contact the <a title="Los Angeles Car Wreck Attorneys" href="http://www.mansellandmansell.com/Articles/who-is-at-fault-in-your-crash/" target="&#95;blank">Los Angeles car wreck attorneys</a> at the law firm of Mansell &amp; Mansell, A.P.C. today for a free consultation. Let our Los Angeles car wreck lawyers help with your case, and ensure that your legal rights are protected. </p><p />Mansell &amp; Mansell<br />1645 N. Vine Street, Suite 306<br />Los Angeles, CA 90028-8805<!--more-->A <a title="Car Accident Lawyer in Los Angeles" href="http://www.mansellandmansell.com/faqs/car-accident-attorney-la/" target="&#95;blank">car accident lawyer in Los Angeles</a> explains a recent study.'
