aS'<p>What types of injuries can a personal injury attorney help me with?</p><p>Many people are under the misconception that a <a href="http://www.thklaw.com/practice-areas/personal-injury/">personal injury lawyer in Connecticut</a>&#160;only handles accident cases.&#160; Personal injury attorneys manage cases that are caused by negligence, recklessness, intentional or a deliberate wrongful act committed by a personal, corporation, company, or entity.&#160; The case may be an auto accident, nursing home abuse,&#160; a defective product, unsafe premises, assault, slip and fall, undergoing traumatic event due to someone&#8217;s wrongful death, service of alcohol by a bar or restaurant to an intoxicated patron, and even a dog bite.</p><p>Personal Injuries</p><p>Physical Personal Injuries</p><p>Injuries that result from physical personal injuries are:</p><p>- Traumatic brain injury<br />- Head trauma<br />- Back injury<br />- Neck problems<br />- Broken bones<br />- Burns<br />- Blood loss<br />- Arm and hand injuries<br />- Leg and foot injuries<br />- Chest injuries<br />- Hip injuries<br />- Damage to internal organs<br />- Death<br />- Loss of consciousness <br />- Scarring<br />- Loss or impairment of hearing<br />- Loss or impairment of eyesight</p><p>If you were injured due to the fault of another person, you are entitled to compensation for your injury.&#160; Compensation is awarded for the following damages:&#160; pain and suffering, lost wages and loss of earnings, medical expenses, out-of-pocket expenses, and property damage.&#160; Physical and emotional injuries, permanent impairment or disability, impairment of your daily activities of leisure and necessary daily activities of living such as walking, sitting, and standing. </p><p>If an immediate family member such as a spouse, child, or parent was seriously injured, you can file a personal injury lawsuit on their behalf.&#160; If your loved one died as the result of their injury, a wrongful death lawsuit for additional damages for burial or funeral expenses, pain and suffering, loss of life, loss of decent future earnings &amp; activities, an action for loss of consortium on behalf of the spouse of the decedent or seriously injured husband or wife may be filed in addition to the primary action for dead spouse or severely injured spouse.</p><p>Other Types of Injuries</p><p>Not all injuries are caused by physical harm.&#160; Other types of injuries a Connecticut personal injury lawyer can help you with are financial and emotional injuries, cost wages, cost earning potential.</p><p>Financial injuries such as fraud, an unethical contract, or a real estate dispute can affect your family and business.</p><p>Cases of libel, slander, or emotional abuse can cause long-term negative effects on you, your family, and your business.&#160; </p><p>If you are not sure what type of injury for which you should seek a personal injury attorney, you would be wise to present your case to someone who can give you a definitive answer.</p><p>This article was prepared by the <a href="http://www.thklaw.com/attorneys-staff/">Connecticut personal injury&#160;attorneys</a> at Tindall, Holmes &amp; Kestenband, LLC, 1-866-488-8625, <a href="http://www.thklaw.com/">www.thklaw.com</a>.</p><p>Tindall, Holmes &amp; Kestenband<br />67 Holmes Avenue<br />Waterbury, CT 06710<br />Phone: (203) 755-0018</p><p>Satellite Office<br />One Lewis Place<br />Hartford, CT 06106<br />Phone: (866) 488-8625</p><!--more-->Many people are under the misconception that a <a href="http://www.thklaw.com/practice-areas/personal-injury/">personal injury lawyer in Connecticut</a>&#160;only handles accident cases.&#160; Personal injury attorneys manage cases that are caused by negligence, recklessness, intentional or a deliberate wrongful act committed by a personal, corporation, company, or entity.&#160;'
