aS'<p>A train <b>struck and killed</b> a 55-year old man riding a bicycle in downtown Tucson Monday night, the <a href="http://azstarnet.com/news/local/crime/article&#95;334a04d0-41a9-11df-b6bd-001cc4c002e0.html">Arizona Daily Star reports</a>. Jerry Williams reportedly rode his bike around the lowered crossing arms as a westbound train approached. Witnesses also said Williams ignored the flashing lights at the intersection as well as the train&#8217;s warning horn. </p><p><b>Crossing the tracks on a bike</b> can be very dangerous. In addition to heeding all warning signals, bike-riding safety guidelines suggest riders either walk or ride your bike with wheels perpendicular to the tracks to avoid getting tires caught. In this particular <b><a href="http://www.blackmanlegal.com/CM/PracticeAreaDescriptions/TrainInjuryAccidents.asp" target="&#95;blank">train accident fatality</a></b>, authorities are waiting for Williams&#8217; toxicology report to find out if alcohol was involved.</p><p><i>The <a href="http://www.blackmanlegal.com/">personal injury lawyers</a> at Blackman Legal Group, a California-based law firm founded by renowned trial attorney, <a href="http://www.blackmanlegal.com/CM/Custom/Attorneys.asp#Blackman">Clifford Blackman</a>, has been representing injury victims since 1976, and have special expertise in cases involving <a href="http://www.spinal-injury-california.com/">spinal cord injury</a>, <a href="http://www.brain-injury-lawyer.com/">traumatic brain injury</a>, <a href="http://www.personal-injury-san-francisco.net/burn-injury.php">burn injury</a>, <a href="http://www.personal-injury-san-francisco.net/personal-injury-overview.php">catastrophic injuries</a> and <a href="http://www.wrongful-death-lawfirm.com/">wrongful death</a>.&#160; The nationwide toll-free number to call for a free consultation is <b>1-888-395-3551.</b></i></p>'
