aS'<p>If you&#8217;ve been injured in a <a href="http://www.accidentslawyernewyork.com/" target="&#95;blank">construction accident in New York City</a>, whether you were on the job or merely an unsuspecting passerby, you know you need the assistance of an attorney.&#160; But you may be confused about what kind of lawyer will be best able to investigate, evaluate, and handle your case.</p><p>You need an attorney who specializes in construction site accident injury cases.&#160; Many attorneys handle negligence cases, but construction site accidents are often more involved than a general negligence case.&#160; You need an attorney who is familiar with construction site safety law, local rules and regulations governing construction sites, O.S.H.A. and the local Industrial Code.</p><p>But it&#8217;s not enough to know the law.&#160; You need an attorney who understands the day to day workings of a construction site, the trades, the relationships on a building site, communication among workers and supervisors, the role of the unions, the site safety directors, the construction manager, the general contractor, and the subcontractors.&#160; Your attorney ought to have the capacity to investigate and understand the causes of your accident in order to identify where responsibility lies.&#160; In short, you need an attorney who has experience and thorough familiarity with the both the law and the way things actually work at the site.&#160;&#160; </p><p>A lawyer with prior experience with many <a href="http://www.accidentslawyernewyork.com/aop/construction/" target="&#95;blank">New York City construction accident injury</a> cases will be well equipped to handle your case wisely.&#160; You want an attorney who has both settled such cases and taken them to trial, someone who is equally comfortable at the settlement conference or in court, and is a skilled negotiator with insurance company representatives.&#160; </p><p>You should not hesitate to ask an attorney about their experience with all facets of construction site accident injury litigation.&#160; Finally, you want a compassionate lawyer who will listen to your story and fully grasp how your injury has impacted your health, your financial status, and indeed, your life.</p><p>Choose an attorney who exclusively practices personal injury law, but has specific experience in claims related to construction accidents.</p><p>Contributed by The Law Office of John O&#8217;Gara, Esq., P.C., <a href="http://www.accidentslawyernewyork.com/attorneys/" target="&#95;blank">New York construction accident attorney</a>.</p><!--more-->If you&#8217;ve been injured in a <a href="http://www.accidentslawyernewyork.com/" target="&#95;blank">construction accident in New York City</a>, whether you were on the job or merely an unsuspecting passerby, you know you need the assistance of an attorney.&#160; But you may be confused about what kind of lawyer will be best able to investigate, evaluate, and handle your case.'
