aS'\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" margin: 0in 0in 0pt;">What is soil subsidence?&#160; Subsidence occurs when a building is\r\nconstructed on fill soil.&#160; Fill soil is\r\nnot the natural bedrock, but is soil that is brought in to the building site\r\nfrom another location.&#160; For example, is a\r\ndevelopment is being constructed on a canyon, fill soil is brought in to fill\r\nin the canyon in order to make a level building pad.&#160; Fill soil needs to be properly\r\ncompacted.&#160; If the soil is not properly\r\ncompacted, it will settle, or subside over time.&#160; Soil subsidence is the settling of fill soil\r\nover time.&#160; As the soil settles, the\r\nstructures built on top of the fill soil can also settle.&#160; This can lead to damage to the buildings,\r\nwalls, roads, and other building structures.&#160;\r\nDepending on how poorly compacted the fill soil is, subsidence can occur\r\nfor a number of years, and can get progressively worse over time.&#160; Subsidence is often triggered by water.&#160; The more rain or irrigation, the greater\r\nlikelihood that subsidence will occur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" margin: 0in 0in 0pt;">&#160; Do you suspect that damage may be occurring at\r\nyour home because of subsidence?&#160; Call us\r\nat 1-866-2020 for a free consultation.</p>\r\n\r\n'
