aS'<div class="WordSection1">Couples must tackle the same issues during separation as they do during divorce:</div><p /><ul><li><div class="WebBulletList">Child custody</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Child support</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Property division</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Spousal support</div></li></ul><p /><div class="WordSection4"><p class="WebText">In many separations, the terms reached can later be used to set precedents for divorce.&#160; To help clients make informed decisions, a divorce lawyer needs to know all the facts pertinent to separation. </p><p class="WebText">Information you should bring to a separation or divorce consultation with a <a title="Long Beach divorce lawyer" href="http://www.bsdfamilylaw.com/" target="&#95;blank">Long Beach divorce lawyer</a> includes:</p></div><p /><div class="WordSection5"><p class="WebHead2h2"><strong><em>Financial information</em></strong></p><ul><li><div class="WebBulletList">Tax returns (last three to five years)</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Pay stubs for you and your spouse</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Bank statements</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Retirement accounts</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Pension plans</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Health insurance</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Life insurance</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Credit card statements</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Investment account statements</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Approximate living expenses</div></li></ul><p class="WebHead2h2"><strong><em>Assets</em></strong></p><ul><li><div class="WebBulletList">List of possessions&#8212;cars, boats, jewelry, paintings, RV, etc. </div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">List of non-marital property&#8212;inheritances, family heirlooms, etc.</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Coin collections</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Stamp collections</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Antiques</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Furniture</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Appliances</div></li></ul><p class="WebHead2h2"><strong><em>Property </em></strong></p><ul><li><div class="WebBulletList">Real estate property deeds</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Car titles and registrations</div></li></ul><p class="WebHead2h2"><strong><em>Debts</em></strong></p><ul><li><div class="WebBulletList">Mortgage loans</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Car loans</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Student loans</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Private loans</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Credit card debt</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Unpaid bills</div></li></ul><p class="WebHead2h2"><strong><em>Legal contracts</em></strong></p><ul><li><div class="WebBulletList">Prenuptial agreement</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Post-nuptial agreement</div></li></ul><p class="WebHead2h2"><strong><em>Children information</em></strong></p><ul><li><div class="WebBulletList">Names, ages, and addresses</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Relevant medical records (if child has a medical condition)</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Police records showing abuse or neglect</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">Court appointment of a <a href="http://research.lawyers.com/glossary/guardian-ad-litem.html">guardian <i>ad litem</i></a></div></li></ul></div><p /><p class="WebHead2h2"><strong><em>Purpose of a consultation</em></strong></p><p class="WebText">Meeting with a divorce lawyer provides an opportunity to answer all your questions about divorce and to discuss your objectives.&#160; Before meeting with a lawyer, you should jot down any questions you have, such as:</p><ul><li><div class="WebBulletList">Do you offer mediation, collaborative divorce, and other alternatives to litigation?</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">How frequently do you settle cases out of court?</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">What is your experience with divorce cases?</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">What is the best approach for my divorce?</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">How are legal fees determined?</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">With your current caseload, do you have time to devote to my case?</div></li><li><div class="WebBulletList">What is your availability if I have questions or concerns?</div></li></ul><p class="WebText">Be sure to discuss the reasons why you want a divorce and your goals for child custody and property division.&#160; The consultation with a divorce lawyer is a two-way process.&#160; A&#160;Long Beach divorce lawyer determines whether he or she can do a good job of representing you, and you decide whether the lawyer&#8217;s skills meet your needs.&#160; </p><!--more-->In many separations, the terms reached can later be used to set precedents for divorce.&#160; To help clients make informed decisions, a divorce lawyer needs to know all the facts pertinent to separation.'
