aS'<p>While it is possible to buy or sell commercial property without legal guidance, the <a href="http://www.ramirezassociates.com/">Dallas real estate lawyers</a> of&#160;Ramirez &amp; Associates, P.C. does not recommend this approach.&#160; Commercial real estate is a complex and rapidly changing field, and you need a professional who is hired specifically to look out for your best interests.<br />Realtors, brokers, mortgage lenders, and other parties involved in transactions concerning property all have their own attorneys, or use the attorneys retained by their companies, to protect them while they work in their chosen field.&#160; The only job of a qualified real estate attorney is to protect his or her client.&#160; Without this protection, you risk becoming involved in a transaction that could cause you financial or legal harm in the long run.&#160;&#160; <br /><br />If you are buying a property, your <strong>real estate attorney</strong> can help: </p><ul><li>Review offers and counteroffers made</li><li>Ensure that the title is valid</li><li>Ensure that no covenants, easements, or liens exist against the property, or will interfere with your use of it</li><li>Explain the purchase contract to you</li><li>Prepare and register all necessary legal documents concerning the purchase</li><li>If necessary, modify the terms of the mortgage with a bank</li><li>Clarify any adjustments made to the terms, including taxes paid or utility costs owed</li><li>Secure <a href="http://www.tdi.state.tx.us/title/titleman.html" target="&#95;blank">title insurance</a>, to protect against loss from defects in the title</li><li>Confirm that your registered ownership is valid and subject only to liabilities you knowingly accepted</li><li>Attend the closing meeting, reviewing all documents that you are asked to sign</li></ul><p>If you are selling a property, your real estate attorney can help:&#160;</p><ul><li>Review offers and counteroffers made, including the purchase and sale agreement</li><li>Negotiate any offers, or terms of offers, made</li><li>Prepare deeds and arrange for insurance certificates</li><li>Assist with legal issues that arise surrounding the title&#160;</li><li>Attend the closing meeting, reviewing all documents that you are asked to sign</li></ul><p>Contact&#160;the&#160;<a href="http://www.ramirezassociates.com/attorneys/" target="&#95;blank">real estate attorneys in Dallas</a>, Ramirez &amp; Associates, P.C. for help with a real estate matter in Texas or Latin America.&#160;The&#160;lawyers&#160;represent clients from around the world with Multinational Operations, and&#160;they do business in the United States and Mexico.&#160; The offices are located in Dallas, Texas and Mexico City, Mexico.&#160; </p>'
