aS'<div class="body"><p>This <a href="http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/local/breakingnews/os-truck-fire-crash-orange-20101108,0,2823800.story">accident happened at approximately 11:15 p.m. as an unidentified 49-year-old man from Apopka, Florida was driving a Ford pickup truck south on Apopka Vineland Road</a>.&#160; 18-year-old Chelsea Rodriguez of Apopka, Florida was stopped at the stop sign on McCormick Road at its intersection with Apopka Vineland Road.&#160; It was reported that Rodriguez make a left turn into the path of the Ford Pickup truck.&#160; There is a stop sign on McCormick Road but not on Apopka Vineland Road.&#160; Rodriguez was driving a Honda Pilot SUV and was struck in the driver door.&#160; The impact caused both vehicles to catch fire.&#160; Both drivers killed in the accident.&#160; Rodriguez was carrying 18-year-old Alexandria Price of Davenport, Florida at the time of the crash.&#160; Price is listed in serious condition at Orlando Regional Medical Center.&#160; This accident is still under investigation.&#160;</p><p>This Central Florida car accident is a tragedy for all involved.&#160; Notwithstanding, the at-fault driver or owner of a motor vehicle has an obligation to pay damages to those injured or killed by negligence.&#160; In this instance, there may or may not be a separate owner.&#160; Thus, it appears that the unidentified man and the passenger have claims against Rodriguez\'s estate.&#160; Whatever the limits are, this appears to be a limits case.&#160; However, my particular concern is for the seriously injured passenger.&#160; The insurance proceeds will likely&#160;not cover all of her medical bills and/or liens.&#160; Many people do not know that health insurance must be repaid from a third party personal injury settlement and have a lien or subrogated interest against the recovery.&#160; A Central Florida personal injury or car accident lawyer can help with this scenario.&#160; If you or a loved one have suffered an injury or a death in the family as a result of a Central Florida car accident, please contact a <a href="http://www.moodylaw.com/html/auto-accidents.html">Central Florida car accident attorney </a>for a free consultation.</p></div><!--more-->Deadly Central Florida car accident kills both drivers and seriously injures passenger.'
