aS'<p>The&#160;<a title="Glendale personal injury lawyers" href="http://www.mylalawyers.com/" target="&#95;self">Glendale Personal injury lawyers</a>&#160;of Zinder &amp; Koch, APLC talk about personal injury in California and how it can affect you.</p><p>Personal injury laws are in the news quite frequently in Southern California, normally in regard to punitive damages or other amounts awarded in relation to a particularly catastrophic accident or injury.&#160; However, personal injury laws impact our lives in much subtler ways than we sometimes notice.</p><p>Consider the coffee you purchased this morning.&#160; You probably did not stop to reflect on the small warning printed on the side of the disposable cup, reminding you that your coffee is hot.&#160; However, that warning is there as a direct result of personal injury litigation brought on by individuals burned by the contents of a hot cup of coffee.&#160; The legal decision in this case, requiring such warnings be printed, translates into more effort and resources expended by the cup manufacturer. This in turn leads to higher prices for that cup of coffee you may have bought this morning in Glendale. Injury litigation can have an economic impact but, in this case, fewer people are likely to be burned.</p><p><strong>Personal injury laws can improve business</strong></p><p>Not all personal injury laws mean higher prices passed on down the supply chain.&#160; Some create booms for specific industries.&#160; When you were a child, for example, you probably never considered wearing a bicycle helmet while cruising your neighborhood on your two-wheeler.&#160; Now, bike helmets are ubiquitous, thanks to personal injury laws that led to the legal mandate that all California cyclists under eighteen wear helmets.&#160; This certainly means slightly more of a cost outlay for your average cyclist, but the increase in safety is immeasurable. And the companies that manufacture such helmets are thriving.</p><p>Also consider hands-free devices in automobiles.&#160; Personal injury litigation has led to the widespread perception that talking on a cell phone while driving is a negligent act, since it distracts the driver and removes one hand from the steering wheel.&#160; Many states, including California, now maintain laws requiring the use of hands-free devices if you talk on a cell phone while driving.&#160; Again, this means pricier equipment for the consumer, but theoretically leads to safer driving conditions for all&#8212;and increased profit for electronics companies.</p><p><strong>Experienced Glendale personal injury lawyers</strong><br />If you or a loved one has been the victim of a personal injury, a case of insurance bad faith, or instance of funeral home abuse, contact the <a href="http://www.mylalawyers.com/firm-overview/">law firm</a> of My L.A. Lawyers today to schedule a free initial consultation.&#160; My L.A. Lawyers represents clients in Los Angeles, California, including in the areas of Glendale, Burbank, Santa Clarita, Palmdale, and throughout the San Fernando Valley.&#160; Let our <a title="Glendale personal injury attorneys" href="http://www.mylalawyers.com/attorneys/" target="&#95;self">Glendale personal injury attorneys</a> start working to protect your rights today.</p><!--more--><a title="Glendale personal injury lawyer" href="http://www.mylalawyers.com/" target="&#95;self">Glendale personal injury lawyer</a>, Jeffrey Zinder of Zinder &amp; Koch talks about how injury laws affect business.&#160;&#160; Contact our <a title="attorneys" href="http://www.mylalawyers.com/attorneys/" target="&#95;self">personal injury attorneys</a> today for legal guidance you can depend on.'
