aS'<p>Texas highways are among the most dangerous roadways for tractor trailer accidents in the nation.&#160; Of the more than 5,000 fatal traffic accidents that occurred on Texas roadways in 2007, the <a href="http://ldcblogs.martindale.com/lawyers/serendipity/www.nhtsa.gov/">National Highway Traffic Safety Administration</a> says that 18-wheelers caused roughly 450.&#160;&#160; </p><p>Because of their massive size and weight, these big rigs can leave terrible death and destruction in their wake whenever they are involved in a collision.&#160; Fully loaded, these 18-wheeler tractor trailers can weigh as much as 80,000 pounds when they come barreling down the highway.&#160; If they happen to be carrying flammable chemicals or hazardous materials, the collateral damage they cause in a collision can intensify.&#160; </p><p>The most treacherous interstates worth noting in East Texas include the following:</p><p>-I-30 from Ft. Worth to Greenville<br />-I-35 from Waco to Denton<br />-I-20 from Abilene to Tyler<br />-I-45 from Dallas to Houston</p><p>There are also many local highways in the Dallas area, such as Routes 67 and 75 that have seen their share of bad truck accidents and fatalities.&#160;&#160; </p><p>If you have been involved in a trucking accident then contact a <a href="http://www.derryberryzips.com/Wrongful-Death/">Texas wrongful death attorney</a> at&#160;the Law Firm of Derryberry and Zips.</p><p><a href="http://www.derryberryzips.com/">Derryberry &amp; Zips</a><br />3333 Lee Parkway<br />Suite 600<br />Dallas, Texas 75219 </p><!--more--><a href="http://www.derryberryzips.com/Wrongful-Death/">Texas Wrongful Death Attorney</a> discuss dangerous&#160;highways in Texas.'
