aS'<p><a href="http://mjmandel.com/">San Francisco Personal Injury Lawyers</a></p><p>As reported by the San Francisco Chronicle, The San Francisco City Attorney\'s Office may file a civil lawsuit against the owners of a building and the club where a gun battle erupted after a party Sunday night, officials said Friday.</p><p>A group of teens who attended the Theater District party are believed to have started a gunfight that inadvertently killed German tourist Mechthild Schroer, 50. Two other bystanders were shot but survived.</p><p>Police said there was not enough security to handle the crowd outside the event, which took place on the fifth floor of 414 Mason St. The fire marshal told the owners Tuesday that the gathering violated fire codes.</p><p>In a letter, the city attorney told Joseph Ursino, the building\'s owner, and Kurtis Matthews, who rented his San Francisco Comedy College and Clubhouse space to an independent promoter, that they face a lawsuit for violating fire and business codes. The letter noted that the Fire Department would have denied a permit to the party because of the space was designed to handle only 49 people in an office and lacked the exits to handle more or serve as a hall for a public assembly. About 200 came to the event and another 200 milled around outside, police say.</p><p>&quot;As tragic as the circumstances surrounding this unlawful event were on the night of August 8,&quot; City Attorney Dennis Herrera said in the letter, &quot;it is chilling to imagine how ghastly the consequences might have been had a fire or shooting, and its attendant panic, occurred inside the venue.&quot;</p><p>The letter seeks a meeting with the owners in advance of litigation and asked that they reply by Aug. 20.</p><p>San Francisco police investigating the case searched a residence in the 3600 block of Lake Tahoe Terrace in Fremont on Thursday night, but did not make an arrest. Investigators seized unspecified property in the raid.</p><p>If you or a loved one has been injured or killed as the result of inadequate security you may need to speak with an injury attorney.&#160; The <a href="http://mjmandel.com/aop/san-francisco-personal-injury-litigation/">San Francisco personal injury&#160;attorneys</a> Michael &amp; Michelle Mandel offer free consultations to victims and their families.&#160; Call today to speak with a <a href="http://mjmandel.com/aop/california-auto-and-motor-vehicle-accidents/">San Francisco accident lawyer</a> today. 415-651-4924.</p><p>1390 Market Street<br />Fox Plaza, Suite 310<br />San Francisco, CA 94102<br />Free Consultation 415-651-4924</p><!--more--><a href="http://mjmandel.com/attorneys/">San Francisco attorneys</a> handling personal injury.'
