aS'<p><br />As reported by Times Newsline, According to a congressional report, U.S. health regulators are investigating the complications associated with dozens of recalled children\'s medications made by Johnson &amp; Johnson (JNJ.N).&#160; </p><p>The report said that the regulators are also probing 30 deaths related to the complications, but so far no direct link has been found.</p><p>Democratic staff on the House Oversight and Government Reform Committee said in a document released yesterday that the Food and Drug Administration (FDA) does not consider the 775 reported adverse events a &quot;spike&quot; and there is no &quot;clear pattern&quot; showing that the recalled products have caused the problems.</p><p>&quot;At this time, FDA is not aware of any child being harmed by taking one of the recalled products,&quot; said the staff report. &#8220; FDA is still investigating some of these adverse events to determine if the events were related to a child taking one of the recalled medicines,&quot; added the report.</p><p>The J&amp;J has issued a voluntary recall on April 30 and since then several hundred more cases of complications, including seven deaths, have been reported to the FDA. Notably, when the company had announced the recall, the FDA officials had said the chance of getting sick from the products was highly unlikely.</p><p>The recall was issued after the FDA regulators found that the plant producing liquid children\'s versions of Tylenol pain reliever and other medications was not following the right procedure and the drugs were contaminated. </p><p>If you have a loved one who may have been killed or badly injured due to the <a href="http://www.vanbloislaw.com/aop/drugs-medical-devices/">dangerous side effects</a> of over the counter or prescription drugs contact <a title="Van Blois & Associates" href="http://www.vanbloislaw.com">Van Blois &amp; Associates</a> for a free case evaluation. (510) 635-1284</p><!--more-->According to a congressional report, U.S. health regulators are investigating the complications associated with dozens of recalled children\'s medications made by Johnson &amp; Johnson (JNJ.N).&#160;'
