aS'<p>In South Carolina on March 23, a kayaker attempted a second run over 12 foot high Hooker Falls in DuPont State Forest. According to the <a href="http://www.citizen-times.com/article/20100324/NEWS01/100324044/DuPont-kayaker-suffered-spinal-injury">Asheville Citizen-Times</a>, the 21 year old Ohio University student had landed the first attempt without problem. On the second run she did not gain enough speed, subsequently suffering a <b>broken back</b> during her landing, upon striking a large rock at the foot of the falls.</p><p>The woman&#8217;s<b> spinal injury</b> does not pose a threat of <b>paralysis</b>. But, the <b>fractured vertebra</b> in her lower spine requires temporary wear of a back brace which limits her range of motion through recovery. The student was able to walk out of the hospital the same evening to rejoin her spring break trip companions.</p><p>The <a href="http://www.blackmanlegal.com/">personal injury lawyers</a> at Blackman Legal Group, a California-based law firm founded by renowned trial attorney, <a href="http://www.blackmanlegal.com/CM/Custom/Attorneys.asp#Blackman">Clifford Blackman</a>, has been representing injury victims since 1976, and have special expertise in cases involving <a href="http://www.spinal-injury-california.com/">spinal cord injury</a>, <a href="http://www.brain-injury-lawyer.com/">traumatic brain injury</a>, <a href="http://www.personal-injury-san-francisco.net/burn-injury.php">burn injury</a>, <a href="http://www.personal-injury-san-francisco.net/personal-injury-overview.php">catastrophic injuries</a> and <a href="http://www.wrongful-death-lawfirm.com/">wrongful death</a>.&#160; The nationwide toll-free number to call for a free consultation is <b>1-888-395-3551.</b></p>'
