aS'\r\n\r\n<p line-height: normal;" class="MsoNormal">A motorcyclist with a criminal\r\nrecord fled police enforcement early in 2013, and was caught after crashing his\r\nmotorcycle bike after running a red light just after four o&#8217;clock in the\r\nafternoon.&#160; The rider, a 26 year old\r\nmale, was driving illegally as he attempted to flee from the cops, getting\r\ncaught after speeding into a curb while unsuccessfully attempting to make a\r\nleft hand turn and navigate the corner.&#160;\r\nTwo police officers ended up chasing the man and restraining him, as he\r\nattempted to avoid arrest. &#160;The\r\nmotorcycle rider was detained, and the police enforcement found nearly one\r\nhundred illegally obtained, prescription only pain killers in his jacket.&#160; He was charged with several serious crimes,\r\nincluding aggravated assault on a law enforcement officer after the police man\r\ncomplained of shoulder pain; as well as attempting to flee from an officer,\r\nresisting arrest, possession of drug paraphernalia, possession of drugs with\r\nthe intent to sell, as well as a DUI (Driving Under the Influence) for driving &#8220;under\r\nthe influence of a controlled dangerous substance.&#8221;</p>\r\n\r\n<p line-height: normal;" class="MsoNormal"><b>Motorcycle Accident Causes</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p line-height: normal;" class="MsoNormal">Some common motorcycle accident\r\ncauses include:</p>\r\n\r\n<p text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal;" class="ListParagraphCxSpFirst">?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;\r\nThe use of drugs and alcohol while operating or\r\nbefore operating a motorcycle, like in the above account</p>\r\n\r\n<p text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal;" class="ListParagraphCxSpMiddle">?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;\r\nHitting an object on the road (accounts for\r\nabout 25% of motorcycle accident deaths)</p>\r\n\r\n<p text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal;" class="ListParagraphCxSpMiddle">?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;\r\nApproximately 42% of motorcycle accidents are a\r\nresult of car turning left and colliding with the motorcyclist</p>\r\n\r\n<p text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal;" class="ListParagraphCxSpMiddle">?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;\r\nHead on collisions (over 50% of all\r\nmotorcycle-related deaths happen for this reason)&#8212;most of the time, the\r\nmotorcyclist is struck from the front and dies instantly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal;" class="ListParagraphCxSpMiddle">?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;\r\nPoorly maintained roads, which affect\r\nmotorcyclists much more than cars</p>\r\n\r\n<p text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal;" class="ListParagraphCxSpMiddle">?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;\r\nLane splitting, or when a cyclist goes between\r\ntwo lanes, driving on the line barrier as in the case of slow or stopped\r\ntraffic</p>\r\n\r\n<p text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal;" class="ListParagraphCxSpLast">?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;\r\nSpeeding</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p margin-left: 1.5in; text-indent: 0.5in; line-height: normal;" class="MsoNormal"><b>Driver Hits Motorcycle Rider</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p line-height: normal;" class="MsoNormal">A 42 year old woman was driving\r\naround seven in the evening earlier in April of 2013 when she failed to obey a\r\ntraffic law and struck a motorcycle rider who died.&#160; The woman stopped appropriately at an\r\nintersection, but then did not proceed to allow the motorcycle rider his right\r\nof way, striking the man in a head on collision after driving straight into his\r\npath.&#160; The rider, a 44 year old man, was\r\nthrown from his motorcycle and died after hitting the pavement.&#160; Witnesses are saying that it appeared as if the\r\nsmall passenger vehicle pulled out directly in front of the 44 year old male&#8217;s\r\nmotorcycle.&#160; Police are launching an\r\ninvestigation into the case to determine why the woman failed to yield the\r\nright of way.</p><p line-height: normal;" class="MsoNormal">Someone may need <a href="http://utahadvocates.com/personal-injuries/motorcycle-accident/">Salt Lake City Motorcycle Accident Lawyers</a> or Utah injury attorney.</p>\r\n\r\n<p line-height: normal;" class="MsoNormal"><b>Why Do Motorcycle Accidents Happen?</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p line-height: normal;" class="MsoNormal">Motorcycle accidents are amongst\r\nthe most prevalent as well as the most dangerous accidents in the world, partly\r\nbecause they do not offer the encasing protection that passenger vehicles,\r\ntrucks, SUVs, and other types of hooded vehicles do.&#160; For this reason, typical passenger vehicle\r\naccident causes are amplified when a motorcycle is replaced for the car.&#160; Here are some common motorcycle collision\r\ncauses:</p>\r\n\r\n<p text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal;" class="ListParagraphCxSpFirst">?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;\r\nHead on collisions (over 50% of all\r\nmotorcycle-related deaths happen for this reason)&#8212;</p>\r\n\r\n<p line-height: normal;" class="ListParagraphCxSpMiddle">&#160;the motorcyclist is struck from the front and\r\ndies instantly</p>\r\n\r\n<p text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal;" class="ListParagraphCxSpMiddle">?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;\r\nSpeeding</p>\r\n\r\n<p text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal;" class="ListParagraphCxSpMiddle">?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;\r\nApproximately 42% of motorcycle accidents are a\r\nresult of car turning left and colliding with the motorcyclist</p>\r\n\r\n<p text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal;" class="ListParagraphCxSpMiddle">?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;\r\nThe use of drugs and alcohol while operating or\r\nbefore operating a motorcycle</p>\r\n\r\n<p text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal;" class="ListParagraphCxSpMiddle">?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;\r\nLane splitting, or when a cyclist goes between\r\ntwo lanes</p>\r\n\r\n<p text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal;" class="ListParagraphCxSpMiddle">?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;\r\nHitting an object on the road (accounts for\r\nabout 25% of motorcycle accident deaths)</p>\r\n\r\n<p text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal;" class="ListParagraphCxSpLast">?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;\r\nPoorly maintained roads, which affect\r\nmotorcyclists much more than cars. Be careful when you on a cycle or any two wheeler for that matter on the streets and highways.</p>\r\n\r\n<!--more-->Tragic bike accident news from the state of Utah.'
