aS'<p>The employment market for stockbrokers has changed dramatically.&#160; Bank of America bought Merrill Lynch.&#160; Morgan Stanley bought Smith Barney.&#160; Wells Fargo bought Wachovia which bought A.G. Edwards.&#160; JP Morgan bought Bear Stearns and Lehman Brothers is in bankruptcy.&#160; These drastic changes have forced financial advisors to consider whether they should stay at a merged firm, in a radically different work environment, or look for work elsewhere.&#160; If you are a broker, you may be unhappy with new management or find that products and services offered by your new firm don&#8217;t suit your business.</p><p>While many brokers have decided to stay after a merger, many have left and many will leave.&#160; Brokers are evaluating retention offers and weighing these against what they may find at other firms.&#160; The broker who considers leaving must try to realistically predict how much of his book he can bring with him. </p><p>In this environment, registered representatives who are considering changing firms are well-advised to hire a lawyer who understands the securities industry.&#160; An experienced securities lawyer can provide valuable advice regarding obligations under current employment contracts and provide effective and independent counsel to negotiate agreements with prospective employers.&#160; The broker who tries to change firms without investing in legal advice may put his career and client relationships in jeopardy.</p><p>Whether you need pre-conflict advice or assistance with a dispute, <a title="Westchester securities attorneys" href="http://www.dougstonelaw.com/">attorney Douglas Stone</a> has the wisdom and <a title="Westchester securities lawyer" href="http://www.dougstonelaw.com/practice-areas/Westchester-securities-fraud-law/">securities</a> industry knowledge necessary to provide sound legal advice.&#160; <a title="Westchester securities lawyers" href="http://www.dougstonelaw.com/Westchester-attorney-douglas-stone/">Mr. Stone</a> strengthens clients&#8217; cases by anticipating their opponents&#8217; tactics and strategizing to counter their claims.&#160;If you are considering an <a title="Westchester employment lawyer" href="http://www.dougstonelaw.com/practice-areas/employment-law/">employment change</a> and need legal advice and representation, call <a title="Whiteplains Securities Lawyer" href="http://www.dougstonelaw.com/Westchester-attorney-douglas-stone/">attorney Douglas Stone</a> at <u>866-720-3754</u> to arrange a free consultation.&#160; His e-mail address is dstone@dougstonelaw.com. </p><p />'
