aS'<p>Many jurisdictions within New York State permit drivers charged with speeding tickets to plead those tickets down to less serious charges, including parking violations. The practice of allowing speeding tickets to be reduced to the non-moving violation of a parking offense has been troubling to New York State lawmakers because aside from the perceived safety issue raised by this practice, the reduction to a parking violation avoids the mandatory state surcharges imposed on moving violations and allows the revenue collected from the parking violation offense to be retained by the locality.&#160; <p /></p><p>In an effort to stem the loss of revenue to the State, the Legislature included a measure in the State budget passed April 1, 2013 which will impose a $25.00 surcharge on speeding tickets that are pleaded down to a parking offense. This will make the overall cost somewhat greater for the fine payable for bargained-for parking violation. However, despite the increased costs, this outcome remains a far better disposition than a guilty plea to a speeding violation because it avoids points on a driver&#8217;s license, increased insurance premiums and possible NYSDMV assessments.<p /></p><p>Motorists charged with speeding tickets and other traffic offenses in a Suffolk County court can contact our office and receive a free consultation. Effective legal representation can have a dramatic result on the outcome of a traffic law case.<p /></p><!--more-->The NYS Legislature included a measure in the State budget passed April 1, 2013 which will impose a $25.00 surcharge in certain situations of a plea to&#160;a parking offense.'
