aS'<p>When traveling through the busy highways and roads of California, a driver in Glendale, El Segundo, and Venice Beach can get accustomed to seeing car accidents on the side of the road.  Most of the time, we don&#8217;t think too much of the accidents or their victims; however, this changes when we become the victim of a car accident.  Back injuries are common and painful consequences of car accidents.  \r\n\r\n</p><p>All back injuries should be taken seriously, but many car accident victims do not realize how serious their injuries are immediately as symptoms often take hours or even days to fully develop.  Collision victims often refuse medical evaluation at the site of the accident believing that their soreness is just from stress or inconsequential.  By the next day, inflammation has been allowed to continue and muscles will spasm and seize.  By that time, an opportunity has been missed for the victim to begin evaluation and treatment early, reducing damage.  </p><p>The <a href="http://www.ehlinelaw.com/pages/100221/car-accident-victims.htm">victim of a car crash</a> should take any soreness seriously, seeking evaluation in a clinic or hospital immediately.   Depending upon the first responders to be able to accurately assess the victim&#8217;s condition can be a painful mistake.\r\n\r\nWhen symptoms do begin to appear, they are often very painful and will worsen without treatment.  Upper back injuries are very common as the neck will be whipped back and forth during a collision, straining the muscles of the upper and mid back.  </p><p>Lower back injuries are also common as the body may be twisted violently.  These movements are out of the normal range of motion for the back and often result in strains, sprains, tears, as well as disc injuries and injuries to the delicate nerves contained within the spine.  Inflammation and nerve impingement can result in loss of sensation of the extremities such as the hands and feet, as well as loss of function of remote parts of the body such as the bowels and bladder. \r\n\r\n</p><p>Of course, the most noticeable side-effect of back injuries is the inability to move properly and function as one normally would.  This can have devastating and long-term effects on the personal and work life of a victim if untreated.  If you or your loved one is the victim of back injuries due to a car accident caused by another&#8217;s negligence, a personal injury attorney can help you get the medical treatment and recompense you deserve.\r\n\r\n\r\nThere is a <a href="http://www.ehlinelaw.com/pages/3140/Auto-Accident-Lawyer-LA.htm">Back injuries car accident</a> <a href="http://www.ehlinelaw.com/">personal injury lawyer</a> at Ehline Law Firm PC waiting for your call at 655 North Central Avenue 17th Floor Glendale, CA 91203 USA +818.485.2311.</p><!--more-->Collision victims often refuse medical evaluation at the site of the \r\naccident believing that their soreness is just from stress or \r\ninconsequential.  By the next day, inflammation has been allowed to \r\ncontinue and muscles will spasm and seize.  By that time, an opportunity\r\n has been missed for the victim to begin evaluation and treatment early,\r\n reducing damage.'
