aS'<p><strong>A Portland personal injury lawyer explains</strong><br />When the majority of us think of the word injury we most often visualize harm to a part of the body.&#160;But Portland <a href="http://www.atrlaw.pro/aop/Portland-personal-injury/">personal injury lawyers</a> know how misleading that definition of injury can be. Emotional distress can be just as debilitating and devastating to the life of a person as any physical injury.&#160; Equally as important, it can form the basis for a claim entitling the victim to monetary compensation.<br /><br /><strong>Portland injury lawyers help you collect on your emotional loss</strong><br />You may be wondering how emotional distress is quantified in legal terms.&#160;Although emotions differ from person to person, the law recognizes that certain emotional states have practical consequences.&#160; For instance, a diagnosis of depression from an injury received may make it difficult to go to work, care for your children, or even enjoy your relationship with your spouse.&#160; Emotional injuries can also result in decreased productivity, anxiety attacks, and Post Traumatic Stress Disorder. <br />In addition to the toll these ailments take on your psyche and loved ones, they may also have an impact on your finances.&#160; Treatments for mental illness and conditions can be expensive, in terms of both time and money.&#160; These conditions can impair your ability to work, make new business contacts, or seek appropriate employment.&#160; <br />If you suffer from emotional ailments due to the negligent actions of another person, you deserve to be compensated.&#160; A Portland personal injury lawyer at Ainsworth, Thelin &amp; Raftice, P.A. can discuss the best way to proceed with your case.&#160; Do not feel that because the damage to your body was minimal, or non-existent, that you have not suffered because of an accident.&#160; Contact one of our Portland injury lawyers today to see how we can start alleviating that suffering.<br /><br /><strong>Discuss your case with a Portland personal injury attorney </strong><br />Injured people and their families in Southern Maine rely on the skill and professionalism of the attorneys at Ainsworth Thelin. Contact our team of <a href="http://www.atrlaw.pro/">Portland personal injury attorneys</a>, for a consultation and evaluation of your case at no cost. Call us at 1-866-492-0325, or <a href="http://www.atrlaw.pro/contact-us/">contact us</a> online.</p><!--more-->When the majority of us think of the word injury we most often visualize harm to a part of the body.&#160;But Portland <a href="http://www.atrlaw.pro/aop/Portland-personal-injury/">personal injury lawyers</a> know how misleading that definition of injury can be. Emotional distress can be just as debilitating and devastating to the life of a person as any physical injury.&#160;'
