aS'<p>Accidents are called that for a reason.&#160; They are simply unplanned and often beyond our control. &#160;<u><a title="Trucking accidents" href="http://mccamylaw.com/aop/atlanta-truck-accident-lawyers/" target="&#95;blank">Trucking accidents</a></u> are especially dangerous, no matter the cause.&#160; Sometimes they can be due to issues with roads or highway infrastructure, inclement weather or even by breaking or swerving in an attempt to actually avoid an accident.&#160; However, many accidents are simply caused by driver negligence.</p><p>Truck drivers in particular have the added responsibility of driving a larger and significantly more dangerous vehicle.&#160; If you get in an accident with a car, your odds are pretty good.&#160; If you\'re driving a car and involved in a <b>trucking accident</b>, you are at a greater risk for a serious injury and even death.</p>Some common causes of <u><a title="trucking accidents in Atlanta" href="http://mccamylaw.com/aop/atlanta-truck-accident-lawyers/" target="&#95;blank">trucking accidents in Atlanta</a></u> are aggressive driving, speeding, recklessness such as unsafe lane changing, driver fatigue, equipment failure, or even substance abuse.<ul type="disc"><li><u>Aggressive Truck Driving:</u> Speeding, failure to maintain lane, erratic lane changing or &quot;cutting off&quot; other vehicles, &quot;brake checking&quot; and running other vehicles off of the road are all aggressive driving.</li></ul><p /><ul type="disc"><li><u>Speeding:</u> Trucks weigh far more than the average passenger vehicle.&#160; Combine high weights with high speed, and you simply have a greater force of collision.&#160; A speeding truck can not be slowed or stopped as fast as a car.&#160; </li></ul><p /><ul type="disc"><li>Unsafe Lane<u> Change:</u> An unsafe lane change can be as simple as neglecting to use signal lights, or it can be as reckless as changing into lanes without enough clearance.&#160;&#160; </li></ul><p /><ul type="disc"><li><b><a href="http://www.saferoads.org/issues/fs-truckdriverfatigue.htm">Driver Fatigue</a></b>: In the U.S. truck driver/operator hours of service (HOS) are regulated by the <a href="http://www.fmcsa.dot.gov/">Federal Motor Carrier Safety Administration</a> (FMCSA), but due to deadlines, financial incentives, and unexpected setbacks like traffic jams, trucker drivers often try to &quot;make up lost time&quot; by skipping breaks, resulting in dangerous fatigue.</li></ul><p /><ul type="disc"><li><u>Faulty Equipment/Unsecured Loads:</u> &#160;Serious road traffic accidents can be caused by improperly secured cargo, tire tread separation or zipper rupture, or any number of other equipment malfunctions</li></ul><p /><ul type="disc"><li><u>Substance Abuse:</u> &#160;Substance abuse is growing problem amongst truckers.&#160; Trying to stay awake and alert long hours may cause a truck driver to resort to alcohol or controlled substances. </li></ul><p>If you have been involved in a <u><a title="trucking accidents in Atlanta" href="http://mccamylaw.com/aop/atlanta-truck-accident-lawyers/" target="&#95;blank">trucking accident in Atlanta</a></u>, or its surrounding areas, contact the experienced trucking accident lawyers at our firm.</p><p><strong>McCamy, Phillips, Tuggle &amp; Fordham - <a title="Truck Accident Lawyers in Atlanta" href="http://www.mccamylaw.com/aop/atlanta-truck-accident-lawyers/" target="&#95;blank">Truck Accident Lawyers in Atlanta</a></strong></p><p>300 Waugh Street <br />Dalton, Georgia 30720<br />Toll Free: 1-866-959-9483</p><p /><p /><!--more-->Accidents are called that for a reason.&#160; They are simply unplanned and often beyond our control. &#160;<u><a title="Trucking accidents" href="http://mccamylaw.com/aop/atlanta-truck-accident-lawyers/" target="&#95;blank">Trucking accidents</a></u> are especially dangerous, no matter the cause.&#160; Sometimes they can be due to issues with roads or highway infrastructure, inclement weather or even by breaking or swerving in an attempt to actually avoid an accident.'
