aS'<p class="MsoNormal">\r\nConcord car accidents can result in severe broken bone injuries. The force of a car crash can crush, shatter or snap any one of the body&#8217;s 206 bones. A compound bone fracture injury, which involves an open wound, carries a higher risk of infection due to the exposure of bone and tissue. Bone fractures are also classified as simple. A simple bone fracture injury does not involve trauma to the skin or skin&#8217;s tissue, but can still result in a serious injury. Both compound and simple bone fractures can result in permanent disability, chronic pain and infection. </p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>What is the Difference Between a Bone Fracture and a Broken Bone?</b></p><p class="MsoNormal">Bone fractures and broken bones are one in the same. In fact, according to the Merriam-Webster Dictionary, fracture is defined as &#8220;the act or process of breaking or the state of being broken.&#8221; Bone fractures, or broken bones as they are also called, are a result of a bone not being able to support the energy placed on it.</p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Broken Bone Statistics</b></p><p class="MsoNormal">The National Ambulatory Medical Care Survey and the American Academy of Orthopedic Surgeons has provided the following broken bone statistics:</p><p class="MsoNormal" /><ul><li>More than six million bone fractures occur in the United States each year.</li><li>Broken bone injuries account for approximately three million emergency room visits annually.</li><li>Almost 900,000 bone fracture injuries require hospitalization every year.</li><li>Approximately 60 percent of broken bone injuries occur outside of the home.</li><li>The most common bone fracture for victims under the age of 75 is a wrist fracture. For victims over the age of 75, hip fractures are the most common type of bone\r\nfracture.</li><li>In the U.S., men are more likely to experience a broken bone injury than women.</li></ul><p /><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Recovering Compensation for a Concord Broken Bone Injury</b></p><p class="MsoNormal">If you suffered a broke bone injury in a car collision, you may be able to receive help for damages associated with the accident. Before collecting money for damages, you must prove that your injuries were caused by the negligent or reckless actions of another person. Defense attorneys may try to shift blame onto you, making it harder for you to establish fault. An aggressive <a href="http://www.concordcaraccidents.com/">Concord car accident attorney </a>will work diligently on your behalf to prove your injuries were cause by another party&#8217;s negligent actions and prove you deserve compensation for medical bills, lost earnings, physical pain, emotional distress and any other expense associated with the crash.</p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Talk to a Concord Personal Injury Lawyer</b></p><p class="MsoNormal">Before you talk to anyone about your accident, talk to a competent <a href="http://www.esteyandbomberger.com/">northern California personal injury lawyer</a>. By making one phone call, you can ensure your legal right to maximum financial damages is protected. Almost all personal injury lawyers will offer you a free case review and take your case on a no recovery, no fee basis.&#160;</p><!--more-->Concord car accidents can result in severe broken bone injuries. The\r\nforce of a car crash can crush, shatter or snap any one of the body&#8217;s 206 bones.'
