aS'When children are injured at school , the school can be liable for the child&#8217;s injuries.&#160; Because of laws set in place to protect government and quasi-governmental entities, any claim being raised against a school must comply with the notice of claim statute.&#160; When an individual has a claim against such an entity, the law requires that the entity receive timely notice regarding the claim and damages.&#160; Notices of claim are best prepared by attorneys.'
