aS'<p dir="ltr">There are many auto accidents that could take place because of defective tires, sometimes it takes a car accident lawyer to not only point out what are the main causes the accident that the victim have fallen into, but to go even more in depth to be able to identify the how the tire is defective if it was the cause of the accident. The same requirement is also expected from motorcycle accident attorneys and truck accident lawyers likewise. Car accident lawyers not only serve to be a personal injury lawyer to file claims on behalf of their client, but their experience and vast knowledge in the field of automobile will allow an effective lawsuit to be filed.</p><p dir="ltr" /><p dir="ltr">In the midst of anger or rage, clients might point their fingers to the manufacturers after theyve met with an accident that was caused by defective tire. This is a grieve mistake as they first have to realize that there are many factors that contribute to the defect of tires, other than the usual manufacturing fault. Theres a list that is compiled to ease clients in better understanding the different defects of tires that are found and the relevant parties involved.</p><p dir="ltr" /><p dir="ltr">Old tires Tires that are kept for a long time could start deteriorating, even without being used. Retailers could misinform their buyers and have old tires sold to them as new ones, but lawyers are able to run extensive checks and gather relevant information on the age of the tire.</p><p dir="ltr" /><p dir="ltr">Tread separation The defect has been placed under the medias spotlight with manufacturers recalling the defective tires. During a tread separation, where the main rubber frame is separated from the actual steel belt that holds it in place. This often leads to a blowout, where drivers lose control of the car and could lead to fatal accident. In the manufacturing process, improper supervision of work or inspections could have caused the tire to be distributed with defect.</p><p dir="ltr" /><p dir="ltr">Incompatible tires Tires might not have defects themselves, but if theyre incompatible with the vehicle, it could bring about equally detrimental accidents that arise from tire defects. Along the assembly line, there could many errors that could be made when strict regulations arent adhered. Car accident lawyers will be able to determine if the accident was caused by the installation of incompatible tires.</p><p dir="ltr" /><p dir="ltr">After identifying the relevant parties that could be responsible for the tire defect, victims are able to file claims to seek compensation. Either to cover medical cost or property damage, an effective lawsuit could take place after discussions are made with a personal injury lawyer. Inquiry about necessary proceedings and the relevant details that should be given could be made so that the lawsuit could be filed with little delay from the time of accident.</p><b><p dir="ltr">Law Offices of Ledger &amp; Associates<br />811 Wilshire Blvd<br />Suite 1000<br />Los Angeles, CA 90017<br />Office: 213-493-6588<br />Toll Free 800-300-0001<br />Website: <a href="http://www.ledgerlaw.com/">www.ledgerlaw.com</a></p></b>'
