aS'<br /><p>Automobile, motorcycle and truck crashes occur every day in Oklahoma City and the surrounding areas. With major highways such as Interstate 35 and Interstate 40 passing through Oklahoma, traffic accidents are a major cause of personal injuries in the state. When an accident occurs, many people do not know how to properly handle it, especially if they are injured. An Oklahoma City personal injury attorney can provide the information and insight you need to make the best possible decisions in your difficult legal situation.</p><p><a href="http://oklegal.onenet.net/oklegal-cgi/get&#95;statute?99/Title.12/12-95.html" target="&#95;blank">Oklahoma law</a> provides that you have two years to bring your personal injury cause of action. However, the quicker you take action, the better for preserving evidence and the likelihood of your success.</p><p><strong>Steps to take after an accident</strong><br />When you are involved in an auto accident or some other type of accident resulting in a personal injury, it can be confusing and overwhelming. While you may not realize it, you are most likely in a state of shock. Below are a few simple steps for what to do after a wreck or other accident:</p><ul><li>Obtain medical treatment as soon as possible, which may include calling an ambulance to the scene.</li><li>Call the police and, if possible and safe, wait at the scene of the accident for them to appear.</li><li>Tell the police officer(s) exactly how the accident occurred.</li><li>Obtain the other driver\'s insurance information. If possible, take a picture of their insurance verification card.</li><li>Be careful what you say to the other driver and try to keep conversation to a minimum. You don\'t want to say something that can be used against you later.</li><li>If you have a camera in your car or on your smart phone, take pictures of the accident scene and damage to both vehicles (or as soon as practically possible). Remember to take close-up pictures and from a variety of angles.</li><li>Contact your insurance company immediately to report the accident.</li><li>DO NOT talk with anyone who calls you from the other driver\'s insurance company.</li><li>Contact an <a href="http://www.kanelopouloslaw.com/practice-areas/personal-injury/" target="&#95;blank">Oklahoma City personal injury attorney</a> immediately if you were injured or suffered property damage in the accident.</li><li>Keep records of all of your medical treatment.</li></ul><p><strong>Discuss your case with an experienced personal injury lawyer in Oklahoma</strong><br />The attorneys at <a href="http://www.kanelopouloslaw.com/" target="&#95;blank">Kanelopoulos Law Firm</a> work closely with individuals and families dealing with the consequences of an accident, injury or fatality. Our goal is to provide you with information and guidance to secure an adequate financial recovery so that you can heal and move on with your life. Our lawyers are available for home and hospital visits if your injuries make it difficult for you to meet with us in our Oklahoma City offices. We offer a free initial consultation.</p><p><strong>Kanelopoulos Law Firm<br />4549 NW 36th Street<br />Oklahoma City, Oklahoma 73122</strong></p><!--more-->An auto accident can be overwhelming, especially if you are injured. Following a few important steps after your accident can help protect your right to recovery for damages suffered. The attorneys at the Kanelopoulos Law Firm in Oklahoma City are prepared and fully equipped to assist you.'
