aS'<p><a href="http://www.freddry.com/" target="&#95;blank">Chicago Criminal Attorney</a>, Fred Mark Dry,&#160;describes the current DUI conviction penalties in Illinois.<br /><br />First DUI conviction</p><ul><li>Loss of full driving privileges for a minimum of one (1) year.</li><li>Possible imprisonment for up to&#160;364 days.</li><li>Maximum fine of $2,500.</li></ul><p>Second DUI Conviction</p><ul><li>Minimum five (5) year loss of full driving privileges for a second conviction within a twenty (20) year period.</li><li>Mandatory five (5) days in jail or thirty (30) days community service for a second conviction.</li><li>Possible imprisonment for up to one (1) year.</li><li>Maximum fine of $2,500.</li></ul><p>Third DUI Conviction - Class 4 felony</p><ul><li>Loss of full driving privileges for a minimum of (10)&#160;years.</li><li>Possible imprisonment for up to three (3) years.</li><li>Maximum fine of $10,000.</li></ul><p>If you have been involved in a <a href="http://www.freddry.com/aop/Chicago-dui-dwi/" target="&#95;blank">Chicago DUI</a> arrest, please contact attorney Fred Mark Dry to review your case.</p><p>Fred Mark Dry<br />203 North LaSalle Street<br />Suite # 2100 <br />Chicago, IL 60601<br />Phone: 866-935-0295</p><!--more--><p><br /><a href="http://www.freddry.com/" target="&#95;blank">Chicago Criminal Lawyer</a>, Fred Mark Dry,&#160;describes the current DUI conviction penalties in Illinois.&#160; Including first, second, &amp; third DUI conviction penalties.&#160; These penalties can be discouraging.&#160; It\'s&#160;very&#160;important you speak with an experienced attorney right away.</p>'
