aS'<p MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt" /><p MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt">If you are a victim of personal injury, it might be possible for you to receive financial compensation from the negligent party.&#160; However, this does not mean that every personal injury case has grounds for a lawsuit.&#160; </p><i>Personal injury settlements</i><p MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt">There is no need to file a lawsuit if a personal injury victim and the opposing party reach a settlement outside of civil court.&#160; A settlement is an agreement in which the plaintiff ceases to pursue legal action against the defendant in exchange for an agreed upon amount of money.</p><p MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt">The benefits of injury settlements include the following:</p><p class="ListParagraphCxSpFirst" TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in">?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; It is cheaper and faster than the lawsuit process</p><p class="ListParagraphCxSpLast" MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in">?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; You and your attorney can construct the settlement to compensate for your injury or to capitalize on tax benefits</p><p MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt">Always consult your attorney before agreeing to a settlement as it is possible that the sum you are offered is lower than what you are entitled to.</p><p MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><b><i>For help with a San Diego personal injury lawsuit</i></b></p><p MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt">If you cannot contact the defendant, or if they are unwilling to settle, your attorney might suggest filing a lawsuit.&#160; During the proceedings of a lawsuit, your lawyer will try to prove your case by showing that the defendant was careless and that this carelessness harmed the plaintiff.</p><p MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt">You will need to take the following steps in order to file a lawsuit:</p><p class="ListParagraphCxSpFirst" TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in">?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; <b>Gather documentation:</b> Collect medical bills and employment records that demonstrate income lost due to your injury.</p><p class="ListParagraphCxSpMiddle" TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in">?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; <b>Collect evidence:</b> Gather evidence that supports your version of what happened, such as photographs, statements from witnesses, and police reports.</p><p class="ListParagraphCxSpMiddle" TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in">?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; <b>Draft your complaint.</b>&#160; This document describes the facts of your accident and provides a summary of your injuries.</p><p class="ListParagraphCxSpLast" MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in">?&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; <b>File your complaint.</b> Finally, you need to file your complaint at the courthouse in the county where your accident occurred.</p><p MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt">After you file, you need to serve a Summons and a copy of the Complaint to the negligent party.&#160; A Summons is a legal document informing the defendants that you filed a lawsuit against them.</p><p><strong>The most important thing you can do after you are injured is to contact a personal injury attorney.&#160; Your attorney should be thoroughly knowledgeable in state laws regarding settlements and lawsuits.</strong></p><p><strong>The attorneys at <strong>The Hoey Law Firm</strong> have successfully handled many <a href="http://www.hoeyfirm.com/cases/">San Diego personal injury lawsuits</a>, some of which won our clients millions of dollars.&#160; Contact The Hoey Law Firm today</strong>.&#160; We look forward to working with you.</p><p MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt">The Hoey Law Firm | 11975 El Camino Real, Suite 150 | San Diego, CA 92037</p><!--more--><p MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt">If you are a victim of personal injury, it might be possible for you to receive financial compensation from the negligent party.&#160; However, this does not mean that every personal injury case has grounds for a lawsuit.&#160; </p>'
