aS'<p class="MsoNormal">As a motorcyclist there are a number of freedoms that come with transportation that other commuters don\'t receive.&#160;&#160; In California, motorcycle riders can often be seen splitting lanes and zipping through traffic.&#160; Their gas costs are minimal and parking is usually not an issue.&#160; These freedoms do not come without a cost, however.&#160; As any <a href="http://www.bestattorney.com/california-motorcycle-accident-lawyers.html">California motorcycle accident lawyer</a> can tell you, operating a motorcycle leaves the motorist exposed to dangers that automobile owners take for granted.&#160; <br /><br />When riding a motorcycle you leave yourself vulnerable to all the elements around you.&#160; The biggest danger that a motorcyclist will face are visionary hazards.&#160; A number of motorcycle accidents continue to occur year after year because the driver of the automobile that hit the motorcycle did not see them.&#160; Wearing a reflective vest, driving a bright colored motorcycle and using your daytime headlight are all some of the ways you can help other drivers to see your vehicle before it\'s too late.<b></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b></b><b>Other Factors That Could Cause Your Motorcycle Accident</b><b></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b></b>Some of the other dangers that could cause a motorcycle accident include dangerous roads, insufficient riding skills, distracted or intoxicated drivers and defective motorcycles.&#160; <b><br /><br />Dangerous Roadways </b>have plagued a number of roads from city streets to rural highways. For a number of vehicles on the road, potholes, small debris, oil slicks and uneven pavement are minor obstacles.&#160; If these obstacles go unattended by city, county or state officials they could cause serious or fatal injuries to those who operate a motorcycle.&#160; <b><br /><br />Distracted or intoxicated drivers </b>can easily miss a motorcyclist, making a quick lane change that could result in a serious motorcycle accident.<br /><br />Once involved in a <a href="http://california-lawyer-attorney.com/california-motorcycle-accident-lawyers.html">motorcycle accident in California</a> it is important that you are aware of your rights as an injured victim.&#160; To find out you will need to consult with a knowledgeable California motorcycle accident attorney who can help you receive a maximum recovery.<b></b><br />This Article was brought to you by<b><br /><br />Bisnar &amp; Chase Personal Injury Attorneys</b>1301 Dove Street, Suite 120<br />Newport Beach, CA 92660<br /><a href="http://www.bestattorney.com">www.bestattorney.com</a><br />949-203-3814<b></b><br />and<b><br /><br />Bisnar &amp; Chase Personal Injury Attorneys</b>1111 S Grand Ave, Suite 101, <br />Los Angeles, CA 90015<br /><a href="http://www.bestattorney.com">www.bestattorney.com</a><br />323-238-4683</p><!--more-->As a motorcyclist there are a \r\nnumber of freedoms that come with transportation that other commuters \r\ndon\'t receive.&#160;&#160; In California, motorcycle riders can often be seen \r\nsplitting lanes and zipping through traffic.&#160; Their gas costs are \r\nminimal and parking is usually not an issue.&#160; These freedoms do not come\r\n without a cost.'
