aS'<p>Over the years, many myths, urban legends, and rumors have spread regarding <a href="http://www.visitnc.com/" target="&#95;blank">North Carolina</a>, including <a href="http://www.jnl-law.com/aop/Raleigh-workers-compensation/">Raleigh worker compensation laws</a>.&#160; Such stories and half truths can lead people to file workers compensation claims in Raleigh that have no chance of success, or to not file such claims when they are legally entitled to compensation.</p><p>This page addresses some, but not all, myths regarding workers comp law.&#160; If you have additional questions regarding a potential workers compensation claim, contact an experienced workers comp lawyer in Raleigh such as those at the Levy Law Offices.</p><ul><li><u>I did not immediately report my injury, so I cannot file a </u><a href="http://www.jnl-law.com/aop/Raleigh-workers-compensation/laws/">workers comp claim in Raleigh</a><u>.</u></li></ul><p>You have up to 30 days to report a workplace injury or job-related illness to your employer.&#160; A claim may be filed with the North Carolina Industrial Commission for up to two years following the date of the injury.&#160; If this timeframe expires, you may still have options for filing under workers compensation law, especially if asbestos or toxic exposure is involved.&#160; </p><ul><li><u>Can I see my own doctor?</u></li></ul><p>Yes, but if your employer maintains a list of approved doctors and your doctor is not one of them, your employer can wait some time before paying any of your bills.&#160; A Raleigh workers compensation law attorney can tell you more about this.<br />Independent contractors cannot make a worker comp claim in Raleigh<br />Independent contractors may, under certain circumstances, be considered employees, subject to the same rights as full-time workers.&#160; It is best you consult an attorney to find out if your injury is eligible for a workers compensation claim.</p><ul><li><u>I cannot afford a Raleigh worker comp lawyer</u></li></ul><p>Raleigh workers comp attorneys are limited regarding the fees they may collect.&#160; While you are free to represent yourself in any legal action, your employer and their insurance company will most certainly have professional attorneys representing them.&#160; </p><p>My Raleigh workers comp claim is legitimate, so my employer will just pay me<br />Some employers may deny any worker compensation claim in Raleigh out of hand in the hope that you will give up and go away.&#160; You should always expect some resistance, especially at first.&#160; One way to prove you are serious, and perhaps earn more respect from your employer, is to retain an experienced Raleigh workers compensation attorney to handle your initial filings.</p><ul><li><u>I have no further recourse if my Raleigh worker compensation claim is denied</u></li></ul><p>This is absolutely not true.&#160; There are several options for additional petitions, hearings, and appeals.&#160; </p><p>Contact Levy Law Offices for help filing a workers compensation claim in Raleigh<br />If you require legal help regarding a workers compensation settlement in Raleigh, contact the Levy Law Offices today.&#160; Levy Law Offices employs experienced Raleigh workers compensation lawyers and provides a free initial consultation in workers\' compensation cases. Like other workers compensation law firms, we typically handle these cases on a contingency fee basis.</p><p>Levy Law Offices<br />140-B Wind Chime Court<br />Raleigh, NC 27615</p><!--more-->Joshua Levy addresses some&#160;myths regarding <a href="http://www.jnl-law.com/aop/Raleigh-workers-compensation/laws/">Raleigh workers comp law</a>. Such stories and half truths can lead people to file workers compensation claims in Raleigh that have no chance of success, or to not file such claims when they are legally entitled to compensation.'
