aS'<p>The federal government has been required for several years now to \r\nprovide annual reports with regards to the status of bankruptcy filings \r\nin the United States after the new bankruptcy laws were passed by \r\nCongress in 2005.&#160; As such, the reporting office has released its annual\r\n report that relates to the calendar year of 2011, and one of the \r\naspects of this divorce dealt with the progress of people who had filed \r\ncases under Chapter 13 of the United States Bankruptcy Code.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>According to this report, more than 185,000 <a href="http://www.goldenstatelawgroup.com/helping-you-end-your-stress-chapter-13-bankruptcy-lawyers-san-diego.html" title="Chapter 13 bankruptcy">Chapter 13 bankruptcy</a>\r\n cases were dismissed during 2011 by the courts.&#160; When a case is \r\ndismissed it&#8217;s because the court finds that the payment plan as part of \r\nthe case should not continue.&#160; More troubling was the fact that 48 \r\npercent of these cases that were dismissed reached this conclusion in \r\nthe court system because the debtor was not remaining current with the \r\npayment plan that was agreed upon originally.</p>\r\n<p>When a Chapter 13 bankruptcy case is dismissed, it can remove the \r\nAutomatic Stay that prevents creditors from resuming collection \r\nefforts.&#160; Such a development can also lead to the foreclosure of loans \r\nthat were saved by the filing and other serious issues.&#160; Ultimately, the\r\n creditor can re-file the case, but he or she may basically have to \r\nstart all over again.</p>\r\nSan Diego Bankruptcy Lawyers\r\n<p>There are several reasons that someone may choose a Chapter 13 \r\nbankruptcy filing, and there are also cases where a debtor may be \r\nrequired to file a case under this chapter so that some of the existing \r\ndebts can be repaid during the course of a repayment plan.&#160; However, \r\npeople who are operating under such a plan need to be proactive if they \r\nrun into trouble down the road.</p>\r\n<p>If you are experiencing serious financial problems and you need to put an end to them, seek the help of <a href="http://www.goldenstatelawgroup.com/bankruptcy-overview-bankruptcy-attorneys-san-diego.html" title="San Diego bankruptcy lawyers">San Diego bankruptcy lawyers</a> who have been helping consumers and businesses regain their financial health for many years.&#160; Contact the <strong>Golden State Law Group</strong> today to schedule a free initial consultation.</p><!--more-->If you are experiencing serious financial problems and you need to put an end to them, seek the help of San Diego bankruptcy lawyers who have been helping consumers and businesses regain their financial health for many years.&#160; Contact the Golden State Law Group today to schedule a free initial consultation.'
