aS'<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n\r\n</p><p class="MsoNormal">While trains are equated with slow, lazy trips along the countryside, they are actually high speed accidents waiting to happen.&#160; Commuter and commercial trains are zig zagging across the country every minute of every day, transporting goods and people at increasingly high speeds and they have become more and more dangerous over the years.&#160; In fact, since the 1990&#8217;s, the numbers of train accidents have been steadily increasing and unfortunately, trains cause about 1,000 fatalities every year and countless more train and railroad personal injuries great and small.&#160; Train accidents come in all shapes and sizes &#8211; conductor error due to sleep deprivation, collisions with vehicles at crossings, trains jumping the tracks and causing personal or property damage, chemical spills, explosions, bridge failure and on and on and on.&#160;\r\n\r\nIs you have suffered any form of train or railroad accidents or personal injury from a train accident, there are extremely experienced train and railroad personal injury law firms ready, willing and able to represent you. Train and railroad personal injury law attorneys will guarantee that your claim is prosecuted to the full extent of the law, that all parties (whether it the train company, a vendor, a municipality or any other responsible party) are appropriately attached to the train and railroad accident law suit and that you or your family are compensated fully.&#160; Keep in mind that not all train accidents are catastrophic and result in the loss of life.&#160; Many, many of the cases prosecuted by train and railroad accident lawyers involve local subways, commuter rails, train collisions with cars/trucks and even personal injuries that occur during a ride on a train.\r\n\r\n</p>  <p class="MsoNormal">It is never a good idea to try and do it yourself when dealing with a train or railroad accident.&#160; If you can answer &#8220;yes&#8221;, &#8220;ma