aS'<p>You must take many issues into consideration when filing for divorce in Santa Barbara.&#160; The first thing you should do is consult an attorney who specializes in matrimonial law.&#160; An experienced family law attorney can explain the different types of divorce proceedings and help determine what is right for you.&#160; Once you understand all of your options, your attorney helps you through the process and ensures that your divorce resolves in a satisfactory and equitable agreement.&#160; </p><p><strong>Types of divorce processes </strong>A variety of divorce processes are available to you when you are divorcing in Santa Barbara: </p><ul><li>Separation.&#160; A legal separation is not the same as a divorce.&#160; In a separation, you will agree on terms for division of property and child custody, but the marriage is not legally dissolved and the parties may not remarry.</li><li>Mediation.&#160; Divorce mediation is a process by which the divorcing parties reach an agreement outside of court in a series of meetings facilitated by a neutral mediator.&#160; Mediation gives the parties the opportunity to work out the terms of their divorce on their own instead of being bound by the ruling of the court.</li><li>Collaborative divorce.&#160; Like mediation, collaborative divorce is an alternative to a court proceeding.&#160; In a collaborative divorce, the parties and their attorneys work together to reach an equitable settlement that is in the best interests of everyone involved.&#160; Collaborative divorce emphasizes communication and often incorporates the input of experts such as financial consultants and child specialists.&#160; If you pursue a collaborative divorce, it is best to have an attorney who is specially trained in collaborative family law.</li><li>Litigation.&#160; In cases where a divorce is contested and the parties cannot reach an agreement on their own, the divorce will ultimately be resolved in a courtroom.&#160; In litigation, the judge decrees the final divorce agreement and outlines all the terms, including child support, spousal support, and division of property.</li></ul><p>An experienced family law attorney can tell you more about the different types of divorce proceedings and will help you determine what is the most appropriate course of action based on your situation.</p><p><strong>Contact a Santa Barbara divorce attorney</strong>Finding the right family law and estate planning attorney is not always easy, but it is important. Contact the experienced <a href="http://www.wilsonpettine.com/">Santa Barbara divorce attorneys</a> at Wilson &amp; Pettine, LLP to learn how they can help you through your family law matter, will and trust needs, or civil litigation case.</p><p>Conveniently located one block from the <a href="http://www.sbcourts.org/index.asp">Santa Barbara County Courthouse</a>, Wilson &amp; Pettine, LLP represents clients throughout Santa Barbara and the neighboring area, including Carpinteria, Montecito, Goleta, and Summerland. </p>'
