aS'<p>If you are seriously injured, get to the hospital as soon as possible.&#160; But if you are not seriously injured, try to regain your composure and take as many of the following steps as possible:</p><p>- Collect the contact information of witnesses.<br />- Take pictures of the wreck with your cell phone or camera.<br />- Take pictures of road conditions to document weather or other hazards.<br />- Take notes about important details, including what the other driver or witnesses say.<br />- Make sure that the police are called and that they write an accident report.<br />- Call your auto insurance agent.<br />- Do not say anything that in any way implies you were at fault.<br />- Do not sign any legal documents, such as waivers or releases.<br />- Seek medical attention immediately for any pain or injury caused by the accident, even if it does not feel serious.</p><p><strong>Contact us today</strong></p><p>If you or a loved one suffered a physical or mental injury resulting from a car crash, you may be able to recover money damages.&#160; The <a href="http://www.rubensteinandrynecki.com/">New York&#160;personal injury attorneys</a>&#160;of the Brooklyn-based law firm of Rubenstein&amp; Rynecki have decades of legal experience representing accident victims in tough negotiations and some of the highest profile trials in New York.&#160; Let us fight for you.&#160; If there is no recovery, there is no fee.&#160; For a free consultation, call us at 800-447-HURT or 718-522-1020.</p>'
