e likely to be able to make a better choice.</p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" /><p>&#160;</p><p /><p class="MsoNormal">To find out more about the reputation of your prospective lawyer within the legal community of your area, you can also try checking with the local legal agencies. You will be more comfortable engaging the services of the personal injury lawyer if he or she has a good reputation amongst their peers. It also helps to ask for professional references from the attorney prior to making any decision. This is because it is important for a good personal injury lawyer to have multiple positive references as well as good reputation, so that satisfactory settlements can be achieved.</p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" /><p>&#160;</p><p /><p class="MsoNormal">The charges of the lawyer should also be taken into consideration. It is better to find out the charges, to avoid facing exorbitant charges after you have signed a contract.</p><p /><p /><p>Ledger&#160;Law Firm<br />811 Wilshire Blvd<br />Suite 1000<br />Los Angeles, CA 90017<br />Office: 213-493-6588<br />Toll Free 800-300-0001<br />Website: <a href="http://www.ledgerlaw.com/">www.ledgerlaw.com</a></p><p /></div>'
