aS'<p class="MsoNormal">Top Corporate Fundraising Team at Detroit Walk Like MADD Event</p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" /><p class="MsoNormal">The <b><a href="http://www.buckfirelaw.com/">Michigan personal injury lawyers</a></b> of Buckfire &amp; Buckfire, P.C. announced it raised over $2,700 for Mothers Against Drunk Driving (MADD) at the 5K Walk Like MADD event in Troy, MI on Saturday, April 2, 2011. Team Buckfire &amp; Buckfire was the top corporate fundraising team at the event, generating the most money of all the participating walk teams, raising a total amount of $2,750. Awards were also given out by MADD to top individuals who raised the most money. Attorneys Daniel Buckfire, Larry Buckfire, and Robert Lantzy were all recognized for their efforts. Daniel Buckfire raised a total of $950.00. Larry Buckfire raised a total of $785 and Robert Lantzy raised a total of $580.</p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" /><p>&#160;</p><p /><p class="MsoNormal">In addition to raising funds through the 5K walk team, Buckfire &amp; Buckfire is State of Michigan Sponsor of MADD, donating $20,000 to the MADD organization. The money will be used towards MADD mission to stop drunk driving, support the victims of this violent crime and prevent underage drinking. The law firm specializes in <b><a title="Michigan car accident lawsuits" href="http://www.buckfirelaw.com/practice&#95;areas/michigan-auto-accident-attorney-best-michigan-car-accident-lawyers.cfm" target="&#95;blank">Michigan car accident lawsuits</a></b>.</p><p /><p class="MsoNormal"><b></b><p /><p class="MsoNormal">&#8220;We believe that investing in our community not only improves the lives of our friends and neighbors, but it also enriches our own lives and makes us better lawyers,&#8221; says Attorney and Partner Larry Buckfire.</p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" /><p>&#160;</p><p /><p class="MsoNormal">What&#8217;s more, since many victims of Michigan drunk driver accidents do not understand their legal rights, Buckfire &amp; Buckfire 