aS'<p>Last month, a Lowell Superior Court jury awarded a plaintiff 2.25 million in a motor vehicle injury case.&#160; </p><p /><p>First, it shows that there are juries who will award substantial damages in a motor vehicle cases in Massachusetts, although such juries are rare these days.&#160; </p><p /><p>Second, it shows that juries are becoming aware that even seemingly minor car accidents and a minor head injury can seriously damage victims.</p><p /><p>In this case, after a rear end accident, the victim was diagnosed with minor traumatic head injury and suffered memory loss, loss of concentration and speech problems. </p><p /><p>Many juries would probably been tempted to accept the insurance company&#8217;s contention that the accident and such a minor head trauma could cause such large problems.&#160; Insurance industry propaganda wants us all to believe that anyone who files an insurance claim is trying to get something they are not entitled to; fortunately this jury saw through the same old insurance company defense and compensated this woman for the severe long-lasting impact on her life.</p><p /><p>If you are in need of a&#160;<a href="http://whitmanlaw.com/aop/massachusetts-injury-lawyer/massachusetts-injury-lawyer1/">Massachusetts personal injury attorney</a>&#160;in any areas including Boston, Brockton, Waltham, Burlington, Woburn, Lynn, Lowell, Malden, Medford, Watertown, and Worcester, please do not hesitate to contact Whitman Law. We look forward to hearing from you.</p><p>Protect your legal rights. Get the <em><b>Whitman Advantage</b></em> today.</p><!--more-->If you are in need of a Massachusetts personal injury attorney&#160;in any areas including Boston, Brockton, Waltham, Burlington, Woburn, Lynn, Lowell, Malden, Medford, Watertown, and Worcester, please do not hesitate to contact Whitman Law. We look forward to hearing from you.'
