aS'<p>Divorce can be very hard on your children. We trust that you are seeking the course of action you feel is best for your child, and we fight to enforce your position.&#160; </p><p><b>Des Moines temporary child custody</b></p><p>Before your divorce is final in Des Moines, temporary child custody may be a step worth considering, especially if your spouse does not honor your custody agreement in Des Moines.</p><p><b>Des Moines child support</b></p><p>The Iowa court may order the non-custodial parent to pay an amount that is reasonable and necessary for supporting a child. The court considers:</p><ul type="disc"><li>The responsibility of both parents to support and provide for the welfare of the minor child</li><li>The child\'s need for a close relationship with both parents</li></ul><p>However, the judge is also expected to follow the child support guidelines established by the <a href="http://www.iowacourtsonline.org/Supreme&#95;Court/" target="&#95;blank">Iowa Supreme Court</a>. A judge must follow these guidelines unless doing so would be unjust or inappropriate. This is where Hope Law Firm, PLC comes in. We work to ensure that the child support order is appropriate for your personal situation and for the proper care of your child.</p><p><b>Joint child custody in Des Moines </b></p><p>In Des Moines, joint custody means that both parents have legal custodial rights and responsibilities.&#160;Shared <a href="http://www.thedesmoinesdivorcelawyer.com/Child-Support-&-Custody/" target="&#95;blank">custody in Des Moines</a> have the best rate of success if both parents are capable of working together to do what is best for the child.</p><p>Both parents have joint custody and share parenting time. In a Des Moines shared custody arrangement, a judge has granted both the mother and father custody. When establishing the custody arrangement that is best for the child, the court&#8217;s considerations include: </p><ul type="disc"><li>The suitability of each parent to be a custodian</li><li>The psychological and emotional development of the child</li><li>The parents&#8217; ability to communicate with each other about the child</li><li>Each parent&#8217;s level of care for the child before and since the separation</li><li>Whether each parent can support the other\'s relationship with the child</li><li>The child&#8217;s wishes, taking into account the child\'s age and maturity</li><li>Whether the parents agree to joint custody</li><li>The geographic proximity of the parents</li><li>The safety of the child or the other parent</li></ul><p>In Iowa, parents must attend a course about the effect of divorce on children within 45 days of the custody order.</p><p><b>We take legal action to protect your child</b></p><p>You know what is best for your children, and we know how to work with you to achieve your goals. Contact <a href="http://www.thedesmoinesdivorcelawyer.com/" target="&#95;blank">Des Moines child custody attorneys</a> at Hope Law Firm, PLC.</p><p>Hope Law Firm, PLC<br />317 6th Avenue<br />Des Moines, IA 50309<br />(515) 255-3559</p><!--more-->Divorce can be very hard on your children. We trust that you are seeking the course of action you feel is best for your child, and we fight to enforce your position. Before your divorce is final in Des Moines, temporary child custody may be a step worth considering, especially if your spouse does not honor your custody agreement in Des Moines.'
