aS'<p>Many times we get call here at William Muhr attorneys from a victim indicating that they were in a <a href="http://www.williammuhr.com/">Denver auto accident</a>, but\r\nthe accident may have occurred several months ago. With all of the potential\r\ncomplications surrounding an auto accident, including fixing your car, getting\r\nit towed, getting a rental, getting to work, etc, many people forget to take\r\ncare of themselves because they do not believe they have an injury.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Everyone will get into a car accident at some point in their life. If you\r\nlive in Denver you are especially prone, because Denver is rated as having one\r\nof top three worst driving conditions of all the cities in the US. (Probably\r\nbecause so many people move here from places that do not have snow, and the\r\nfact that while most of the time road conditions are pretty good-when they get\r\nbad they get bad fast and messy in the Denver area) In the Denver area alone,\r\nthis means that approximately 5,860 people will be rear ended in 2010. Everyone\r\nresponds differently to be being rear-ended, but most likely you will be\r\ninjured due to the unique set of forces that the occupant is exposed to in a\r\nDenver auto accident. Whiplash type problems became commonplace with the\r\nintroduction of the train. The quick force of a sudden start or stop tears\r\nthrough muscles, ligaments, tendons, the joint capsule, nervous tissue, and\r\nsometimes even bone. You can be injured even though no damage is shown on your\r\ncar, in fact, it is well known that vehicle damage has no correlation to\r\noccupant injury. If you are ever involved in an auto accident, here is some information\r\nthat will help you get through the stress of dealing with the situation:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Check for injuries, at hesitate to call an ambulance when in doubt.<br />\r\n2. Call 911-don&#8217;t rush past or let someone talk you out of calling 911.<br />\r\n3. Take photographs of the scene-another valuable reason to have an iPhone or\r\nother camera phone.<br />\r\n4. Whatever you do, do not leave the scene before the police arrive.<br />\r\n5. Move cars to a safe place so that you and other drivers are safe.<br />\r\n6. Make notes about specifics of the accident. Where and how did it happen,\r\nwhat is the damage to the cars, etc.<br />\r\n7. Get the other drivers information. Name, vehicle make and model, insurance\r\ninfo,<br />\r\n8. Get information from witnesses-if they will let you-why not use the video\r\ncamera on your phone?<br />\r\n9. If you are injured, and not in need of an emergency room visit. Schedule an\r\nappointment with a doctor that is familiarwith auto accidents.<br />\r\n10. You might need to consult a <a href="http://www.williammuhr.com/cases/practice-area/denver-car-accident-lawyers/">Denver auto accident attorney</a>-one who deals\r\nspecifically with Denver auto accidents.<br />\r\n11. Other than the police; do not make statement to anyone.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&#160;\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>The William Muhr Attorneys and Counselors at Law have been\r\nwinning millions for their clients since 1988.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b>Contact an expert Denver auto accident attorney &#160;today: &#160;Call 800-934-4529 to speak with an auto\r\naccident attorney immediately for expert advice.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p /><div border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 0pt; padding: 0pt; display: none; opacity: 0.9; position: absolute; width: auto; z-index: 99999;" id="seolinx-tooltip"><div margin: 0pt; padding: 0pt; overflow: auto; width: auto;">&#160;PR: <a href="javascript:{}" title="Google pagerank" seolinx-type="param" seolinx-param-index="0" color: blue; font-family: Tahoma; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">wait...</a>&#160;I: <a href="javascript:{}" title="Google index" seolinx-type="param" seolinx-param-index="1" color: blue; font-family: Tahoma; font-size: 7pt; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: