aS'<p class="MsoNormal">\r\n<b>Q. I&#8217;ve had to take time off work due to my motorcycle accident injuries. Can I get reimbursed for the wages I have lost while recovering from my injuries?</b></p><p class="MsoNormal">A. Possibly. If it is determined that you were not at-fault for the motorcycle accident, you may be able to pursue compensation for lost wages from the at-fault party. If the accident was caused through no fault of your own, you may also be able to recover compensation for medical care costs, caregiving services, occupational rehabilitation, physical therapy, physical pain, disability, diminished quality of life, and emotional suffering.</p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Q. Why is an investigation of my case so important?</b></p><p class="MsoNormal">A. A prompt and thorough investigation of your case is important for several reasons. One reason why an investigation should be conducted immediately is the preservation of evidence. Insurance companies typically have an investigator on the scene of an accident within hours of a crash occurring. In an attempt to diminish the value of a claim, an insurance company may tamper with evidence. An investigation can also reveal who was responsible for the crash occurring. If several parties are found to be at-fault for a motorcycle collision occurring, several parties may be liable. </p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Q. How much can compensation can I recover?</b></p><p class="MsoNormal">A. Every motorcycle accident is unique and therefore, every motorcycle accident claim settlement will vary. The outcome of a settlement will depend on many factors, including the severity of the injury, the type of injury, and the experience of the attorney handling the case. A Victorville motorcycle accident attorney with years of experience handling personal injury claims can recover up to four times more compensation than if a victim were to handle the case on their own or with the assistance of an inexperienced lawyer.</p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Q. How much will it cost me to hire an experienced Victorville motorcycle accident lawyer?</b></p><p class="MsoNormal">A. Almost every<a href="http://www.victorville-injury-lawyers.com/motorcycle-accidents">Victorville motorcycle accident attorney</a> will work on a contingency fee basis, meaning the attorney&#8217;s fee is contingent upon securing you a settlement. If the attorney is unable to win you compensation, you will not be charged for the attorney&#8217;s services. You can discuss a contingent arrangement and the details of your case in a private consultation.&#160; You should not be charged for the consultation and should not be pressured to hire the attorney. Contact a <a href="http://www.victorville-injury-lawyers.com/">Victorville personal injury lawyer</a> today before you are not allowed to pursue compensation.&#160;</p>'
