aS'First, what is a &#8220;personal injury?&#8221;  In the context of this article a personal injury is an injury to your body, mind or emotions that was caused by someone else.  If you have suffered an injury at the hands of another party, you may be eligible to file a personal injury lawsuit.  There are all different kinds of personal injuries -- traffic accidents, assaults, accidents in the home, product defect accidents (product liability), medical and dental accidents, industrial diseases, asbestosis, chest diseases (emphysema, pneumoconiosis, silicosis, chronic bronchitis, asthma, chronic obstructive pulmonary disease, and chronic obstructive airways disease), occupational deafness, stress, dermatitis and repetitive strain injury.  \r\n\r\nAll of these are personal injuries suffered for various reasons and in different places like work or home or out on our nations roads.  Personal injuries that wind up in lawsuits happen every day in every way across the country.  However, not all injuries will necessarily turn into personal injury lawsuits.  If you stub your toe on the way to the bathroom does that qualify as a personal injury?  Well, it may be an injury but it\'s not necessarily a personal injury lawsuit.  If someone walking by drops a huge metal weight and shatters your toe that is more likely a personal injury lawsuit.  The key element in a personal injury lawsuit is that the harm done to your body was caused by the negligence of another.  If someone else caused injury to your body, mind or emotional well being then you may be eligible to file a personal injury lawsuit which may in turn allow you to collect monies for medical, hospital legal and some cases punitive rewards. \r\n\r\nIf you are not 100% sure, it can never hurt to take a few minutes and contact a personal injury lawyer to find out more.  Remember, the best course of action is to report your injury to medical and legal professionals as fast as possible.  The faster you do talk to a personal injury legal expert, the fresher the facts about your accident will be and the quicker a legal action can be made on your behalf.  Your personal injury attorney will walk through every moment of the accident, of how you were injured, review your case and then determine whether or not you have grounds to bring a legal action and seek financial compensation.  If it does go forward, your lawyer will handle the legal proceedings.  A personal injury attorney will help you sort out what can be very complicated medical information, help you deal with your insurance company and most importantly, they will help you walk through the entire personal injury lawsuit from start to finish. \r\n\r\nIf you have suffered a personal injury of any type and need help determining whether or not you have a case,  seek the advice and counsel of an experienced personal injury attorney as soon as possible to determine what legal options you may have.  For a free and detailed evaluation with a personal injury lawyer at Ledger &amp; Associates, please call 1-800-300-0001 or visit the firm\'s website for more information at <a href="http://www.ledgerlaw.com/">LedgerLaw</a>.<!--more-->If you have suffered an injury at the hands of another party, you may be eligible to file a personal injury lawsuit.'
