aS'<p>The Birmingham divorce process can be complicated and stressful for all parties involved.&#160; Divorce mediation is becoming increasingly popular as an alternative to traditional divorce litigation.&#160; </p><p>Mediation is a non-adversarial, confidential process in which a neutral third party, the mediator, facilitates an agreement acceptable to both people.&#160; The agreement pertains to all aspects of their divorce, such as child custody, child support, and property distribution.&#160; Mediation may also address non-legal issues, such as emotional trauma, or how the parents interact with each other and around their children.</p><p>Advantages for children</p><p>The stress and animosity often generated during a litigated <a href="http://www.covenantlawpc.com/aop/birmingham-separation/" target="&#95;blank">Birmingham divorce&#160;separation</a> can be emotionally damaging not only for the couple, but for the children as well.&#160; Mediation is a more empowering choice for children because:</p><p>?&#160;Separating parents maintain control of their children&#8217;s needs, and can develop a comprehensive parenting plan without the interference of judges and lawyers.</p><p>?&#160;Mediation is more private than a traditional divorce.&#160; Family lives and financial matters are kept entirely confidential, and are not flaunted before the media.&#160; Mediation encourages children to discuss the divorce directly with their parents rather than seeking information from sources who do not have the children&#8217;s best interests at heart. </p><p>This article was provided by <a href="http://www.covenantlawpc.com/about-us/" target="&#95;blank">divorce lawyers in Birmingham</a> at Covenant Law Firm, P.C., located 2230 Third Avenue North, Birmingham, Alabama 35203.</p><!--more-->The stress and animosity often generated during a litigated <a href="http://www.covenantlawpc.com/aop/birmingham-separation/" target="&#95;blank">Birmingham divorce&#160;separation</a> can be emotionally damaging not only for the couple, but for the children as well.&#160;This article was provided by <a href="http://www.covenantlawpc.com/about-us/" target="&#95;blank">divorce lawyers in Birmingham</a> at Covenant Law Firm, P.C., located 2230 Third Avenue North, Birmingham, Alabama 35203.'
