aS'<br /><p>Being arrested may be the most traumatic event of your life. But with experienced criminal defense attorneys by your side, you may be able to successfully defend yourself and move on with your life.</p><p>Below are the top five reasons you must have a lawyer by your side when police question you:</p><ul><li><b>Talking to police without your lawyer will not help your case:</b> If police detain you, then they suspect you are guilty. If police arrest you, then they have enough evidence to do so. You cannot talk your way out of an arrest. Talking to police without a lawyer present will not help you in any way. In fact, talking without an attorney may actually hurt your case.</li><li><b>Lawyers can negotiate better deals:</b> Regardless of whether you are innocent or guilty, it is in your best interests to have a lawyer present during police questioning. An experienced attorney can negotiate with police or possibly have the charges against you reduced.</li><li><b>Information can be used against you:</b> If you tell your story without a lawyer present, police may or may not accurately remember your statement. Furthermore, any information you give police can be used against you.</li><li><b>A lawyer can protect your rights:</b> Under the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fifth&#95;Amendment&#95;to&#95;the&#95;United&#95;States&#95;Constitution" target="&#95;blank">Fifth Amendment</a>, you have certain inalienable rights. While not common, police sometimes violate these rights. But with a lawyer present, your rights will be protected.</li><li><b>A lawyer can bear witness:</b> Lastly, it is important to have a lawyer present during police questioning because he or she can bear witness to all interactions with law enforcement. </li></ul><p><b>Seek trustworthy criminal defense lawyers</b></p><p /><p>At The Daugherty Law Firm, our <a href="http://www.daughertylawpc.com/">Manassas criminal defense lawyers</a> understand the law and are ready to defend the rights of individuals accused of committing all types of crimes. If you or a loved one faces criminal prosecution, contact us immediately by phone at 703-659-2437 or visit our office located at 9315 Center St., Suite 106, Manassas, Virginia 20110-5571.</p><!--more-->Learn the top five reasons you must have a lawyer by your side when police question you.'
