aS'Brought to you by <a href="http://www.williammuhr.com/cases/practice-area/denver-auto-accident-attorney/">Denver auto accident attorney</a> William Muhr.<br /><br />Travelers insurance has launched its first mobile application, called &#8220;Auto Accident Help&#8221; and is available for both iPhones and Blackberry and are free to download and use. The application is available from iTunes or Travelers.com. The application is intended to make the auto accident claim simpler for drivers. In the instance of an accident, a driver can begin their claim process immediately from their phone. <br />Often, after an accident, drivers may be nervous or stressed. These feelings cause distraction and often drivers forget to note the needed information for the claims process. This application walks drivers step by step through the claims process so they are able to get the necessary information and eventually will make their claims process more speedy and easy. <br />The company says, &quot;Immediately after an accident, it is natural to feel unsure about what steps to take and we want to be there to help guide people through the process,&quot; said Patrick Gee, Senior Vice President for Travelers Personal Insurance Claims. &quot;Our new mobile applications allow us to do so by helping consumers with the necessary and important steps after an auto accident.&quot; <br />This application is another step in the company&#8217;s mobile strategy and comes months after the launch of their mobile website. <br /><br /><!--more-->Brought to you by <a href="http://www.williammuhr.com/cases/practice-area/denver-auto-accident-attorney/">Denver\r\n auto accident attorney</a> William Muhr.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTravelers insurance has launched its first mobile application, called \r\n&#8220;Auto Accident Help&#8221; and is available for both iPhones and Blackberry \r\nand are free to download and use.'
