aS'<p>Police in West Plains, Missouri, are investigating a <b>train crash</b> that <b>killed</b> a 24-year old man on Monday evening, the <a href="http://www.news-leader.com/article/20100406/BREAKING01/100406011/1007/NEWS01/West+Plains+train+death+being+investigated+as+suicide">News-Leader reports</a>. So far, the police have not determined if the crash was a suicide and are working with the Burlington Northern Santa Fe to investigate the cause.</p><p><a href="http://www.usatoday.com/news/nation/2010-04-04-train-peds&#95;N.htm">USA Today</a> cites a Federal Railroad Administration (FRA) spokesperson saying that incidents involving pedestrians is the number one cause of death in the railroad industry, far outstripping fatalities in <b><a href="http://www.blackmanlegal.com/CM/PracticeAreaDescriptions/TrainInjuryAccidents.asp" target="&#95;blank">train-vehicle collisions</a></b>. Over the past 10 years, the number of deaths involving trains and motor vehicles has dropped 42 percent to 248 compared to deaths involving pedestrians in the same period, which have fallen only percent to 434.</p><p><i>The <a href="http://www.blackmanlegal.com/">personal injury lawyers</a> at Blackman Legal Group, a California-based law firm founded by renowned trial attorney, <a href="http://www.blackmanlegal.com/CM/Custom/Attorneys.asp#Blackman">Clifford Blackman</a>, has been representing injury victims since 1976, and have special expertise in cases involving <a href="http://www.spinal-injury-california.com/">spinal cord injury</a>, <a href="http://www.brain-injury-lawyer.com/">traumatic brain injury</a>, <a href="http://www.personal-injury-san-francisco.net/burn-injury.php">burn injury</a>, <a href="http://www.personal-injury-san-francisco.net/personal-injury-overview.php">catastrophic injuries</a> and <a href="http://www.wrongful-death-lawfirm.com/">wrongful death</a>.&#160; The nationwide toll-free number to call for a free consultation is <b>1-888-395-3551.</b></i></p>'
