aS"<p><u><b>NASSAU COUNTY PARKING &amp; TRAFFIC VIOLATIONS AGENCY</b></u></p><p>The Nassau County Traffic &amp; Parking Violations Agency is located near my&#160; Hempstead office.&#160; I have been defending driver's charged with moving violations for nearly two decades and have handled more than 20, 000 tickets.&#160; The court permits me to proceed with your written authorization, so you don't have to miss work or school to attend court. &#160; Based upon my history of cases in this court, I can forecast a result for you based upon the charges pending against you and your driving record. &#160; Call me for a free consultation at 516 485 4888.</p><p>Have you missed your court date and been suspended or convicted by default?&#160; If you have been convicted by default, are suspended or have tickets pending in this court, please feel free to call me, Jeanne Marie Beckmann, Esq. for a free consultation at 516 485 4888 or visit my website at www.NassauTrafficLawyer.com</p><p></p><p>DON'T PAY YOUR TICKET! </p><p><br />Paying\r\n a ticket means that you are&#160;pleading guilty.&#160;&#160; If you plead   guilty&#160;to\r\n  a moving violation, the&#160;Court will notify the Department   of&#160;Motor \r\nVehicles  (DMV).&#160; A moving violation is a driving&#160;error that   \r\ncontributes to&#160;the likelihood  of an accident, such as speeding,   \r\nfollowing too closely, unsafe lane change, crossing hov divider, passing\r\n   a red light, failing to signal,  etc.&#160; DMV assigns points to moving  \r\n violations.&#160;&#160;The DMV will note the  conviction&#160;and&#160;points&#160;on your   \r\ndriving record.&#160;&#160;&#160;Convictions for any moving  violations will not   \r\nbe&#160;deleted from your driving record until January of the fourth year following the conviction.&#160;&#160;  </p><p /><p /><p>\r\n</p>"
