aS'<p>For many homeowners in Mississippi, Chinese drywall damage has been an ongoing source of problems. Drywall imported from China contains significant amounts of sulfur and sulfur-related compounds. Many believe that humidity causes the sulfur compounds in the drywall to migrate into the indoor air in your house.</p><p>At least 500 million pounds of <a href="http://www.luckeyandmullins.com/">Chinese drywall</a> was installed in up to 100,000 homes, condominiums and apartments in the U.S. from 2004 to 2007. A large portion of that was in the Gulf Coast region in the aftermath of hurricanes in 2004 and 2005.</p><p>Chinese drywall problems</p><p>Problems with Chinese drywall include the following:</p><ul><li>Chinese drywall emits sulfur dioxide, carbon disulfide, hydrogen sulfide, strontium sulfide, and carbonyl sulfide in a gas form, which is believed to cause a wide variety of material, environmental and health problems.</li><li>Sulfur dioxide corrodes copper electrical wiring, waterlines (such as those leading to refrigerators), faucets, circuit breakers, smoke detectors, and air conditioner coils.</li><li>The federal Agency for Toxic Substances &amp; Disease Registry (ATSDR) advises doctors to look for symptoms that include sore throat, stuffy nose, cough, shortness of breath, chest pain, nausea, eye irritation, and headaches after short-term exposure.</li><li>The ATSDR also says that longer-term exposure can result in fatigue, loss of appetite, irritability, poor memory, dizziness, and insomnia.</li></ul><p>Health problems</p><p>Health problems from <a href="http://www.luckeyandmullins.com/chinese-drywall-damages/">Chinese drywall damages</a> have caused many people to leave their homes. Defective Chinese drywall could be especially dangerous for sensitive populations, such as the very young, the elderly, and people with asthma and chemical sensitivities.</p><p>If you notice any of the above conditions in your home, or your family has developed any symptoms such as nosebleeds and runny nose, eye irritation, headaches, coughing and sneezing, or difficulty breathing, you may be entitled to significant compensation. To determine whether you have contaminated Chinese drywall, go to your attic, remove some of the insulation, and inspect the writing on the back of the drywall. Chinese drywall may be marked &#8220;Knauf-Tianjin&#8221; or &quot;Made in China.&quot; </p><p>From simple negligence cases to complex mass tort litigation, the Luckey &amp; Mullins law firm has developed an excellent reputation by representing thousands of clients throughout Mississippi and the surrounding areas. Whether your needs are large or small, we are dedicated to providing quality legal services without the bureaucracy of a large firm. If you need additional information, please do not hesitate to contact us to discuss your special needs or concerns.</p><!--more-->At least 500 million pounds of <a href="http://www.luckeyandmullins.com/">Chinese drywall</a> was installed in up to 100,000 homes, condominiums and apartments in the U.S. from 2004 to 2007. A large portion of that was in the Gulf Coast region in the aftermath of hurricanes in 2004 and 2005.'
