aS'<p>Accidents happen. They are a fact of life, and they often result in serious injury.&#160; If you were partially at fault in an accident that led to your injury, under Florida comparative negligence law you are still entitled to seek compensation to recover for your damages.&#160; However, if you are shown to have been careless and that carelessness is shown to have contributed to your injury, the amount you can expect to recover is going to be reduced in proportion to your carelessness. An experienced <a href="http://www.attorneywoodruff.com/practice-areas/pinellas-county-injury/" target="&#95;blank">Pinellas County injury attorney</a> will gladly explain how the doctrine of comparative negligence applies to your situation.</p><p><strong>Joint and several liability</strong></p><p>With regard to paying for the damages that you incur, the <a href="http://www.atra.org/show/7345" target="&#95;blank">joint and several liability law in Florida</a> provides that your damages must be paid according to the proportion of fault for each party responsible for your injury. For example, if you are determined to be at fault, the following applies:</p><ul type="disc"><li>Any person found ten percent or less at fault will not be responsible for your economic damages, such as medical expenses and lost earnings.</li><li>Any person found more than ten percent at fault, but less than 25 percent, at fault, will be responsible for only up to $200,000 of your economic damages.</li><li>Any person found at least 25 percent at fault, but not more than 50 percent at fault, will not be responsible for more than $500,000 of your economic damages.</li><li>Any person found more than 50 percent at fault will not be responsible for more than $1,000,000 of your economic damages.</li></ul><p>A skilled <a href="http://www.attorneywoodruff.com/practice-areas/pinellas-county-injury/pinellas-county-injury-lawyers/" target="&#95;blank">personal injury lawyer in Pinellas County</a> can explain the intricacies and nuances of these and all other aspects of personal injury law to you, and he or she can help value your case to determine whether it is in your interests to pursue a claim.</p><b>Experienced Saint Petersburg injury attorneys can assist with your case</b><p>If you suffered any type of serious injury, or if you have questions about personal injury, please do not hesitate to contact Attorney Tom Woodruff, one of the top Saint Petersburg personal injury lawyers. He has an exceptional ability to understand the complex problems injury victims and their families are dealing with.&#160; Woodruff Injury Law serves clients throughout the west coast of Florida.</p><p>Contact us to speak to an experienced Saint Petersburg injury lawyer. We offer a free initial consultation with a skilled injury lawyer in Saint Petersburg.</p><p>Thomas M. Woodruff Attorney at Law<br />4055 Central Avenue<br />St. Petersburg, FL 33713<br />(727) 327-3111</p><!--more-->If you suffered any type of serious injury, or if you have questions about personal injury, please do not hesitate to contact Attorney Tom Woodruff, one of the top Saint Petersburg personal injury lawyers. He has an exceptional ability to understand the complex problems injury victims and their families are dealing with.&#160; Woodruff Injury Law serves clients throughout the west coast of Florida.'
