aS'In California, a <a href="http://www.injuryattorney-losangeles.com/wrongful&#95;death.htm">wrongful death</a> refers to a situation when someone is killed because of another person\'s negligence, carelessness or intentional conduct. &#160;An example would be if someone is killed in an <a href="http://www.injuryattorney-losangeles.com/car&#95;accident&#95;lawyer&#95;los&#95;angeles.htm">automobile accident</a>- the case would be referred to as a &quot;wrongful death&quot; case.&#160;<p><b>Damages in a Wrongful Death Case</b>&#160;</p><p>The damages in a wrongful death case are unique and different in every case. &#160;The reality is that an individuals life is priceless. &#160;There is no amount of money that would make the loss of a loved on any easier. &#160;One of the most difficult tasks in a wrongful death case is to put a value on an individuals life. &#160;In the legal system, the amount in damages refers to the dollar value of the loss. &#160;For example survivors are entitled to sue for not only monetary damages, but also for the loss of comfort, society, love and consortium. &#160;Grief and sorrow are not damages that can be recovered in a monetary calculation. &#160;</p><p><b>Most Common Types of Wrongful Death Cases </b></p><p><b></b>some of the most common types of cases are as follows:</p><p><ul><li>Auto Accidents / Motorcycle Accidents</li><li>Premises Liability / Slip and Fall</li><li><a href="http://www.brain-injuryattorney.com/">Traumatic Brain Injury</a></li></ul><b>Statute of Limitations </b></p><p>In California, the statute of limitations to bring an action for wrongful death varies. &#160;It depends on the circumstances surrounding the case. &#160;There may be a statute of limitations that is only 6-months from the date of the accident or injury. &#160;Once that statute passes, you forever lose your right to bring an action against the wrongdoer.</p><p><b>Who Can Sue?</b>&#160;</p><p>The loss of loved one is a devastating experience. &#160;In California, the following individuals may have standing to sue in a wrongful death action:</p><p><ul><li>Spouse</li><li>Children</li><li>Dependants&#160;</li></ul><b><a href="http://www.injuryattorney-losangeles.com">Wrongful Death Lawyers Los Angeles</a>&#160;</b></p><p>Slaughter &amp; Slaughter is a California <a href="http://www.injuryattorney-losangeles.com">personal injury law firm</a>&#160;that focuses on representing victims and families of catastrophic injuries and wrongful death cases. &#160;</p><p><b></b></p><p><b><a href="http://www.injuryattorney-losangeles.com"></a></b></p><p><b><a href="http://www.injuryattorney-losangeles.com"></a></b></p><p><b></b></p><p><b></b></p><!--more--><a href="http://www.injuryattorney-losangeles.com">Los Angeles wrongful death lawyers</a>, discuss what a wrongful death is and the individuals that may have claims. &#160;Damages calculated in a wrongful death action are unique to the individual and is one of the most difficult tasks to determine. &#160;Call today for a free consultation.'
