aS'<br /><p>It is possible to take all the right steps to ensure that your attorney gets good results for your case, only to defeat your cause with ill-timed words or actions. Here is a list of precautions you should take to ensure that you do not lose the compensation you deserve for your auto accident:</p><ul><li><b>Do not delay seeking medical treatment.</b> A victim of an auto accident may do this under the mistaken belief that the case needs to be settled before a doctor can be seen. Nothing could be further from the truth&#8212;or more damaging to your health. In fact, healthcare records often provide key documentation needed to build evidence that supports your claim. Therefore, be sure to seek any treatment you need in a timely manner, and keep your&#160;attorney updated on your health status.</li><li><b>Do not share more information than you need to with anyone except your&#160;attorney.</b> Do not tell insurance companies anything other than that you have been in an accident, and are seeking both medical and legal counsel. No matter what they say or do, they cannot force you tell them anything more without your attorney present. Do not admit fault for all or any part of the accident.</li><li><b>Do not accept so-called deals from insurance companies.</b> Insurance companies know how to tempt you with offers of quick and easy settlements. Often, these settlements serve their own best interests and not yours. Once you accept and sign their offer, it can be difficult to retract your consent and attain fairer compensation for your injury.</li></ul><p>It would be impossible to list everything you might do that could jeopardize the case for your auto accident. If you have any questions or concerns as to the correct course of action, contact an <a href="http://www.tarasilaw.com/aop/pittsburgh-commercial-vehicle-accidents/">Pittsburgh accident lawyer</a>, and they will guide you in the right direction and build a winnable case that gets the results you deserve and need.</p><p>For a free consultation with the <a href="http://www.tarasilaw.com/">Pittsburgh accident attorneys</a> at Tarasi &amp; Tarasi, located at 510 Third Avenue, Pittsburgh, PA 15219.</p><!--more-->Here is a list of precautions you should take to ensure that you do not lose the compensation you deserve.'
