aS'Interest in our SmartKits has been high in the last few months since we introduced it, and in response to comments we&#8217;ve added a couple items like a handy list of emergency numbers you can use in case of an accident.<br /><br />The SmartKit contains first aid supplies and bandages, an emergency display banner to notify other drivers of the accident, and a flashlight and battery. There also are everyday items you might use, such as a tire gauge and a pocket-size road atlas. All of this comes in a container that will fit perfectly into your glove box or storage bin.<br /><br />We put the SmartKit together to help our clients and others be prepared in case of an accident. At a time of confusion and stress, it&#8217;s good to have at your fingertips certain things that can help guide you through the time following a crash. Information you can gather at the scene could be helpful for us, and could have an impact on the successful outcome of a legal case.<br /><br />The SmartKit provides you with simple step-by-step instructions, along with other resources you&#8217;ll find useful &#8211; for example, a form for getting the name and contact information of the other driver, their insurance information, the name of the police officer who investigates and a few basic facts about how the accident happened.<br /><br />I hope you never need to use the kit, but I&#8217;d like you to have one just the same. Stop by the office and we&#8217;ll set you up with a SmartKit. Maybe there&#8217;s someone you know who would like one, too &#8211; a friend, neighbor or perhaps someone in your own family. Let us know, and we&#8217;ll make sure they get one too.<br /><br />If you can&#8217;t make it in right away but still would like a SmartKit, call me at (303) 758-4777 or drop me an email at DLS@dlslawfirm.com. You can visit us anytime at <a href="http://www.dlslawfirm.com" title="Denver\'s premier auto accident attorney">www.dlslawfirm.com</a>.<!--more-->It\'s a must-have for your