aS'<p>Pedestrian accidents occur every eight minutes on average according to statistics and there are other statistics that show every two hours on average there is a pedestrian in the United States that is killed. </p><p>These are just the tip of the pedestrian accident statistics. According to the statistics 85.7 percent of non-deadly pedestrian accidents take place in an urban area like Riverside. \r\nThere are statistics that show men are involved 69 percent of the time in fatal pedestrian accident, while women are less, but there are female pedestrian fatal crashes. </p><p>This equals to a yearly total of about 5,000 pedestrian fatalities annually. There are also an estimated 64,000 pedestrian injuries annually that result in traumatic head injuries, spinal cord injuries, multiple broken bones, cuts, scrapes and gashes. </p><p>These figures are frightening when anyone that walks for exercise, to work, with their children or even when shopping can be one of the pedestrian accidents that occur every eight minutes on average and can happen in Riverside. \r\nThe highest rate of pedestrian accidents occurs at intersections, even when in a designated crosswalk it is not safe as a person walking. </p><p>There are vehicles that do not stop for crosswalks, people that are making turns onto the street the pedestrian is crossing and don&#8217;t see them or are going too fast to stop. Even the person walking that does not cross the street is not safe, there are accidents every year with vehicles that veer off of the road striking the person walking. </p><p>This can be due to the driver going at a high rate of speed, talking on a cell phone or other distractions that make the driver negligent. \r\nUrban areas are not the only place that pedestrian accidents occur that are fatal or cause injuries, there are 14.3 percent of these accidents that occur in rural areas. </p><p>This means even walking in the Riverside neighborhoods is not always safe. This is where there are pedestrian accidents that involve adults and children. \r\nAfter a pedestrian accident it can be devastating to the injured pedestrian victim and to their family. This is when the San Bernardino, Los Angeles, or Riverside pedestrian accident attorney should be consulted. Ehline Law Firm is a <a href="http://www.ehlinelaw.com/pages/3212/pedestrianattorneyslosangeles.htm">Los Angeles pedestrian attorney</a> who can help.&#160; </p><p>With several locations to meet you in California.&#160; One is located at 201 Wilshire Blvd., Santa Monica, CA 90401. 310.376.8488. This is an <a href="http://www.ehlinelaw.com/" title="accident attorney">accident attorney </a>that has the experience and the resources to hold a negligent driver and their insurance company responsible for the injuries the victim sustained. \r\n</p>\r\n?<br /><a color: rgb(0, 0, 255); text-align: left;" href="http://maps.google.com/maps?hl=en&ie=UTF8&q=santa+monica+pedestrian+accident+attorneys&fb=1&gl=us&hq=pedestrian+accident+attorneys&hnear=Santa+Monica,+CA&ei=utfQTOT&#95;Jpm6tgO4gIG-Ag&ved=0CCUQpQY&view=map&cid=18430828494304026766&t=h&ll=34.017949,-118.500016&spn=0.005336,0.006437&z=16&iwloc=A&source=embed">View Larger Map</a><!--more-->According to the statistics 85.7 percent of non-deadly pedestrian accidents take place in an urban area like Riverside.'
