aS'<p>California is one of the most heavily commuting states in United States. Apart from huge numbers of cars on the road, California roads are also a very busy state with bicycles. Here you have biking lanes on almost all public streets, so biking is a highly recommended mode of transportation. </p><p>But the bad news is: about 720 bicyclists got killed in road accidents in the United States; this number is for last year alone and it reports that there was a fatal bicyclist accident for every 6 hours and half of the victims are children that were below 16 years of age. In addition, about 75% of the bicyclist faces serious injuries and fatal accidents, because of head injuries. </p><p>If a road accident involves a motor vehicle and a bicyclist, most of the time a bicyclist can obtain a lower compensation amount from insurance companies than motor vehicle drivers. One of the recent research reports have revealed that compensation for injuries caused in car accidents are 40% higher when compared with cyclists who sustained the same type of injuries, due to a road accident. This is the reason why most of the bicycle accident attorneys recommend the injured bicyclists should file an insurance claim as quickly as possible. In this case, you should approach an experienced attorney, as he will help you to receive the full compensation. </p><p>\r\nIn most of the cases, a bicycle accident takes place, because of the motorist&#8217;s negligence or heedlessness of the bicyclist while riding the bike. </p><p>Here are some common types of hits in which a cyclist may get injuries and need a <a href="http://www.ehlinelaw.com/pages/3440/PracticeAreas&#95;Bicycle-Accidents.htm">Los Angeles bicycle attorney</a>:\r\n</p><p>?\tIf a motorbike driver turns the bike directly in the path of a bicyclist; \r\n</p><p>?\tIf a motorist\'s fail to stop at a stop sign, at an intersection or red light\r\nA vehicle driver\'s inattention is another main reason which leads to bicyclist accident. </p><p>Cycling accidents are different from other accident cases, because they may present strange legal issues. Hill slopes, conditions of the road, lanes and routes, lines of sight, distinctions among bicycle paths, intersection crossings are some of important legal issues, which may be included in a bike accident case. </p><p>So, it is always good to contact a California bicycle attorney who can understand the legalities properly and can further advocate for you. On the other hand, it is also important for the bicyclist to obey the traffic laws.  </p><p>Most of the time, automobile drivers do not compare a bicyclist with a motor vehicle, and it is also a main reason for accidents. So, it is very important for both the drivers whether bicyclist or motor vehicle driver to observe and cooperate with each other.  If this type of communication does not happen then there will be negligence of appropriate driving practices or an ignorance of driving laws which ends up in accidents. \r\n\r\n\r\n</p><!--more-->The <a href="http://www.ehlinelaw.com/pages/3440/PracticeAreas&#95;Bicycle-Accidents.htm">bicycle attorneys Los Angeles</a> at Ehline Law firm are the <a href="http://www.ehlinelaw.com/">Los Angeles injury lawyer</a> to hire when injured in a <a href="http://www.ehlinelaw.com/pages/3450/hit-by-car-riding-bike.htm">bike crash</a>.'
