aS'<p>Here are some very common questions that people ask about auto accidents and injuries in Escondido, CA. </p><p><b>Q:</b> Is there a statute of limitations for filing auto accident lawsuits in California?<br /><b>A:</b> In California, in most cases, you have two years to file an auto accident lawsuit. The statute of limitations may differ in cases against certain governmental entities and cases involving minors under the age of 18. You should speak to an attorney to verify the specific statute of limitations applicable to your case.</p><p><b>Q:</b> What damages should you seek when suing a negligent driver?<br /><b>A:</b> Some of the damages claimed when suing a negligent driver include:</p><ul><li>Wrongful Death</li><li>Medical Bills</li><li>Pain and Suffering</li><li>Property Damage</li><li>Lost Wages</li><li>Future Medical Care</li><li>Vocational Rehabilitation</li><li>Future Life Care</li></ul><p><b>Q:</b> How much money will I get from my auto accident lawsuit?<br /><b>A:</b> The amount of compensation awarded depends on the facts of your case and the nature and extent of your injuries. Your lawyer will review all aspect of your case in determining the amount of money you should expect.</p><p><b>Q:</b> Can any injured party involved in an auto accident file a lawsuit?<br /><b>A:</b> Yes. Auto accident injury victims are always able to seek recovery from the negligent driver(s) who caused their injuries. Medical bills, pain and suffering, lost wages, property damage, future medical care, vocational rehabilitation, future life care plans, and other damages are often recovered with the assistance of a lawyer.</p><p><b>Q:</b> Are negligent commercial truck drivers liable for wrongful death and personal injury?<br /><b>A:</b> Yes. Large 18-wheeler commercial trucks can cause catastrophic injuries, or even death, usually on freeways at high speeds. If you are the victim of a trucking accident injury, you should immediately hire a lawyer and consider a lawsuit.</p><p><b>LILJEGREN LAW GROUP WILL HELP YOU</b></p><p>For a free, confidential, no-obligation consultation, please contact the Escondido offices of Liljegren Law Group. You may submit your case through <a href="http://www.liljegrenlaw.com/">www.liljegrenlaw.com</a> or by calling (866) 613-9906 toll free. We also help people across California, with offices in Escondido, Oceanside, and Temecula.</p><p><b>LILJEGREN LAW GROUP &#8211; SERIOUS INJURIES. CARING PROFESSIONALS.</b></p><!--more-->Here are some very common questions that people ask about auto accidents and injuries in Escondido, CA.'
