aS'<p padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 15px; color: rgb(89, 84, 81); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><a title="Shutdown Article | The State" href="http://www.thestate.com/2013/10/18/3046085/shutdown-threatened-lifesaving.html" target="&#95;blank" outline: none; cursor: pointer; text-decoration: none; color: rgb(249, 133, 78);">Shutdown threatened lifesaving medicine for Beaufort resident</a>.&#160;A The State&#160;newspaper reported that a 31 year old South Carolina resident was participating in a clinical trial with Novartis and was able to participate in the study, provided that he could prove that he was Medicare eligible.&#160; Due to problems with the recent government shutdown, he was nearly unable to get his paperwork in time.&#160; The South Carolina citizen&#8217;s mother was livid, &#8220;Cancer is something you just don&#8217;t mess with,&#8221; said Stacy White, David&#8217;s mother and a retired nurse. &#8220;And it&#8217;s horrible that government officials can&#8217;t give you something so minor as a piece of paper to save your life, and nobody seems to have an answer.&#8221;&#160; Most situations surrounding the shutdown haven&#8217;t been life and death.&#160; But the affects concern many looking down the road.</p><p padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 15px; color: rgb(89, 84, 81); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Many of our Pensacola and Mobile, Alabama social security clients have been calling our law firm to inquire as to how government shutdown would affect their disability benefits.&#160; The truth is that there is not a perfectly clear answer.&#160; The&#160;<a title="Absolutely everything you need to know about how the government shutdown will work" href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/wonkblog/wp/2013/09/30/absolutely-everything-you-need-to-know-about-how-the-government-shutdown-will-work/" target="&#95;blank" outline: none; cursor: pointer; text-decoration: none; color: rgb(249, 133, 78);">Washington Post</a>&#160;reports that in the event of a shutdown, the Social Security Administration will keep enough staff on hand to ensure that checks go out.</p><p padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 15px; color: rgb(89, 84, 81); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Some experts urge that the best thing to do is ensure that social security is not the only benefit you will receive once you retire or if you are disabled.&#160; Explore private disability insurance and also look into retirement plans offered by your employer.&#160; Even very small investments over a working career can ensure that you are able to retire with dignity.&#160; Review your debt load and determine if you are spending your retirement now on new cars, expensive outings, and a home that isn&#8217;t within your budget.&#160; Dave Ramsey&#8217;s&#160;<a title="Dave Ramsey Financial Peace University material " href="http://www.daveramsey.com/fpu/home/" target="&#95;blank" outline: none; cursor: pointer; text-decoration: none; color: rgb(249, 133, 78);">Financial Peace University</a>&#160;has helped numerous families get out of debt and ensure long term financial viability.&#160; But these are long term solutions and therefore aren&#8217;t making much noise in the headlines.&#160; But we believe that the right answer isn&#8217;t the one that always sound right &#8220;right now.&#8221;</p><p padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 15px; color: rgb(89, 84, 81); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Our firm handles&#160;<a title="Social Security Disability" href="http://whibbsandstone.com/social-security-disability/" target="&#95;blank" outline: none; cursor: pointer; text-decoration: none; color: rgb(249, 133, 78);">social security disability</a>&#160;claims throughout Alabama and Florida, and we work with some of the best experts in the state to ensure that your social security appeal is handled successfully.&#160; We encourage you to call 1-888-219-4561 or&#160;<a title="Contact Whibbs & Stone, P.A." href="http://whibbsandstone.com/contact-personal-injury-lawyers/" target="&#95;blank" outline: none; cursor: pointer; text-decoration: none; color: rgb(249, 133, 78);">email&#160;us</a>&#160;for a no cost consultation.</p><p padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 15px; color: rgb(89, 84, 81); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Don&#8217;t just wait for something to happen, take action.&#160; Call Whibbs &amp; Stone, PA today.</p>'
