aS'<p class="MsoNormal"><em><strong>Some frequently asked questions and answers about consent forms and medical malpractice follow.</strong></em></p><p /><p class="LN2"><strong>What is the purpose of consent forms?</strong></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal">Consent forms are a means by which doctors can express and document that a particular patient gave them permission to treat.&#160; In fact, most physicians will not perform tests, procedures, or other treatments without obtaining the proper permission&#8212;most of the time in writing. However, verbal consent suffices in certain situations.&#160; Consent forms alert patients that complications may occur and that the physician may not be successful in treatment.</p><p /><p class="LN2"><strong>What do consent forms cover?</strong></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal">Consent forms protect physicians in the event that his or her patient claims never to have given permission to perform a certain procedure or never understanding the treatment plan the physician carried out.&#160; Release forms <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=GX8irF-rCewC&lpg=PA118&dq=informed%20consent%20medical%20malpractice&pg=PA112#v=onepage&q=informed%20consent%20medical%20malpractice&f=false">demonstrate </a><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=GX8irF-rCewC&lpg=PA118&dq=informed%20consent%20medical%20malpractice&pg=PA112#v=onepage&q=informed%20consent%20medical%20malpractice&f=false">communication between doctor and patient</a>, but also an expectation that the doctor will adhere to the discussed course of action and provide a reasonable standard of care.</p><p /><p class="LN2"><strong>Does signing a release form waive my rights to pursue a malpractice claim?</strong></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal">Although physicians facing malpractice claims may try to avoid liability by producing a signed consent form, any experienced <a href="http://www.azlawfirm.com/aop/arizona-medical-malpractice/medical-malpractice/">malpractice attorney in Arizona</a> will agree that this type of defense is rarely successful.&#160; Regardless of how clearly worded a consent form is, and even if it is signed by a mentally competent individual, health care providers are still responsible for their patients.&#160; Physicians that commit medical negligence have no liability protection.</p><p /><p class="LN2"><strong>When should you file a malpractice lawsuit?</strong></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal">If a patient believes that a physician, nurse, hospital, or other health care provider was negligent in any way, he or she has grounds for filing a claim.&#160; If consent form, he or she must demonstrate that the form does not impede the claim.&#160; Usually, with the help of a lawyer in Phoenix, he or she argues that the consent form does not cover malpractice. </p><p /><p class="LN2"><strong>What are the different types of malpractice?</strong></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal">Medical negligence occurs when one or more health care providers fail to provide acceptable care to a patient.&#160; Some common incidents of malpractice include the following:</p><p /><ul><li><div class="MsoNormal">Lack of diagnosis, or misdiagnosis</div></li></ul><ul><li><div class="MsoNormal">Surgical errors, such as wrong site surgeries</div></li></ul><ul><li><div class="MsoNormal">Medication errors, such as improper prescription or administration of a drug, or failing to avoid a dangerous drug interaction</div></li></ul><ul><li><div class="MsoNormal">Failure to monitor the status of a patient or to properly oversee recovery</div></li></ul><p /><p class="MsoNormal" /><p>When these and other negligent actions or inactions by a medical professional cause injury or death to a patient, he or she can seek rightful compensation with the help of a <a href="http://www.azlawfirm.com/phoenix-attorney/">Phoenix lawyer</a> &#8212;regardless of whether or not the patient expressed consent.</p><p /><p class="LN3"><strong>Medical malpractice lawyers in Phoenix</strong></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal">The Law Firm of M. Paul Fischer represents clients who suffered injury or illness because of medical negligence.&#160; For more information on medical malpractice, or to schedule a consultation with a skilled Phoenix lawyer, <a href="http://azlawfirm.com/contact-us/">contact the firm</a> today: </p><p /><p class="MsoNormal">The Law Firm of M. Paul Fischer, P.C.<br />40 North Center Street, Suite 100<br />P.O. Box 5139<br />Mesa, AZ 85211-5139<br />Phone: 480-461-4650<br />Fax: 480-461-4658</p><!--more-->When these and other negligent actions or inactions by a medical professional cause injury or death to a patient, he or she can seek rightful compensation with the help of a Phoenix attorney&#8212;regardless of whether or not the patient expressed consent.&#160;'
