aS'<p class="MsoNormal"><b>\r\nQ. How many drunk driving accident fatalities occur each year in California?</b></p><p class="MsoNormal">A. According to the California Highway Patrol&#8217;s (CHP) Statewide Integrated Traffic\r\nRecords System, approximately 1,000 people are tragically killed in drunk driving accidents every year. The CHP also reports that approximately 18,000 people are injured in drunk driving accidents every year in the state.</p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Q. What types of injuries can be sustained in a DUI accident?</b></p><p class="MsoNormal">A. Virtually any type of injury can be sustained in a California DUI accident, including open or closed head injuries, burn injuries, simple or compound bone fracture injuries, spinal cord injuries, severed limb injuries, traumatic brain injuries, internal organ injuries, and neck injuries.</p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Q. I was seriously injured in an accident caused by a drunk driver. Should I talk to a lawyer?</b></p><p class="MsoNormal">A. Yes. If you suffered a serious injury in a car accident caused by a drunk or drugged driver, you should talk to a <a href="http://www.esteyandbomberger.com/drunkdriving-accident.html">California drunk driving accident lawyer</a> immediately. A skilled lawyer can not only help you hold the driver responsible for his or her negligent actions, but can also help you obtain financial compensation. Although no amount of compensation can undo the pain and suffering associated with a serious DUI accident injury, it can help you pay for injury expenses.</p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Q. What types of damages can I obtain compensation for?</b></p><p class="MsoNormal">A. Drunk driving accident victims may obtain compensation for surgery, hospitalizations, medicine, medical equipment, lost wages, lost benefits, loss of quality of life, disability, disfigurement, loss of relations (if applicable), and pain and suffering.</p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Q. How can a California DUI accident lawyer help?</b></p><p class="MsoNormal">A. A professional California DUI accident lawyer can process claim paperwork, collect and document evidence, handle talks with insurance companies and defense counsels, hire expert witnesses, and negotiate a full and fair settlement. Statistics show that with the assistance of a skilled personal injury lawyer, victims can recover up to four times more compensation than if they were to handle a case on their own or hire an inexperienced attorney.</p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Q. What is the first step to hiring a reputable California drunk driving accident attorney?</b></p><p class="MsoNormal">A. The first, and oftentimes, most important step to hiring a reputable attorney is the initial consultation. After hearing your story, a skilled lawyer should be able to tell you whether legal action is a viable option. The initial consultation should be free, so contact an experienced <a href="http://www.esteyandbomberger.com/car-accident.html">California car accident lawyer </a>now!</p>'
