aS'<br />\r\n\r\n<p class=" " /><p class=" ">So many people look for &quot;bulldog&quot;\r\nattorneys, when they really should be seeking a &quot;nice&quot; one. This is\r\nespecially true in Personal Injury cases. </p>\r\n<p class=" ">Why? Because being &quot;nice&quot; helps in\r\nevery stage of <a title="Encino Personal Injury Lawyers" href="http://www.lewitthackman.com/personal-injury/"><strong><em>personal injury</em></strong></a> negotiation, arbitration, mediation, and\r\nyes&#8230;most especially in litigation. Let\'s take a look at the reasons for this,\r\nstarting with finding the best personal injury attorney for your situation:</p>\r\n<ul><li><div class=" ">First, you want your attorney to be &#8220;nice&#8221; to\r\nyou, the client.&#160;You want someone who cares about you, your case, and your\r\nrecovery from your injuries.&#160;If you have suffered a serious injury, or\r\nhave <a title="Wrongful Death" href="http://www.lewitthackman.com/wrongful-death/">lost a loved one</a>, you are vulnerable and need to feel as though you can\r\ntrust your attorney.&#160;You want someone on <i>your </i>side.</div></li></ul><ul><li><div class=" ">You should know that most cases settle before\r\ngoing to trial, which means personal injury attorneys must present&#160;and sell your case to\r\ndefense counsel and insurance adjusters. Your attorney needs to convince them\r\nto ask their superiors for the authorization to pay for your losses &#8211; they\r\nwon\'t ask for maximum payouts if your attorney doesn\'t treat them with courtesy\r\nand respect.&#160;</div></li></ul><ul><li><div class=" ">Cooperation makes a trial run much more\r\nsmoothly. Judges and jurors both like &#8220;nice,&#8221; cooperative attorneys. Attorneys\r\nwho constantly bicker make the trial longer, which is hard on you, hard on the\r\njudge, and most importantly, will annoy the jury. </div></li></ul>\r\n<p class=" ">Don\'t confuse &quot;nice&quot; with &quot;pushover.&quot;</p> \r\n<p class=" ">Though professional courtesy is expected and even demanded, your personal injury attorney &#160;should also aggressively pursue your interests. She or he should not be so nice, that they are timid. </p>\r\n<p class=" ">Again, this goes back to the trust thing: </p> \r\n<p class=" ">You want a personal injury attorney who will fight for your cause, but not in \r\nsuch a manner that she or he offends the other side, the judge, or the\r\never-important jury. </p>\r\n<p class=" "><em>David B. Bobrosky is a </em><a href="http://www.lewitthackman.com/david-b-bobrosky/"><em>San Fernando Valley Personal Injury Attorney</em></a><em> at Lewitt Hackman in Encino, CA. Contact him at </em><a href="mailto:dbobrosky@lewitthackman.com"><em>dbobrosky@lewitthackman.com</em></a><em>, 818.990.2120.</em></p><!--more-->Three critical reasons to hire a nice attorney to handle your personal injury claims.'
