aS'<p class="MsoNormal">Partner, attorney and author, <a title="Daniel Buckfire" href="https://plus.google.com/108760742756407029273#108760742756407029273" target="&#95;blank">Daniel\r\nBuckfire</a>&#160;of Buckfire &amp; Buckfire, P.C., is speaking at the 9<sup>th</sup>\r\nannual No-Fault Institute presented by the Michigan Association for Justice on\r\nThursday, September 20<sup>th</sup> from 3:30 to 4:30 P.M.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">The two day seminar which takes place on Thursday,\r\nSeptember 20<sup>th</sup>and Friday, September 21<sup>st</sup>, is being held\r\nat the Westin Southfield at 1500 Town Center in Southfield, Michigan.&#160; The seminar, titled &#8220;The Assault on Auto\r\nNo-Fault: A War on Many Fronts,&#8221; will concentrate on the recent Supreme Court\r\nDecisions as well as the auto insurance industry and how fight back more\r\neffectively against insurance companies denying the rights for Michigan auto\r\naccident victims to attain the no-fault insurance benefits they are entitled to\r\nafter suffering injuries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Daniel Buckfire will be speaking at the Michigan\r\nAssociation for Justice Seminar on the Insurance Industry.&#160; He will discuss topics such as the auto\r\ninsurance companies approaches, tactics, experts, claims personnel, and more to\r\nhelp one better understand their tactics.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&#8220;Every driver in the State of Michigan is required\r\nto have an automobile insurance policy with no-fault benefits.&#160; An individual <a title="injured in a Michigan car accident" href="http://www.buckfirelaw.com/practice&#95;areas/michigan-auto-accident-attorney-best-michigan-car-accident-lawyers.cfm" target="&#95;blank">injured\r\nin a Michigan car accident</a>, motorcycle accident, truck accident,\r\nbicycle accident, or pedestrian accident, is most likely entitled to Michigan\r\nno-fault benefits, regardless of who was at fault,&#8221; says Daniel Buckfire. &#8220;Many\r\nof times the insurance adjuster will use different tricks and tactics when\r\ndealing with a no-fault insurance claim. They are notorious for playing games\r\nwith personal injury and accident victim&#8217;s benefits.&#160; When this happens, the accident victim should\r\nhire the best possible Michigan car accident lawyer to handle their case.&#8221;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">A person may either pre-register to attend the No-Fault\r\nInstitute seminar or register on site as space permits. Registration begins at\r\n8:30 a.m. daily and is not only open to Michigan Association for Justice Members\r\nbut non-members as well. Depending on your membership will determine the charge\r\nfor registration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">About: Partner, attorney, and author Daniel L.\r\nBuckfire</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Daniel L. Buckfire graduated ******** laude from the\r\nprestigious University of Michigan Law School in 1991.&#160; He has been engaged in the private practice\r\nof law since his successful completion of the bar exam.&#160; He is the Managing Partner of the Law Firm of\r\nBuckfire &amp; Buckfire, P.C. </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Daniel L. Buckfire specializes in Michigan\r\nautomobile negligence cases, as well as no-fault insurance claims, dram shop liability,\r\nand general personal injury accident cases. His adept knowledge of these areas\r\nof law has resulted in numerous significant settlements and verdicts on behalf\r\nof his injured Michigan clients.&#160; He\r\nrecently settled a claim on behalf of car accident victim for $1,375,000.00. To\r\nlearn more about the law firm of Buckfire &amp; Buckfire, P.C. visit <a title="personal injury lawyers" href="http://www.buckfirelaw.com" target="&#95;blank">www.Buckfirelaw.com</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&#160;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&#160;</p><!--more-->(800) 606-1717 Partner, attorney and author, Daniel Buckfire of\r\nBuckfire &amp; Buckfire, P.C., is speaking at the 9th annual\r\nNo-Fault Institute presented by the Michigan Association for Justice.'
