aS'August 16, 2010 (by Ehline Law) Statistics show that civil lawsuits for injuries and <a href="http://www.ehlinelaw.com/pages/3420/expert&#95;losangeleswrongfuldeathattorneys.htm">wrongful death from vehicle accidents</a><p> has fallen approximately 46 percent from 2001-2002 and 2007-2008, which is the latest statistics available. \r\n\r\nIt is not unusual for personal injury lawyers to have television advertisements questioning if there have been injuries due to a vehicle crash and if this has caused undue expenses for medical bills and other responsibilities. \r\n\r\n</p><p>The answer to these questions in California according to the data is that less people are answering yes to those questions. The California Superior Courts total of civil lawsuits has been fixed at approximately 1.5 million. \r\n\r\nPersonal injury claims have dropped to some extent, but not to the degree of vehicle crash lawsuits, with the numbers of California claims in 2001-2002 by drivers, passengers and pedestrians numbered 52,809 for injuries, damage and wrongful death. The data shows the same time period during 2007-2008 there were 28,414 claims filed for the same reasons. \r\n\r\n</p><p>According to Administrative Office spokesman Philip R. Carrizosa, when emailed by California Watch, his answer was one cause of this decrease can be attributed to SB 668, which allows people more time to settle their case without the need to file a lawsuit. This also allowed victims of the September 11th terrorist attack more time to decide if they would take legal action against the airlines. California is now in line with most other states providing a two year statute of limitations and four years to file a lawsuit. Prior to this California was one of only four states that had a one year statute of limitations. \r\n\r\n</p><p>This law changed in 2002 allowing plaintiffs to have an extra year under the statute of limitations to file personal injury lawsuits. Another reason for the decline in personal injury lawsuits could be seen in the California Highway Patrol data that shows the roadways in California have seen less injuries and deaths in recent years. Injury accidents in 202 were 205,223 and total injuries were 310,689. In 2008 there was an approximate 16 percent drop in collisions and injuries dropped approximately 22 percent. \r\n\r\n</p><p><a href="http://www.ehlinelaw.com/pages/4092/san-francisco-personal-injury-attorney.htm" title="San Francisco personal injury attorney">San Francisco personal injury attorney</a>, Michael Ehline, stated one of the reasons for this drop in accident injuries could be due to improvements in safety, including the wearing of seatbelts and automotive safety equipment. Some of which result in <a href="http://www.ehlinelaw.com/pages/4096/sf-auto-defect-attorneys.htm">product liability lawsuits</a>.  \r\n\r\n</p><p>This has been a free public service message from:</p><p>Ehline Law | <a href="http://www.ehlinelaw.com/" title="accident attorney">Los Angeles Accident attorney</a>\r\n</p><p>633 West Fifth Street, 28th Floor\r\nLos Angeles, CA 90071,\r\n</p><p>213.596.9642\r\nhttp://www.ehlinelaw.com/;</p><p><a href="http://maps.google.com/places/us/ca/san-francisco/francisco-st/50/-ehline-law?gl=us">50 Francisco Street, Suite \r\n460, San Francisco, CA 94133</a> </p><p>(415) 684-7688 () \r\n(888) 480-9786 \r\n() </p><br /><p></p><!--more--><a href="http://www.ehlinelaw.com/" title="accident attorneys">Los Angeles accident attorney</a>, Michael Ehline, discusses the lessening of <a href="http://www.ehlinelaw.com/pages/3445/car-accident-law-california-dmv-codes.htm" title="motor vehicle accident lawsuits">motor vehicle accident lawsuits</a>.'
