aS'<p>&#160;Los Angeles and the surrounding areas including West Los Angeles, Pasadena, and <a href="http://www.ehlinelaw.com/pages/100049/torrance-car-accident-lawyer.htm">Torrance</a> are no stranger to heavy traffic and many traffic accidents.  In 2008, California had the highest number of traffic fatalities of all U.S. states.  In Los Angeles County alone, there were nearly 83,000 traffic accidents with 667 of those being fatal, and over 52,000 resulting in non-fatal injuries.  These extreme numbers emphasize the need for automobile drivers and passengers to keep safety in mind at all times.\r\n</p><p>\r\nInjuries to the driver or passengers in a car collision are financially and medically devastating.  Unfortunately, as serious as injuries can be, too few victims take them seriously at the time of the accident.  When there are serious external signs, it doesn&#8217;t even take a doctor to recognize that prompt medical care is needed.  However, many injuries following a car accident aren&#8217;t so obvious according to <a href="http://www.ehlinelaw.com/pages/3140/Auto-Accident-Lawyer-LA.htm">car accident lawyer Los Angeles</a>, Michael P.Ehline, Esq.  Some such injuries include:\r\n\r\n</p><ul><li>Head and brain injuries and trauma</li>\r\n<li>Neck and spine injuries</li>\r\n<li>Back injuries</li>\r\n<li>Internal organ damage</li></ul><p>\r\n\r\nWith the less obvious injuries, symptoms may take days or hours to appear.  Meanwhile, the damage goes unchecked until sometimes it goes too far to be fixed.  All injuries following a car accident should be taken very seriously and attended in a hospital setting.  While these expenses are high and intimidating, the victim can take comfort in knowing that medical testing and treatment can be facilitated immediately if the victim hires a car accident attorney.  </p><p>Attorneys like <a href="http://www.ehlinelaw.com/">car accident lawyer</a>, Michael Ehline, Esq., of Ehline Law Firm PC at 21250 Hawthorne Boulevard #500, Torrance, CA (424) 233-0709, can often facilitate medical testing and care even before the negligent party pays, and in cases where insurance balks or is insufficient.\r\n\r\nMedical costs are not the only financial tolls a victim will suffer following an accident.  Many accidents result in lost work time, expenses for child care if the victim is hospitalized, and sometimes loss ability to work at all or live independently.  They may even result in a lost family member.  </p><p>Many victims of more serious accidents will also require psychological treatment to deal with their trauma and anxiety.\r\n\r\nIf you or your loved one is the victim of a car accident due to another&#8217;s negligence, hiring a car accident attorney can help you not only get the medical care needed immediately, but also receive fair recompense for all losses due to the accident.  An attorney will not only fight for the victim&#8217;s rights, but also for their security and health. </p><!--more-->While these expenses are high and intimidating, the victim can take \r\ncomfort in knowing that medical testing and treatment can be facilitated\r\n immediately if the victim hires a car accident attorney.'
