aS'<p>As shown by recent studies, and the annual increase in incidence of <b>fatal motorcycle accidents</b>, the severity of an accident is often out of the control of the rider.&#160; With the recent death of a stuntrider in North Hollywood, we are reminded once more of this painful truth.&#160; April Stirton, 28, was riding on the Ventura Freeway Tuesday, April 6<sup>th</sup>, when she lost control of her bike.&#160; The resulting fall found her pinned under the back wheel of a tow truck where she was dragged for upwards of 100 feet and killed almost instantly.</p><p>According to <a href="http://www.ktla.com/news/landing/ktla-motorcycle-fatal-101,0,5711020.story">KTLA</a>, Stirton was well liked and very popular in her field, most famous for her appearances on the popular television series <i>CSI: Crime Scene Investigation</i>.&#160; As a professional rider, it appears as though Stirton&#8217;s accident was merely a tragic miscalculation, or a slight lapse of judgment.&#160; Witnesses say that she was wearing a helmet and obeying the speed limit at the time of her <a href="http://www.blackmanlegal.com/CM/PracticeAreaDescriptions/PracticeAreaDescriptions38.asp">fatal accident</a>.</p><p><i>The <a href="http://www.blackmanlegal.com/">personal injury lawyers</a> at <a href="http://www.blackmanlegal.com/">Blackman Legal Group</a>, a California-based law firm founded by renowned trial attorney, <a href="http://www.blackmanlegal.com/CM/Custom/Attorneys.asp#Blackman">Clifford Blackman</a>, has been representing injury victims since 1976, and have special expertise in cases involving <a href="http://www.spinal-injury-california.com/">spinal cord injury</a>, <a href="http://www.brain-injury-lawyer.com/">traumatic brain injury</a>, <a href="http://www.personal-injury-san-francisco.net/burn-injury.php">burn injury</a>, <a href="http://www.personal-injury-san-francisco.net/personal-injury-overview.php">catastrophic injuries</a> and <a href="http://www.wrongful-death-lawfirm.com/">wrongful death</a>.&#160; The nationwide toll-free number to call for a free consultation is <b>1-888-395-3551.</b></i></p>'
