aS'<p>After the divorce puts a dent in your normal activities and leaves you feeling friendless, there are several things you can do to feel less alone.&#160; Some of these include &#8212;</p><ul><li><strong>Consult with a spiritual adviser.</strong>&#160; Particularly for those who already have an active spiritual life, meeting with a trusted spiritual guide, such as your pastor, priest, or rabbi, can be very comforting at this time.</li><li><strong>Receive counseling.</strong>&#160; Meeting with a licensed family psychologist or a skilled counselor often helps newly divorced individuals get themselves on the fast track to emotional and psychological recovery.</li><li><strong>Join a divorce support group or moderated divorce class.</strong>&#160; Either of these is an opportunity to receive advice on dealing with your divorce and a chance to meet others going through the same situation&#8212;those who do so may also make good friends.</li><li><strong>Join an online <a href="http://www.divorcesupport.com/" target="&#95;blank">divorce support</a> group</strong>.&#160; While less personal than meeting physically as a group with local recent divorcees, the anonymity sometimes helps a person deal with particularly difficult or personal matters.</li><li><strong>Taking up new social activities</strong>.&#160; Consider getting involved in volunteering or perhaps join an intramural coed sport team.&#160; Any new activity that helps you define yourself as a new and whole individual&#8212;and introduces you to potential new friends and new horizons?&#8212;can only help your recovery.</li></ul><p>For <a href="www.williamcremins.com/en/aop/Knoxville Divorce Law Firms.aspx" target="&#95;self">divorce mediation in Knoxville</a> contact&#160;William C.&#160;Cremins&#160;who can help you navigate through all aspects of divorce.<p><strong>William C. Cremins</strong><br />810 Henley Street<br />Knoxville<br />TN 37902<br />(865) 546-7124</p></p><!--more--><p>For <a href="www.williamcremins.com/en/aop/Knoxville Divorce Law Firms.aspx">Knoxville divorce mediation</a>&#160;contact&#160;William C.&#160;Cremins&#160;who can help you navigate through all aspects of divorce.</p>'
