aS'\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">As a <a href="http://www.texastriallawyers.com/texas-truck-accidents-lawyer.php">commercial vehicle accident lawyer</a> &#8211; specializing in <a href="http://www.texastriallawyers.com/texas-truck-accidents-lawyer.php">Texas semi truck accident</a>s but interested and concerned about any related topic &#8211; I recently\r\nresearched the subject of traffic congestion. </p><p class="MsoNormal">It is a fact that regular\r\nextended waits in traffic jams contribute to incidences of road rage &#8211; and\r\nfrankly, who among us has not felt our blood pressure rise when we&#8217;ve happened\r\nupon an unexpected line of cars and trucks at a literal standstill on roadways\r\nmeant to be traversed at sixty or so miles per hour? Only the most\r\naccommodating among us are able to internalize this inconvenience as part of\r\nlife&#8217;s expectations. </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">According to the Texas Department of Transportation a 2005\r\nUrban Mobility Study found that &#8220;many of Texas\' metropolitan areas are within the top 85 congested areas <i>in the country</i>. Houston ranked fifth for\r\ntraveler delay and Dallas-Fort Worth ranked sixth&#8221;. </p><p class="MsoNormal">For those of us who live and work in the area\r\nthis bit of news comes as no surprise. Moreover, the information is more than\r\nfive years old which likely means that road congestion has only increased over\r\ntime &#8211; after all there is a definite and significant lag time between the\r\ncollection of findings, their reporting, assigning engineers to consider the\r\nproblem and create solutions and then to the final building and completion of\r\nnew roads that will help to alleviate the problem.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Alternative\r\nsolutions to adding more highways to the already hundreds of thousands of miles\r\nof road that are already in existence in Texas include carpooling, toll roads\r\nand lane restrictions. Probably a combination of all three as well as road\r\nconstruction will be the only viable solution. Meanwhile, pack your patience.&#160;</p><p class="MsoNormal">Greg Baumgartner is a <a href="http://www.texastriallawyers.com">Houston 18 wheeler accident attorne</a>y and the founder of the Baumgartner law firm, which is dedicated to helping personal injury victims seek civil justice. If you would like to speak with an <a href="http://www.texastriallawyers.com">18 wheeler accident lawyer in Houston</a> call the Baumgartner firm.&#160;</p><p class="MsoNormal"></p><p class="MsoNormal"></p>\r\n\r\n<!--more-->Texas has some of the most congested traffic in the nation which results in larger numbers of serious Texas personal injury and wrongful death claims.&#160;'
