aS'-Blog posted but not reviewed or edited by LedgerLaw- <div></div><div><p class="MsoNormal">It is never pleasant to be involved in an accident. This is especially so if you injure yourself in the process, so much so that your health and your work is affected. If you are the sole breadwinner in your family, this can be very painful and affect all aspects of your life. However, do not fret because there is something you can do as a result of the accident. For instance, if you have slipped and fell in your office building or while at work, and sustained injuries as a result of the fall, then you are definitely eligible to claim for personal injury against your employers. As such, you would need to retain the services of a personal injury lawyer.</p><p class="MsoNormal" /><p>&#160;</p><p /><p class="MsoNormal">First of all, details are very important in making a personal injury lawsuit. Your personal injury lawyer would need certain information such as the date and time that the accident happened. This is especially so if it occurred as a result of your employer&#8217;s negligence. It would also be helpful if there were witnesses during the time of your fall. These witnesses could possibly be required to be called upon should the lawsuit be brought to court. Do not worry overmuch about this step at the early stages of your personal injury lawsuit because your lawyers would just need to file away this information for later use.</p><p class="MsoNormal" /><p>&#160;</p><p /><p class="MsoNormal">Next, your injury would of course need to be assessed by a doctor. Even before applying for a lawsuit, you need to get this done first because chances are you would want to claim for insurance as well. This step is equally important because it will let your lawyer know just how much you have lost due to the slip in terms of injuries, length of time it takes for you to recover, and extent of the injuries. If , for some odd reason, you are worried about the repercussions of filing a personal injury lawsuit against your employer, do remember that it isn&#8217;t personal. You are just protecting your interest and the best way to do it would be through your personal injury lawyer.</p><p class="MsoNormal" /><p>&#160;</p><p /><p class="MsoNormal">At the end of the day, if all safety procedures had been put in place, you would not have slipped and fallen, nor would you have been injured. A personal injury claim is the best way for you to gain back some compensation for the hurt and trouble that has been caused as a result of your fall.</p><p class="MsoNormal" /><p>&#160;</p><p /><p /><p>Ledger&#160;Law Firm<br />811 Wilshire Blvd<br />Suite 1000<br />Los Angeles, CA 90017<br />Office: 213-493-6588<br />Toll Free 800-300-0001<br />Website: <a href="http://www.ledgerlaw.com/">LedgerLaw</a></p><p /></div>'
