aS'<p>The California Department of Corrections has announced that it has chosen to close the the Southern Youth Correctional Reception Center in Norwalk on December 31, 2011.&#160;</p><p>All children committed to the Division of Juvenile Justice begin their time at a Reception Center Clinic. &#160;Besides the Southern Youth Correctional Reception Center &amp; Clinic, there is the Ventura Youth Correctional Facility in Ventura that has a bed capacity of 69. The Norwalk facility has a bed capacity of 40. &#160;</p><p>The purpose of the reception centers is to identify population safety issues and mental health screenings. &#160;A Suicide Risk Assessment Questionnaire are completed within one hour. &#160; &#160;An Academic Evaluation is also done. &#160;This consists of a Comprehensive Adult Student Assessment System, English Language Arts, math Diagnostic, Holland Vocational Inventory and California English Language Development test. &#160;Academic Records are also reviewed to identify achievement level and children in need of special education services. &#160;Psychological testing is also administered. &#160;The assessment instruments are the Weinberger Adjustment Inventory, Massachusetts Youth Screening Instrument Youth Self Report, Kaufman Brief Intelligence Test 2, Voice Diagnoistic Interview Schedule for children and the Drug Experience Questionnaire. &#160;If a child scores below 70 in the Kaufman Brief Intelligence, then the Weschler\'s Intelligence Scale for children or the Weschler\'s Adult Intelligence Scale is administered. &#160;</p><p>Southern California has gone thru two prior closures and this will make it the third. If the Southern Youth Reception Center &amp; Clinic is closed the impact would cause children to be transferred to Ventura Youth Correctional Facility or to the N. A. Chaderjian Youth Correctional Facility in Stockton according to employees at the Southern Youth Correctional Reception Center and Clinic. &#160;A local <a href="http://www.topjuveniledefender.com" title="Los Angeles Criminal Defense Attorney">Los Angeles Criminal Defense Attorney</a>&#160;was informed by Norwalk DJJ employees about the pending closure. &#160;&#160;Norwalk DJJ employees state that SYCRCC has the highest number of family visitors and highest number of volunteers at all DJJ facilities. &#160;Jack B. Clark High School at SYCRCC is the #1 ranked high school in DJJ. &#160;Employees also note the economic impact it will have on families of children housed at SYCRCC. &#160;It would be difficult for parents to visit their children as often as they would like. &#160;DJJ employees at SYCRCC are asking the Governor to reconsider and close the Chaderjian Youth Correctional Facility in Stockton instead. &#160;</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p>'
