aS'<p>A good question to ask yourself before you sell your annuity, is if you have\r\nanother regular source of income that will see you through your retirement\r\nyears (maybe this is not such an important question to ask if you have a\r\nterminal disease).&#160;&#160; Another element to consider before you sell, is\r\nthe company with which you choose to sell, are they another AIG that hasn\'t\r\ngotten caught yet?&#160; Laws and regulation exist on a Federal and State level\r\nin most states (47 states out of 50) protecting the consumer, but that does not\r\nmean that all companies are abiding by the rules.&#160; A good lawyer with a\r\nstrong moral compass, like <b>Eugene Ahtirski</b> could help enforce the law on your\r\nbehalf.&#160; It never used to be this way until recently.&#160; <br />\r\n<br />\r\nOrganizations that can verify the good standing of a company&#160; also exist,\r\nlike, the NASAA (National American Securities Administrators Association)\r\ndesigned to protect the consumer and has been doing so since 1919, <br />\r\n<a href="http://www.nasaa.org/home/index.cfm">http://www.nasaa.org/home/index.cfm</a>.&#160;\r\n<br />\r\nThe website of the Department of Insurance for California is another good\r\nwebsite, (<a href="http://insurance.ca.gov/">http://insurance.ca.gov/</a>)\r\nwhere the Insurance Commissioner lives can be extremely helpful, but cannot\r\nadvise you on when and who to sell to.&#160; A lawyer like <b>Eugene Ahtirski</b> well\r\nversed in the changing legislature that surrounds annuities can alert you the\r\nconsumer as to when to sell, what tax laws exist that can hurt or benefit the\r\nsale of your annuity.</p><p><a href="http://eahtirski.com" title="Eugene Ahtirski">Eugene Ahtirski</a></p><p>\r\n</p><p><a href="http://structuredsettlementatty.com" title="Structured Settlement Attorney">Structured Settlement Attorney</a></p><p><a href="http://structuredsettlementexpert.co" title="Structured Settlement Expert">Structured Settlement Expert</a></p><p><a href="http://StructuredSettlementAdvisor.info" title="Structured Settlement Advisor">Structured Settlement Advisor</a></p><p><a href="http://cabankruptcyatty.com" title="Bankruptcy Attorney">Bankruptcy Attorney</a></p><p><a href="http://cabankruptcyatty.com" title="Bankruptcy Attorney"></a></p><p><a href="http://cabankruptcyatty.com" title="Bankruptcy Attorney"></a></p><p><a href="http://cabankruptcyatty.com" title="Bankruptcy Attorney"></a></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p>\r\n</p><!--more-->What to Look Out For When Selling Your Annuity or Structured Settlement. Things factoring or funding companies may not tell you.'
