aS'<p>Whenever involved in a car accident in San Bernardino getting an experienced car accident lawyer is the best way to go. There are a lot of damages that might happen as a result of the accident and having an experienced San Bernardino car accident lawyer can go over what a person is entitled to get back after the accident. \r\n\r\nMany people are surprised by all of the bills that can come after the accident. </p><p>There\'s not only the car accident to think about but sometimes medical bills. That\'s why when involved in a car accident in San Bernardino it\'s important to always keep the receipts of everything that happens, including the damage that happens to the car. \r\n\r\nIf the car gets totaled as a result of the accident, some people take the adjuster\'s word and estimate of how much the car might be worth. </p><p>Never automatically do that. Research newspapers, auto magazines, classified ads online and keep in mind what the year of the car is plus the model, make, mileage and what kind of condition it was in and what equipment the car had. All of this information will help with being able to decide the value of the car. \r\n\r\nAlways pay expenses out of the pocket with either credit cards or checks. When cash is used, always keep the receipt. </p><p>Getting a folder and putting a label on the folder plus receipts might help to make the process go faster. Ask the <a href="http://www.ehlinelaw.com/pages/100045/san-bernardino-car-accident-attorneys.htm" title="san bernardino car accident attorney">San Bernardino car accident lawyer</a> questions. Make sure to let the lawyer know how much money was put in the car. Never be afraid to tell the lawyer how much money was spent on the car. Holding back information might hurt the case and the victims of the car accident might not get as much back because they didn\'t tell the lawyer everything.\r\n</p><p>\r\nBefore it&#8217;s time to talk with the lawyer, go through all of the receipts. Make sure that everything is there. Highlight important ones and write down dates when needed to help the case. The more information that the lawyer has about how much the car is worth and what was spent after the accident happened, the better. \r\nKeep medical bills in a separate folder and make sure that the lawyer has all of the information in regards to the medical bills. It&#8217;s best to double check everything twice instead of leaving something important out.\r\n\r\n</p><p>Michael Ehline, Esq., is a highly experienced personal injury attorney who is here to assist injured victims in car crash and transportation injury accident cases.&#160; Contact us at: </p><p>6700 East Pacific Coast Highway<br />#275, Long Beach, CA 90803<br />(562) 342-9092</p><!--more-->The more information that the lawyer has about how much the car is worth\r\n and what was spent after the accident happened, the better. Michael Ehline, Esq., is a highly experienced personal injury attorney who is here to assist injured victims in car crash and transportation injury accident cases.&#160; Contact us at: 6700 East Pacific Coast Highway\r\nSuite 275, Long Beach, CA 90803\r\n(562) 342-9092'
