aS'<p class="MsoNoSpacing"><b>Kennedy Clark &amp; Williams, PC Welcomes New Attorneys</b></p><p /><p class="MsoNoSpacing"><i></i><p /><p class="MsoNoSpacing"><i>Dallas-based IP law and business litigation firm gains additional expertise to manage growing practice</i></p><p /><p class="MsoNoSpacing"><i></i><p /><p class="MsoNormal"><b>(DALLAS) Feb. 16, 2011 &#8211; </b>Kennedy Clark &amp; Williams<b> </b>has expanded its growing practice with the addition of attorneys Walter G. (&#8220;Bob&#8221;) Pettey, III and Kenneth P. Kula.&#160; </p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" /><p>&#160;</p><p /><p class="MsoNormal">Bob Pettey, Of Counsel to the Firm, has over 30 years of experience in commercial and business litigation before trial and appellate courts and administrative agencies.&#160; Over the past 6 years Bob has arbitrated cases as a member of the Commercial Arbitration Panel of the American Arbitration Association&#8217;s National Roster of Neutrals.&#160; He earned his Juris Doctorate from the University of Alabama and received his bachelor&#8217;s degree from Washington &amp; Lee University.&#160; &#160;&#160;</p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" /><p>&#160;</p><p /><p class="MsoNormal">Ken Kula has joined the Firm as a Member.&#160; Mr. Kula focuses his practice on intellectual property litigation and technology law.&#160; He has represented major Fortune 500 companies, small businesses, private individuals, inventors, entertainment personalities, recording artists and authors.&#160; He earned his Juris Doctorate from Washburn University and received his bachelor&#8217;s degree from St. John Fisher College.&#160; </p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" /><p>&#160;</p><p /><p class="MsoNoSpacing">&#8220;Since 2006, this Firm has experienced great success in intellectual property law and commercial litigation.&#160; The additions of Bob Pettey and Ken Kula to Kennedy Clark &amp; Williams will only enhance our Firm&#8217;s presence and further our growth strategy,&#8221; said shareholder <a href="http://www.kcwfirm.com/pdf/Bio&#95;Kennedy.pdf">Stephen A. Kennedy</a>. &#8220;We are expanding our practice while continuing our focus on intellectual property, business litigation and employment law.&#160; It&#8217;s what we do every day.&#8221;</p><p /><p class="MsoNormal"><b></b><p /><p class="MsoNormal"><b>About Kennedy, Clark &amp; Williams, PC</b></p><p /><p class="MsoNoSpacing">Kennedy, Clark &amp; Williams, PC is a Dallas-based commercial litigation boutique that represents clients in the fields of intellectual property, labor and employment, technology, commercial and business litigation. KCW focuses on patent, trademark and copyright infringement, misappropriation of trade secrets, and business technology disputes. The firm also represents clients in commercial, business, employment and construction disputes. To learn more about the firm, please visit <a href="http://www.kcwfirm.com/">www.kcwfirm.com</a>. </p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" /><p>&#160;</p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" /><p>&#160;</p><p /></p><p>&#160;</p></p><p>&#160;</p></p><p>&#160;</p>'
