aS'<p>-Blog posted but not reviewed or edited by LedgerLaw-</p><p>A lot of factors contribute to and inevitably determine the outcome of any court case. However, one of the most important factors that can make or mar any case is the choice of attorney. For injury cases, the choice of personal injury attorney goes a long way in determining whether you will be compensated adequately for injuries sustained. As such, the selection of a personal injury attorney should only be done after conducting a careful search. This shouldn&#8217;t be too difficult; what is required is the ability to look out for certain traits and qualities. These include the following.</p><p><b>Experience</b></p><p>When talking about a personal injury attorney&#8217;s experience, certain things must be understood. Experience doesn&#8217;t just refer to the number of years a personal injury attorney has spent on litigation. The key word is actually relevant experience. For instance, if you have been involved in a case of motorcycle accident, then the personal injury attorney you need to consider is one who specializes in motorcycle accident cases. The same thing applies to other personal injury cases: always seek out a personal injury attorney experienced in handling the specific case you have been involved in.</p><p><b>Past Verdicts</b></p><p>In the world of injury litigation, one of the yardsticks for measuring the quality of a personal injury attorney is the verdict obtained. The quality of verdicts obtained for previous clients serves as a pointer for determining and assessing whether the attorney has the potential of obtaining favorable verdicts in your own case. Thus, you should ask for previous verdicts obtained and confirm the veracity. This shouldn&#8217;t be difficult however because a successful personal injury attorney will not hesitate to inform you about his or her previous conquests.</p><p><b>Terms of Service</b></p><p>Selection of a personal injury attorney also entails understanding the attorney&#8217;s terms of service. Before making a final decision, you need to be clear about the agreement between you and the personal injury attorney particularly as this relates to his or her fee. Most personal injury attorneys work under a CFA i.e. a conditional fee agreement. This is also sometimes referred to as contingency basis and it simply means that the attorney will only get paid a certain percentage of the total settlement if the case is won. The percentage varies greatly from attorney to attorney and you should ensure that you get a fair deal before hiring any attorney. </p><p /><p>Law Offices of Ledger &amp; Associates<br />811 Wilshire Blvd<br />Suite 1000<br />Los Angeles, CA 90017<br />Office: 213-493-6588<br />Toll Free 800-300-0001<br />Website: <a href="http://www.injurylawyergroup.com">www.injurylawyergroup.com</a></p><p /><!--more-->A lot of factors contribute to and inevitably determine the outcome of any court case. However, one of the most important factors that can make or mar any case is the choice of attorney. For injury cases, the choice of personal injury attorney goes a long way in determining whether you will be compensated adequately for injuries sustained. As such, the selection of a personal injury attorney should only be done after conducting a careful search. This s'
